title: western sandwiches
directions: About 35 minutes before serving, in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat, in hot margarine, cook onion until tender about 5 minutes.
Add ham.
Meanwhile, in a large bowl with fork, beat eggs, milk and salt until well mixed.
Stir into ham mixture. Reduce heat to low; cover and cook 12 to 15 minutes, until top is set and underside is lightly browned.
Serve egg mixture between bread slices.
Makes 4 servings.

title: praline coffee
directions: In a Dutch oven, combine coffee, milk and sugar.
Stirring occasionally, cook over medium-high heat until mixture begins to boil; remove from heat.
Stir in ice cream, vodka, vanilla and maple flavoring.
Serve hot.
Yield: about twenty 6 ounce servings.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Make jello.
Let set for 2 or 3 hours.
Then fold in remaining ingredients.

title: pasta with shrimp and garlic
directions: Cook pasta according to directions.
While pasta is cooking, melt butter or margarine in a 3-quart saucepan.
Add all ingredients, except tomatoes and cheese.
Stir and cook over medium heat for 5 minutes or until shrimp are cooked.
Add cooked spaghetti and heat through.
Add tomatoes and stir until tomatoes are hot.
Sprinkle with cheese and serve.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese. Pour into greased baking sheet.
Pour sauce as the next layer and put any other toppings you like (hamburger, sausage, pepperoni, onions, green pepper).
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over top and sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.	Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth. Gradually beat in sugar. Blend sour cream and vanilla. Fold in whipped cream. Blend well. Chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Garnish with strawberries or pineapple.

title: stir-fry vegetables
directions: Put a little oil and soy sauce in frypan along with vegetables.
Cook until vegetables are soft.

title: hidden valley ranch pinwheels
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Spread on tortillas.
Sprinkle on remaining ingredients, then roll and wrap tightly.
Chill 2 hours.
Cut off ends.
Slice rolls into pieces.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: stuffing topped swiss chicken
directions: Spray a 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole dish with nonstick cooking spray.
Split each chicken breast and stuff it with a piece of Swiss cheese.
Put stuffed chicken pieces in casserole dish.

title: fresh beef brisket
directions: Over medium heat, cook onions in oil until tender.
Add chili sauce to remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling and remove from heat.

title: oatmeal toll house cookies
directions: Sift flour with soda and salt.
Cream shortening until soft. Add sugar gradually and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Add hot water.
Add dry ingredients.
Add nutmeats, chocolate chips, oatmeal and vanilla. Blend.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: olive omelet
directions: Cut olives into large pieces.
Melt butter in 10-inch skillet; add celery and onions and cover and cook slowly 10 minutes. Separate eggs and beat yolks well.
Combine with milk.
Add salt to egg whites and beat until stiff.
Fold in egg yolk mixture, olives, onions, celery and pepper.
Turn into same skillet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until top springs when touched. Crease and fold in half.
Serve with well seasoned tomato sauce.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Mix cottage cheese and sour cream together.
Brown meat, oregano, onion, tomato sauce, garlic salt and pepper.
Put down noodles, then meat mixture, then noodles, sout cream mixture and then noodles.
Top off with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: half time chili
directions: Prepare chili according to package directions using ground turkey or ground beef.
Add corn and chilies with tomato sauce. Serve topped with shredded cheese.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: mexican spaghetti
directions: Cook ground beef in a large skillet.
Add chopped onion. Cook spaghetti separately until done.
In a separate bowl, mix tomatoes, picante and cumin.
Add beef.
In a casserole dish, mix spaghetti and beef together.
Add one cup of cheese to top.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: pepper steak
directions: Marinate cut up steak for 1/2 hour in soy sauce and cornstarch.
Cut green peppers and onions.
Stir-fry in oil over high heat for about 1 minute, then add beef.
Add sugar and salt. Serve over rice.

title: shortcake
directions: Mix and spread in pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: In a large skillet, brown chops in Wesson oil, remove and set aside.
Add onion and celery and cook lightly.
Drain oil and stir in remaining ingredients.
Replace chops and bring to a boil. Cover, lower heat and let simmer for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: lasagne
directions: Mix together the sauce mix, tomato sauce, water and butter. Simmer for 15 minutes, covered.
Stir occasionally.
Brown ground beef; drain fat and add to sauce.
(Sauce can also be used for spaghetti.)

title: fluffy coconut frosting
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Blend in sugar, milk and extract.
Fold in whipped topping and coconut.
Makes 4 cups or enough to frost tops and sides of two 8 or 9-inch cake layers or a 13 x 9-inch cake.

title: fudgie brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 9-inch square pan with foil. Grease foil.
Melt chocolate and butter in double boiler.
Cool 15 minutes.
Stir sugar, eggs, vanilla and flour into chocolate. Pour in prepared pan, spreading evenly.
Top with walnuts.

title: slush dessert
directions: Pat nuts, flour and butter into 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix cheese, sugar and Cool Whip together until smooth.
In a separate bowl, mix instant pudding with milk.
Spread cream cheese mixture over crust.
Cover with layer of Cool Whip.
Garnish with chopped nuts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix meal, flour and onion well and gradually add buttermilk until dough reaches proper consistency.
Dip by rounded spoonfuls into hot, deep fat in which fish has been fried.
Serve hot.

title: praline grahams
directions: Separate crackers in fourths.
Lay side by side on cookie sheet.
Mix butter and sugar; melt until boils and thickens.
Pour over crackers and spread evenly.
Spread pecans evenly over top. Bake 12 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet and place on wax paper to cool.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Saute onion in butter until transparent.
Do not brown.
Mix together ground beef, salt, bread crumbs, egg and pineapple juice. Add onion.
Form into bite size balls.
Place on rack and bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Put a layer of cracker crumbs on bottom of baking dish.
Cover with layer of oysters.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dot with butter.
Repeat with another layer of each (cracker crumbs, oysters, etc.) and end with crumbs and butter on top.
Add milk to cover.
Bake about 20 minutes in hot oven.
You may have to cook longer than 20 minutes.
If using standard oysters, you don't need to cut in two, but if large, cut in two.
Preheat oven for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cook for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: old time fruit pudding
directions: Mix every ingredient well.
Add berries last.
Bake in a greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for about 30 minutes. Recipe can be doubled for larger pan.
Good plain or with milk or ice cream.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix and pour into 9 x 12-inch dish; chill until firm.

title: raisin pie
directions: Combine lemon juice, orange juice, sugar, raisins and 1 1/4 cups water and heat to boiling.
Add pinch of salt.
Mix flour and remaining 1/2 cup water to a smooth paste and add to mixture gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add butter or margarine.
Cool in refrigerator while preparing pie crusts.

title: peach jello
directions: Puree peaches in blender.
Add Jell-O to boiling water; dissolve.
Add blended peaches and juice.
Make Dream Whip; add cream cheese.
Blend and add to Jell-O mixture.

title: stuffed sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut potatoes into halves lengthwise. Scoop pulp out from potato halves into mixing bowl, leaving 1/4-inch shells.
Mash pulp; reserve shells.
Add remaining ingredients to potato pulp; stir to combine.
Spoon potato mixture evenly into reserved shells; place on baking sheet and bake until heated through, about 10 minutes.

title: crazy cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: mom hall's date-nut balls
directions: Melt butter and sugar together in a pan; add dates and cook until boiling.
Remove from heat.
Beat eggs; add milk and salt. Beat egg mixture into hot date batter.
Return to stove and boil for 2 minutes.
Let cool.
Stir in nuts, cereal and vanilla. Shape into balls and roll in coconut.
These are very rich and wonderful!

title: icing for sheath cake
directions: Put oleo, cocoa and milk in pan; heat to a boil. Remove from heat and add sifted powdered sugar. Blend well; add vanilla and nuts. Pour over hot cake.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Mix together the sweet potatoes, butter and milk until well blended.
Stir in the flour, baking soda and sugar.
Shape the dough into a ball and knead about 8 to 10 times on a well floured board.
Roll the dough out 1-inch thick and cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Bake in a greased baking pan at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: raisin sauce (ham)
directions: Mix brown sugar, mustard and cornstarch.
Slowly add lemon juice, vinegar, water and raisins.
Stir over low heat until thick.

title: alex's shrimp chili
directions: Well, first off, you got to wait until the first "killin' frost".
Back home to South Carolina that's usually tween Thanksgiving and Christmas.

Then you pick out a sloat bout 120 to 140 pounds (you want him to dress out around 90 to 100 pounds). Now a axe head works good but most folks generally use a bullet to start things off (or end things up, pending on if'n you're the people or the pig).
You got to stick the carcass real quick or else it won't drain good and the meat will be bloodshot.

title: cream cheese cranberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and cranberry sauce until thick and clear; cool.
Blend cheese with 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Add vanilla and milk.
Spread cold sauce over bottom of shell.
Pour cheese mixture on top and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 350° and bake 50 minutes.

title: spicy broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli florets.
Trim and peel stems.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Place broccoli in a steamer basket over boiling water; steam 2 to 3 minutes.
Refresh under cold water.
Drain well.

title: simple chili
directions: Brown beef and drain.
In a large pot combine beef, tomato juice, chili beans (can use less beans or no beans if desired), and 2-Alarm mix.
(I leave out the packet of masa, this only makes the chili thick.)
Heat thoroughly.
Serve topped with shredded cheese with some crackers on the side.
For an excellent Frito pie, just add Fritos, onions and relish.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes and line 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix next six ingredients and spread over potatoes, then spread crushed corn flakes.
Next, drizzle other melted oleo on corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: heavenly salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Allow to cool.
To cream cheese add pineapple and nuts.
Stir into jello. Fold in cool whip and pour into mold.
Chill and serve when firm.

title: marilyn's cheap chili
directions: Brown meat, onion, green pepper and seasonings.
Add other ingredients and simmer 45 minutes, covered.
Add only enough water to soup cans to swish them out, then add to other ingredients.
Two cans of soup is sufficient.
Use three cans for stretching recipe or thinning chili.

title: carribean milk cooler
directions: Combine all ingredients except ice in covered shaker and shake vigorously until frothy.
Pour into tall glass filled with ice.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients (can add 1 cup raisins).
Pour into broiler pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lollipop cookies
directions: You will also need 24 to 30 wooden sticks with rounded ends.

title: marinated brisket
directions: Rub seasoning on brisket of about 3 to 4 pounds.
Make sure to rub both sides.
Place brisket in foil-lined pan and pour in sauce mixture.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in oven at 250° for 6 to 7 hours.
Place pan of water underneath while cooking.
Drippings make good gravy.

title: caramel apple pie
directions: For pastry: In a bowl, stir together 1 1/4 cups flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Cut shortening into flour.	Sprinkle 1 teaspoon of water over flour.
Mix.
Keep adding 1 teaspoon of water until mixture is moist.
Form dough into a ball; set aside.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on large round tray.
Pour salsa over cream cheese; spread shredded lettuce on salsa.
Pour tomatoes on lettuce.
Top everything with shredded lettuce.
Use tortilla chips to scoop up Mexican dip and enjoy.

title: berry-sauced poached pears
directions: Peel and core pears, leaving the stem intact.
Cut a thin slice off the bottom of each pear so pears will stand upright. In a large saucepan combine water and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil
Add whole pears.
Return to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes or until pears are tender, turning once.
Transfer pears and cooking liquid to a mixing bowl.
Cover and chill for 3 to 24 hours.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Line bottom of pan with crescent rolls.
Spread mustard over crust (coat).
Saute zucchini, onion and parsley in butter until zucchini is just tender.
Cool slightly.
Mix together with beaten eggs and cheese.
Add oregano, basil, salt and pepper.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Let stand before slicing.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry or microwave bacon.
Dice celery and onions and fry in bacon fat, then drain.
Boil potatoes.
Cool, peel and slice in casserole.
Combine in 2-quart saucepan in order given, stirring after each addition.
Boil until thick and pour over potatoes. Add celery and onions.
Break up bacon on top.
Parsley is optional.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Stir all together in a bowl and freeze.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix flour, salt, baking powder and shortening.
Add water or chicken broth, just enough to make the dough the consistency of pie dough.
Roll out the dough to thickness of newspaper cut into inch square.
Drop slowly, one at a time, into the hot chicken broth, stirring constantly.

title: easy pork chop casserole
directions: Place chops in casserole and sprinkle with ingredients in order listed.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Keep watch and keep rice pushed down into liquid.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw
broccoli (do not cook).
Mix the first 6 ingredients together in mixing bowl.
Pour into greased Pyrex baking dish. Melt
stick
margarine
and mix with 1 stack of Ritz crackers (crushed) and spread over top of casserole.
Bake 45 minutes
Done when firm.
If soupy, casserole is not done.

title: chiffon cake
directions: Beat whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Sift sugar, salt, baking powder, flour, oil, yolks, water and vanilla.
Then fold together ingredients.
Pour into Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 60 minutes and then at 350° for 5 minutes.

title: crazy crunch
directions: Mix popped corn and pecans on a greased cookie sheet. Combine sugar, margarine and syrup in a 1 1/2-quart saucepan. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil 10 to 15 minutes or until mixture turns to light caramel. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and pour over popped corn. Mix to coat and spread to dry. Break apart. Store in tightly covered container.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes and mash them.
Add all other ingredients.
Turn into casserole and heat until bubbly hot.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together; combine remaining ingredients and add to the first 5 ingredients.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Pour mixture into pans and bake 50 minutes at 350°. Bread is nice and moist.

title: best-ever christmas cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg, honey and flavoring.
Blend flour, soda and salt; stir in.
Chill dough.
Heat oven to 375°.
On floured surface, roll dough 1/4 inch thick.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place 1 inch apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
When cool, ice and decorate as desired.
Makes about 5 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; cook over medium to low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool. Clean and prepare fresh strawberries; slice and arrange in baked 9-inch pie crust.
Pour mixture over strawberries.
Top with whipped topping just before serving.

title: baked hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix all together, except cracker crumbs and butter.
Then sprinkle cracker crumbs with melted butter.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. For your family, double recipe and bake in a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: pineapple bars
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs; add vanilla, almond flavoring, flour and pineapple juice.
Mix well; spread 3/4 of batter in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pineapple over batter. Cover with remaining batter and swirl with knife.
Bake at 350° until done.
Frost with glaze.

title: delicious brownies
directions: Grease and flour a jelly roll pan.
Mix all ingredients and pour in prepared pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: french apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix sugar, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt into bowl.
Stir in apples. Pour into pie crust.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Saute onion & garlic. Dredge beef cubes in flour; brown in oil. Add other ingredients, add enough water to make gravy; simmer until all flavors blend. Serve over hot cooked noodles.

title: taco salad dip
directions: First Layer:
Mix mayo, sour cream and taco seasoning.

title: pistachio inside-outside cake
directions: Blend together; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Grease and flour Bundt or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes (Bundt pan) or 30 minutes (9 x 13-inch).
Cool cake for 15 minutes if in bundt pan and then remove and cool on rack for 20 minutes more (leave in pan if a 9 x 13-inch).
Split into 2 layers (if Bundt).

title: spicy bacon pasta
directions: Heat the oil and cook bacon.
Cut into 1-inch strips.
When bacon is crispy, transfer to paper towel to drain.
Discard half of bacon drippings.
Saute onion in remaining fat until tender. After mashing tomatoes, add onion with pepper flakes.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Cook and drain pasta.
Serve sauce over pasta, topped with bacon.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts in bottom along with a little powdered sugar.
Mix everything together except frosting; mix for 2 minutes.	Stir the frosting into batter.	Bake 55 minutes at 350°.

title: buffet lasagne
directions: In skillet, brown beef with onion and garlic.
Pour off fat. Add salt, oregano, basil, tomato paste and water.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pinwheels
directions: Combine Crisco, sugar, salt, vanilla and egg and beat thoroughly.
Sift together flour and soda.
Add to Crisco mixture and blend.
Divide dough in half.
Add melted chocolate in half of the dough and blend.
Put each dough section on large piece of waxed paper.
Cover with a second piece of waxed paper and roll each dough to 1/8-inch thickness.
Place chocolate sheet of dough on top of other sheet of dough.
Roll up lengthwise using waxed paper as a pusher and making sure the layers fit.
Twist ends of dough together.
Chill overnight.
Cut in 1/8-inch slices and place on greased baking sheets.
Bake in moderately hot oven (375°) for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Combine cake mix, salad dressing, eggs, water and cinnamon, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Stir in carrots and walnuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool and spread with frosting.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Drain liquids from pineapple chunks and orange sections.
Add marshmallows and coconut and sour cream; mix well.
Put in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter. Add cheese and milk; stir until blended and melted. Dissolve bouillon in boiling water. Add to cheese mixture. Stir in broccoli and lemon juice. Heat through.

title: angels delight
directions: Scald milk and salt.
Separate eggs.
Beat yolks with sugar and add milk; bring to boil.
Add the gelatin which has been dissolved in cold water.
Let mixture cool until slightly thickened, then add beaten egg whites.
When mixture begins to set, add whipped cream.
Cut off brown crust of angel food cake. Break cake into walnut size pieces.
Make layers of cake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Next put cherries, nuts and gelatin mixture. Sprinkle top with coconut and cherries.

title: golden puffs (doughnuts)
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add oil, milk and egg.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by small teaspoonfuls into 375° oil.
Fry about 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on absorbent paper and roll warm puff in cinnamon-sugar mixture or confectioners sugar, if desired.
Batter will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Pare and slice apples and add to cranberries.
Add water and cook until skin of berries break.
Add sugar and pour into a 9 1/2-inch pie dish lined with pastry.
Put strips of pastry over the top in crisscross fashion and bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: deep, dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add all remaining ingredients except boiling water.
Beat for 2 minutes. Stir in boiling water.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes on rack.
Remove from the pan.
Top with your favorite frosting.

title: el dorado
directions: In oiled casserole, place layer of chips.
Mix next four ingredients.
Layer meat mixture on chips.
Mix next four ingredients together.
Layer cottage cheese mix.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal applesauce cookies(an old family recipe.)
directions: Mix all together as given.
Drop from teaspoon on greased baking sheet about 2-inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Saute onions in oleo.
Cool thoroughly.
Mix rest of ingredients and put in casserole.
Top with green onions and brown. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add well beaten eggs. Sift flour once before measuring.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and add alternately with the milk.
Add the vanilla and mix well.
Grease a round pudding pan or skillet generously with butter and line with brown sugar.
Place in the pan slices of well-drained pineapple with maraschino cherry in center of each and walnut meats surrounding pineapple slices, if desired.
Pour cake batter over the mixture in the pan and bake. When cake is done, turn pan upside down.
Do not remove pan for a minute so as to allow butterscotch mixture to run down over cake instead of clinging to pan.

title: twenty-four hour salad
directions: Grate or chop the cabbage, onions and bell pepper.
Mix well. Mix the remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over the first mixture. Refrigerate for 24 hours. This will keep in refrigerator for a day.

title: nutty carrot spread
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until blended.
Stir in carrots and remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Spray pan with nonstick cooking spray. Dip chicken in spread; coat with combined remaining ingredients. Place in pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: coffee icing
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and coffee.
Blend in milk until of spreading consistency.

title: aggression cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put all ingredients into bowl and mash. Knead and squeeze until thoroughly mixed.
Form into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Butter the bottom of a small glass; dip in sugar, then mash balls flat.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: layered bean dip
directions: In a microwave dish, layer cream cheese.
Add chili and top with Cheddar cheese.
Microwave 3 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: potato soup, hot
directions: In a large pot, heat bacon drippings.
Saute onion, celery and mushrooms until soft.
Blend in flour over medium heat until golden brown.
Stir in chicken broth and milk.
Add potatoes, stirring until soup bubbles and thickens slightly.
Simmer 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in cheese one handful at a time until melted and smooth.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: honey dijon sauce
directions: Mix the Dijon and honey together in a saucepan over low heat, then add the seasonings and serve.

title: microwave turkey chili
directions: Microwave together, in a 3-quart glass bowl for about 7 minutes, the first 4 items listed.
Cook until turkey is no longer pink and vegetables are tender.
Stir once during cooking time and break up lumps.
Drain mixture and break up lumps again.
Return the mixture to the bowl.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Make the dough according to package directions and chill. Roll out the dough into a rectangle or square about 1/3-inch thick. Slightly dampen a paper towel and brush it over the top surface to remove excess flour. Spread butter evenly over the top and sprinkle on all the brown sugar and the cinnamon. Roll up dough and slice into 2/3-inch rounds. Bake as directed on the box.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients to soft ball stage.
Stir to prevent burning.
Add syrup, butter, salt and vanilla.
Stir only to mix. Pour slowly over
popcorn.
Mix well.
Form into balls, carefully with hands, pressing only to hold together.
Makes 10 balls, 3 inches in diameter.

title: sweet and sour ham
directions: Stir-fry ham, pepper, carrot,
pineapple
and broccoli. In separate bowl mix cornstarch,
water,
brown
sugar,
wine, catsup, soy sauce and mustard.
Add to stir-fry mixture.
Stir until thick.
Serve over rice.

title: corn meal mush
directions: Heat the water to boiling.
Mix corn meal and salt with milk. Pour into boiling water, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened, stirring frequently.
Continue cooking over low heat for 15 to 20 minutes.
Pour into dish.
Let set until cold, then slice and fry.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: apple crunch muffins
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon into mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening with a pastry blender until fine crumbs form.
Combine egg and milk.
Add dry ingredients all at once, stirring just enough to moisten.
Stir in apples.
Spoon batter into paper-lined 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups, filling 2/3 full.
Top with recipe below before baking.

title: cheesy onions
directions: In a skillet melt butter, saute onions until clear and lightly brown.
In a 2 quart casserole, layer onions, 2/3 c. cheese and pepper.	Blend soup, milk, and soy sauce in a sauce pan heating slightly.
Pour into casserole and stir gently.
Top with bread slices.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; then push bread slices under sauce, sprinkle with remaining cheese, bake an additional 15 minutes.
Good side dish with beef, pork roast or ribs.

title: little cheese cakes
directions: Makes 70 (2-inch) cakes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix dressing mix according to package directions.
Mix other ingredients and marinate at least 8 hours.

title: easy biscuits
directions: Mix together.
Spoon into muffin pan coated with Pam.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: mashed potatoes with cream cheese
directions: Peel, slice and boil potatoes in water until tender, drain. Mash potatoes, gradually stirring in milk, cream cheese, onion power, salt and pepper until light and fluffy. Sprinkle with paprika. Serve immediately.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix Cool Whip, pudding, nuts and pineapple together.
Mix well, chill and serve.

title: khrustiki (bow ties)
directions: Use same method as in making noodles, a bit on the soft side. Knead dough and work smooth.
Roll out very thin and cut with wheel cutter into 2 x 3-inch oblong strips.
Make slit in center and twist ends through slit and out back.
Drop in deep, hot fat and fry until light brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients together and top with the crushed potato chips.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.
Very good.

title: impossible pie
directions: Pour
all ingredients into a blender; blend well.
Pour mixture into
a
10-inch
greased pie pan.	Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: country steak
directions: Cut tenderized steak into serving pieces.
Flour both sides and brown in shortening
in skillet.
After browning, drain off excess grease, then mix together the soup and water.
Pour in skillet over meat.
Add onion.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Stir often.

title: chocolate-oatmeal macaroons
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt. Cream butter; gradually add sugar, creaming well. Add milk and vanilla. Blend in dry ingredients, oats and nuts. Drop by rounded teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°. Cookies harden after baking. Cool several minutes before removing from pan.

title: noodle kugel
directions: Boil noodles about 6 minutes; set aside.
Mix well in blender 3 eggs, salt, 1 pint sour cream and 1/4 teaspoon baking powder.
Melt 1/4 pound butter (margarine) in baking dish.
After draining noodles, put them back in pan and pour in egg mixture.
Mix well. Add one large can crushed pineapple with juice and about 3 tablespoons cottage cheese.
Mix and pour into baking dish.
(If you like, you may add raisins.)
Mix some cinnamon and brown sugar together and sprinkle over top.
Also crush some corn flakes and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with your meal.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together, simmer on low heat for 30 minutes.

title: midnight cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually and cream until fluffy. Blend in well beaten eggs.
Slowly add hot water to cocoa and mix until smooth.
Stir to dissolve completely.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with the cocoa mix.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 8-inch square pan for 50 minutes in 350° oven.
Done when it springs back to the touch or toothpick comes out clean when put in middle.

title: calamondin orange marmalade
directions: Boil fruit and sugar for 3 minutes.
Add drained crushed pineapple and sugar; boil for 3 more minutes.
Fill jars.
To seal the jars, either put them in the hot water bath for 5 minutes, or seal with paraffin.

title: beef and tortellini soup
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven or sauce pot over high heat, cook ground beef, stirring frequently, until all pan juices evaporate and beef is well browned, about 10 minutes.
Spoon off any excess fat.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour mixture into two greased pie pans and bake in 350° oven for 40 to 50 minutes, until done. Pies freeze well.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Peel and cut potatoes.
Cook approximately 30 minutes.
Drain and mash with a mixer.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Put in 2-quart dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican fudge
directions: *When making a lot, use a 16 ounce size.

title: elegant chicken
directions: Run cold water over beef.
Drain and arrange in bottom of a 12 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Place chicken on beef.
Top chicken with bacon.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: crusty individual meat loaves
directions: Mix everything together except corn flakes.
Form mixture into 8 or 9 balls.
Crush corn flakes in a plastic bag and coat meat with flakes, shaping into loaves.
Place in shallow pan and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: chicken and rice salad
directions: Combine chicken, red peppers, rice, lettuce and eggs.
Blend mayonnaise, mustard and seasonings.
Pour over rice mixture and toss lightly.

title: homemade play dough
directions: Combine flour, salt and powdered alum.
Mix with boiling water.
Add oil and mix well.
Divide and add food coloring as desired.
Keep covered when not in use.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer for 2 hours.

title: apple pie(one crust)
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and butter.
Add next 4 ingredients to apples.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: sangria
directions: Into large pitcher pour lemon juice, orange juice and sugar; stir to dissolve sugar.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Best if made ahead of time and allowed to chill and flavors to blend.
Try eating the fruit!

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Bring to a boil oleo and water.
Add flour and mix well.
Add 4 eggs, one at a time, and mix well after each one.
Spread into greased jellyroll pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and milk.
Add vanilla pudding.
Pour over crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Drizzle chocolate syrup over top.

title: molasses whoopie pies
directions: Sift flour with soda, salt, cinnamon and ginger; set aside. Cream butter and sugar; beat in eggs.
Stir in molasses.
Add flour mixture, alternating with milk.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.

title: mystery salad
directions: Make pudding according to package, using buttermilk.
Fold in Cool Whip immediately.
Add mandarin oranges.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Just before serving, add cookies and bananas.

title: apple squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter; add sugar slowly, thoroughly blend.
Add eggs, one at a time; blend.
Add vanilla and almond extract.
Mix in flour a little bit at a time.
Spread 3/4 of batter in greased 13 x 9-inch glass pan.
Spread pie filling (not touching edges).
Add remaining batter in small drops.
Use a dragging motion as batter is thick.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until top is light brown.
Cut into small squares.

title: pinkerton punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Top with fruit ice ring.

title: turtle waffle iron cookies
directions: Blend cocoa and oil together.
Stir in sugar, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour and salt; mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on a medium hot waffle iron.
Bake 1 minute or until done.
Frost when cool.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine the oat bran, brown sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and pumpkin in a large bowl.
Make a well and combine the pumpkin, milk, egg whites and oil.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon into muffin pans, which have been sprayed with Pam.
Fill 2/3 full and bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: italian potatoes
directions: In a 350° oven, melt margarine in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Sprinkle in dry salad dressing mix.
Spread evenly over melted margarine.
Cut cleaned, dried potatoes in half lengthwise.
Place cut side down in the margarine mixture.
Bake approximately 50 minutes until cut sides of potatoes are crisp and golden brown.

title: cowboy beans
directions: On top of stove, cut onion in pot on top of beans.
In a separate pan, brown hamburger and drain.
Put in beans.
Pour sauce over beans and meat.
Cook until done.
Cook in crock-pot 4 to 5 hours on low.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and then add to remaining ingredients except zucchini.
Blend together, then stir in all grated zucchini and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: norwegian meatballs and celery
directions: Cook onion in 2 tablespoons butter until transparent.
In large bowl, mix 1/2 chicken broth, onion, meats, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Beat egg whites into soft peaks.
Mix lightly into meat mixture.
Shape into 18 balls.
Melt 3 teaspoons butter in heavy skillet, brown 9 meatballs.
Remove.
Add remaining 3 tablespoons butter and remaining meatballs.
Remove.

title: tuna-macaroni bake
directions: In 3-quart casserole, combine macaroni, tuna and tomato. Blend and heat next 3 ingredients.
Pour over macaroni mixture. Top with crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated 375° oven 30 to 60 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 portions.

title: shipwreck
directions: Layer the ingredients in a greased casserole.
Top with tomato soup and enough water to cover all.
Bake covered in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: hot rolls
directions: Combine in large mixing bowl the boiling water and shortening. Add sugar and salt and allow to cool. Combine yeast and slightly warm water and add to first mixture. Add flour until not too stiff (usually about 7 cups).

title: tailgate dip
directions: Microwave cream cheese until soft.
In a bowl, mix thoroughly the cream cheese with mayonnaise.
Spread out on pizza pan; top with taco sauce, diced tomatoes, onion, green peppers and jalapenos.
Scoop out with chips and enjoy.

title: emily's crab casserole
directions: Combine crabmeat, chopped eggs, parsley and onion.
Set aside. Combine remaining ingredients and stir carefully into crabmeat mixture.
Place into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish and cover with crumbled bread crusts, if desired.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes, until done.

title: creamy cole slaw
directions: Mix together.
Add small package slaw mix.

title: dinner in a pumpkin
directions: Clean out pumpkin.
In large skillet saute onion in oil until tender.
Crumble meat and brown.
Drain drippings.
Stir in soy sauce, brown sugar, mushrooms, broth and soup, bring to boil. Lower heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add cooked rice and water chestnuts.
Spoon into pumpkin shell.
Bake 1 hour at 350° until pumpkin is soft.

title: five bean bake
directions: Combine all ingredients (do not drain beans) in a 4-quart casserole.
Put bacon slices across top.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Makes 20 servings.

title: glorified chops
directions: Brown pork chops in cooking oil.
Pour off fat.
Stir in soup, cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together the hash browns, soup, cheese, sour cream and onion in a baking dish.
On top, crumble Ritz crackers (approximately 1 stack).
Pour on the melted butter.
Bake for hour at 325°.

title: applesauce fruit cake ring
directions: In large bowl, thoroughly mix all dry ingredients.
In medium bowl, mix applesauce, buttermilk, butter, fruits and nuts.

title: slimmer salad
directions: Sprinkle dry jello over cottage cheese; mix well.
Add pineapple and whipped topping; mix well.
Place in refrigerator and chill 2 hours.
Makes nine 1/2-cup servings (71 calories).

title: clam chowder
directions: Dice and fry out salt pork.
Remove browned pieces and set aside.
Saute and brown chopped onion in salt pork grease, then return salt pork bits to pan.
Add flour and blend well.
Remove from heat when thickened.
Cook diced potatoes in clam juice, then combine with onion, flour and pork mixture over low heat.
Add chopped clams, cream and baby clams.
Salt and pepper to taste. Remove from low heat.
Do not heat again until ready to eat.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat, drain.
Add tomato sauce and paste and seasonings. Cook thoroughly.
Cook lasagna noodles.
In pan, layer noodles, mixture and cheeses. a thin layer of each until pan is full finishing with a top layer of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 40 minutes until brown on top.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix margarine and cocoa.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix separately, then add to the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: joanna's salad
directions: Mix oranges, onion rings and almonds.
Tear lettuce and pour salad dressing mixed with soy sauce over it.
Put lettuce into salad bowls.
Put first 3 items on top and serve.

title: peanut butter drops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; mix well. Drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients; add more water if needed to make mixture moist.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Cook for 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.
Makes about 50 balls.
Serves 20.

title: chicken ala swiss
directions: Arrange chicken in pan and top with cheese.
Pour cream of chicken soup over chicken and cheese.
Sprinkle dressing over all. Drizzle melted butter over that. Cover and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake another 30 minutes.

title: pralines
directions: You also need a 4-quart heavy pan.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: In a large pot, combine potatoes, celery, carrots, onion, water, parsley and bouillon cube.
Cook over medium heat until soft (about 20 minutes).
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Reduce heat and add milk and eggs.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix Bisquick and water.
Add remaining ingredients and make into a ball.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: herb seasoned chicken
directions: Melt butter.
Add the spices and mix well.
Coat chicken breasts with mixture.
Bake on cookie sheet at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chili chicken
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Cook onion in oleo.
Add rest of ingredients and noodles and some cheese.
Put in greased casserole and top with remaining cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Mix sugar, sour cream and club soda together.
Add Bisquick; knead 12 times in bowl.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased pan. Brush with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 16 to 18 minutes. Makes 9 to 10 biscuits.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 2 1/2 cups more cold water.
Add frozen strawberries with juice. Mix together, pour 1/2 mixture into bowl and refrigerate until firm.
Spread sour cream on top of firm jello.
Set into refrigerator for 15 minutes. Pour other half of jello and strawberries on top of sour cream. Put back into refrigerator until firm.

title: six-week muffin batter
directions: Cream shortening and sugar in a large bowl.
Push this mixture aside and beat the eggs lightly in same bowl.
Mix 1 cup flour into the eggs and add the buttermilk; mix all the batter.
Add the balance of flour (4 cups), soda and salt and mix thoroughly.
Add the Raisin Bran and fold in.

title: steak and vegetables
directions: In a bowl, combine the cornstarch, bouillon, water and soy sauce; set aside. Cut steak thinly across the grain, then cut slices in half; set aside. In a nonstick skillet or wok, stir fry green pepper, onion and garlic in oil for 4 minutes; remove and set aside. Add meat; stir-fry for 4-6 minutes. Stir cornstarch mixture and add to pan. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 1 minute or until thickened. Add tomatoes, water chestnuts and green pepper mixture; cook and stir until heated through. Sprinkle with pepper. Serve over rice. Yield: 4 servings.

title: mama's sweet potato pudding
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and mix well.
Fold in potatoes and coconut.
Add milk and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Check to see if done.
If not, add another 10 or 15 minutes.

title: mom's banana cake
directions: Mix together: butter, eggs and sugar.
Add to this mixture: banana pulp, vanilla, baking powder, soda, salt, nuts and buttermilk.
Mix in flour.
Pour into greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Place bread in bottom of a 9 X 13 casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread on top.
(Do not grease the pan.) Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Note:
This is a double recipe, so it can easily be divided in half.

title: pineapple macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Cool.
Add pineapple chunks; drain and reserve juice.
Add mandarin oranges.
Combine pineapple juice, sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Slowly add eggs; cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly until bubbly.
Pour sauce over macaroni, pineapple and oranges.
Chill overnight.
Before serving, add bananas and sour cream.

title: green rice
directions: Beat together milk and egg.
Cook rice according to package. Mix with other ingredients.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Top with cheese; bake 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: strawberry pie
directions: May use blueberries with blackberry jello.

title: deviled ham ball
directions: Mix together and chill 2 to 3 hours.
Roll in ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on until done.
Let cool, peel and slice about 1/2-inch thick.
Fry in butter until brown.
Remove from skillet and sprinkle with sugar and serve while hot.

title: easy cream of broccoli soup
directions: Chop stems from head of broccoli. Simmer in one can chicken broth until tender. Add one can cream of mushroom, cream of chicken, or cream of celery soup. Bring to almost boiling while stirring. Add Half and Half or milk. Heat and serve. Top with grated cheddar cheese, if desired.

title: cheese and bacon frittata
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
Grease a 9 X 9 baking pan.
In a medium bowl using wire whisk, beat eggs, milk, green onion, butter, salt, and pepper until well blended.
Pour mixture into baking pan.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon evenly over the top.
Bake 20 minutes or until set and golden brown.
Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: apple butter
directions: Stir all together; boil slowly 20 minutes.
May add food coloring.
Yields 4 to 5 quarts.

title: the ultimate chocolate chip cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed using an electric mixer until creamy.
Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda and mix into creamed mixture until just blended.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoons 3-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies or 11 to 13 minutes for crispy cookies.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together well.
Beat in egg yolks until well blended.
Beat in sour cream and flavorings.
Sift flour and soda together.
Beat into butter mixture, 1 cup at a time, until well blended.
Gently fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours, or until done.

title: egg-sausage brunch
directions: Put cubed bread in a greased 9 x 13 baking dish and spread browned and drained sausage over bread cubes, then put cheese over top.
Beat eggs with milk and dry mustard.
Pour this over sausage, bread and cheese.
Cover with saran wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning mix 1 can cream of mushroom soup with 1/2 cup of milk.
Pour over other ingredients.
Garnish with mushrooms and bake approximately 1-1/2 hours at 325°.

title: party dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.

title: baked peach cobbler
directions: Place peaches in bottom of an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over peaches.
Mix 1 cup sugar and 1 cup cornstarch together and sift over batter.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over sugar topping.
Do not stir.
Bake at 325° for 60 minutes.
Cool slightly before serving.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening.
Add water and knead.
Add more flour, if necessary.
Let dough stand 30 minutes before rolling.
Do not let stand longer.
Roll on slightly-floured board until 1/4 inch thick.
Cut in diamond-shaped pieces.

title: sourdough rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add oil, egg, sugar, buttermilk and flour.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours. Bake in muffin tins or roll out and cut and bake on cookie sheet at 450° for approximately 20 minutes.
Oil tops before baking. Mixture will keep two weeks in refrigerator.

title: tofu pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Cool well.
Add lemon juice and mint extract.
Blend Jell-O mixture and tofu until smooth, approximately 45 seconds.
Pour into pie crust; chill overnight. Top with Cool Whip and sliced kiwi or fresh strawberries.

title: rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Blend thoroughly.
Bake in a covered baking dish.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: oyster stew
directions: Heat milk in double boiler until as hot as possible.
Add salt, pepper and Schilling savor salt.
Then add butter.
When all are combined thoroughly, add oyster meat.
Simmer 1/2 hour or until oysters surface.
Skim off oysters and portion into serving bowls.
Let milk mixture simmer 15 to 30 minutes longer, then ladle over oysters.
Top each serving with pat of butter.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef with your diced onion. Mix ketchup, brown sugar, mustard, salt and pepper in a small bowl.
Drain ground beef and stir in sauce mixture and beans.

title: fried egg rolls
directions: In a skillet, add a little bit of oil. Brown meat. Add onion, celery, carrot, cabbage and seasonings. In another skillet, add enough oil to deep-fry. Place wrapper on counter and fill center with meat mixture. Wrap bottom and sides and roll up. Seal edge with a little water. Deep-fry until brown. Serve with sweet and sour sauce.

title: strawberry crunch dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, combine flour, sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Stir in butter.
Transfer mixture to large baking tray.
Bake for 20 minutes, stirring often.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Cool.
In a large bowl, beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating constantly until very thick. Add undrained strawberries and lemon juice.
Beat at least 10 minutes, until mixture is very light and fluffy.
(Mixture will fill a large bowl.)
Fold in Cool Whip.
Distribute half of brown sugar and nut mixture in bottom of buttered 13 x 9-inch glass dish.
Carefully spread strawberry mixture over the top.
Sprinkle with remaining nut mixture.
Cover and freeze for at least 8 hours.

title: turkey gumbo soup
directions: Heat broth to boiling.
Add vegetables, seasoning, rice and turkey.
Cover and cook slowly 15 minutes until vegetables and rice are tender.
Calories per serving:
approximately 170.
Yields 6 servings, approximately 1 cup each.

title: leftover cereal (oatmeal) pudding
directions: Beat milk into cereal until smooth.
Add egg yolk, well beaten.
Add cinnamon, butter, sugar and raisins.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven for 45 minutes.
Beat egg white until stiff; beat in powdered sugar and vanilla.
Cover pudding with meringue and return to oven for 8 minutes to puff and color.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 1/2 pound Hershey bar and spread on top.

title: sweet potato puff
directions: Slice and mash boiled potatoes.
Mix other ingredients with potatoes and pour into a casserole dish.
Top with marshmallows and brown in oven.

title: roast turkey
directions: Baste turkey and place breast side down on roasting rack in baking dish.
Calculate total cooking time, allowing 9 to 12 minutes per pound.
Divide total time in half.
Microwave at High 10 minutes.
Reduce power to 70°.
Microwave remainder of first half of total time.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients and mold into patties and refrigerate.
Deep fry in Wesson oil until browned.
Serves 4.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan with cooking spray.
Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Sprinkle brown sugar on bottom.
Top with even layer of pineapple.
Slice cherries in half and arrange cut side up in pan.
In bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt and set aside.
In second bowl, mix applesauce, sugar, pineapple juice and
eggs (whites or whole).
Add flour mixture and mix just to blend.
Gently pour batter onto pineapple layer in pan.
Do not mix.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes, or until tester inserted comes out clean.
Remove from oven, allow to cool 10 minutes.
Invert cake onto serving dish and cool completely before serving.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Alternate eggs and flour, saving 1 cup flour to dredge fruit.
Add fruits and nuts.
Add baking powder to flour.
Mix in flavoring.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Test after 1 hour.
Cool before removing from pan.

title: fruit and cheese salad
directions: Drain pineapple into a small saucepan.
Add apples, nuts and cheese to pineapple.
Mix well.
Add sugar, flour and
egg to pineapple juice in saucepan.
Mix well and cook on medium heat until thick and clear.
Pour over fruit mixture.
Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.
Best if refrigerated overnight.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower and onions up in a bowl.
Add Miracle Whip and French dressing.
Mix and chill until ready to serve.

title: chocolate whip pie
directions: Cook pudding mix according to directions on low flame.
Pour into pie shell and chill for 2 to 3 hours.
When ready to serve, fill in top of pudding pie with Cool Whip.
Garnish with chocolate shreddings.
Serve and enjoy.
Quick and easy.

title: wild chicken and rice bake(low-fat)
directions: Put rice and seasoning package in 8-inch casserole.
Mix soup, water, chestnuts, peas and carrots.
Mix into rice.
Push chicken pieces under rice mixture.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: burritos
directions: Brown ground beef.
Put refried beans (1/2 can) in with beef and cook for 5 minutes.
Spread out tortillas and spread a thin coat of sour cream on each.
Put ground beef mixture in shells and roll up.
Put in casserole dish.
Spread chili over top, then sprinkle with chopped onion, cheese and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut meat into thin long strips, approximately 3-inches.
Cut peppers and onion into strips also.
Take 2 tablespoons olive oil and place in skillet or wok.
Heat on medium to high heat.
Place in meat and seasonings.
When brown add in peppers and onion. Cover with lid until vegetables are tender.

title: beat and eat frosting
directions: Combine ingredients.
Add 1/4 cup boiling water.
Beat to stiff peaks at least 4 to 5 minutes.
Great for angel food cake!

title: ooey gooey cake
directions: Melt oleo; add to cake mix and egg.
Mix well.
Press into oblong cake pan.
Mix powdered sugar, eggs, vanilla and cream cheese.
Beat until fluffy.
Pour over cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until top is lightly brown.

title: spaghetti or linguine with tuna fish
directions: Saute finely chopped garlic in saucepan with oil, add olives, tuna crumbled and chopped parsley.
Cover saucepan and cook 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, mashed.
Add salt and pepper.
Simmer slowly for 40 minutes.
Cook macaroni in boiling salted water for about 8 minutes or to desired taste.
Drain, pour sauce over macaroni and serve.

title: santa's whiskers cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream together butter or margarine and sugar. Add milk and vanilla or rum flavoring.
Blend.
Stir in flour, chopped cherries and chopped pecans.

title: molded shrimp salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add salt, catsup and vinegar. Blend well.
Refrigerate until partially set; add remaining ingredients.
Pour into individual molds or a 9-inch square pan until set.
Delicious served with hot rolls and a fruit and cottage cheese salad.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients and add oil, eggs and carrots. Mix well.
Bake in three 8-inch pans at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni in salted water until tender; do not overcook. Remove from heat and drain; wash in cold water until cool.
Mix with remaining ingredients in a large covered bowl.
Add a little of the sweet pickle juice.
Place in refrigerator, stirring occasionally.
This is better if made the day before.

title: onion-rye rolls
directions: Combine water, onion soup mix and potatoes.
Cool to lukewarm. Add yeast; stir in rye flour, milk, sugar, caraway seed, oil and egg.
Beat 2 minutes with mixer.
Add 2 1/4 to 2 1/2 cups of white flour to make stiff dough, beating well by hand.
Cover and let rest 30 minutes.
Toss on floured surface until no longer sticky. Roll out 1/2 inch thick.
Cut with 3-inch round cookie cutter or tuna fish can.
Place on cookie sheets, well-greased and sprinkled with cornmeal.
Let rise until light and doubled.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until light golden brown.

title: mix-melt appetizers
directions: Cut cheese slices into triangles.
Top each cracker with cheeses, peppers and olives.
Broil until cheese begins to melt. Makes 32 appetizers.

title: meat loaf for special diets
directions: Mix ingredients; shape into meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in covered dish.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Put chicken parts in large baking dish.
Mix salad dressing, soup mix and apricot preserves together.
Use water to rinse jars and mix in.
Pour mix over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover.
Add pineapple and green pepper for garnish.
Bake, uncovered, 1/2 hour more.
Serve.
Good with rice.

title: pistachio mousse
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and salt in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir until all is dissolved.
Add yeast to 1 cup lukewarm water in large mixing bowl.
Stir until it dissolves.
Add eggs and 6 cups flour alternating with other mixtures.
Beat well.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Roll out and cut into small squares.
Dip in melted butter and layer in tube pan.
Let rise to top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cauliflower broccoli salad
directions: Cream together Parmesan, mayonnaise and sugar; pour over chopped veggies and bacon.

title: good iced tea
directions: Pour boiling water over tea bags and steep.
Add sugar, limeade, lemonade and enough water to make 1 gallon.
Strain before serving.

title: banana nut bread
directions: In mixer bowl, cream together sugar and cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Beat in mashed bananas and eggs.
Add biscuit mix and fold in pecans.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour, or until golden brown.

title: meat pie
directions: Boil in water the meat, potatoes and carrots until done.
Save the water.
Drain the peas and corn.
In a big bowl, combine meat, potatoes, carrots, peas and corn.
Make sure the meat is crumbly. Potatoes will be like mashed potatoes and carrots will be soft. Put one pie crust into pie pan.
Put in meat stuffing; mash down after all the meat stuffing is in and put other pie crust on top. Crimp edges to seal in meat.
Do not make slits in top.
Bake 1 hour at 375° or until pie crust is golden brown.

title: rachel's chicken fajitas
directions: Put 1 tablespoon oil and

chicken in skillet to let chicken thaw. Add dry sauce mix. Add 1/2 cup water. Add salsa. Add sour cream. Microwave wraps. Fill wraps with sauce made. Put in baking pan; sprinkle cheese on top. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: old fashioned cole slaw dressing
directions: Finely shred the head of cabbage.
Add the mayonnaise and sprinkle with pepper.
Combine the vinegar, sugar and a sprinkle of salt.
Pour over cabbage and mix.
Let stand all day or all night to marinate.
Keep refrigerated.

title: quick german chocolate cake
directions: In a bowl mix all cake ingredients and place in 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until toothpick comes out clean.

title: no-measure beef stew
directions: In a 3-quart casserole, combine tomato sauce and salad dressing mix.
Stir in beef, parsnips, potatoes and onions. Cover and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Stir in the green peppers and celery.
Cover and bake another 50 to 60 minutes or until meat and vegetables are tender.
Stir well before serving.

title: rhubarb freezer jam
directions: Cook rhubarb and sugar until a sauce.
Add jello.
Mix in and stir, then pour into jars.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into quarters. Mix the granulated sugar and cinnamon together. Coat each biscuit piece with this mixture; set aside. Melt the margarine; add brown sugar and mix well. Spray a Bundt pan with vegetable spray and layer biscuits, pecans and brown sugar mixture in the pan. Pour remaining brown sugar mixture over the top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Makes 12 servings.

title: angel fluff rice salad
directions: Cook rice until done.
When done, add 1 1/2 cups sugar while warm for dissolving.
Cool rice and add 1 can crushed pineapple. Be sure to drain pineapple, because the juice will curdle Cool Whip.
Add Cool Whip and marshmallows to rice and pineapple.
May need more Cool Whip if rice texture is too thick.
Mix in walnuts and chunks of pineapple (optional).
Place candied cherries on top.

title: chicken bake
directions: Boil chicken, celery and onion. Take off bones and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Salt and pepper chicken. Mix the mushroom soup, chicken soup and 1 can of milk together.
Pour over the chicken. Mix stuffing, 1 soup can broth and butter.
Spread on top of chicken and soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sara's cut out cookies
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Cream sugar and butter. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each.
Alternately add flour mixture and sour cream to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and remaining flour.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll to 1/4-inch thick on floured cloth.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes at 375°.

title: caramel popcorn(no baking)
directions: Mix all ingredients over stove until marshmallows are melted and sugar dissolved. Pour over popcorn; toss and serve.

title: really "rich" fudge
directions: Mix butter, milk and chocolates together in saucepan. Cook over medium heat until all chocolates are melted and mixed well, approximately 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add marshmallow cream; blend well. Stir in vanilla and nuts. Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool; cut into 1-inch squares.

title: burgundy beef tips
directions: Brown beef in small amount of oil.
Add onion and cook until tender.
Add drained mushrooms, bouillon and water.
Cool until beef is tender, adding more water if necessary.
Add wine last 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Stir cranberries and sugar; let stand 20 minutes.
Pour into sieve and let juice go through.
Add cream, nuts and grapes.
Mix well.

title: 6 layer pudding cake
directions: Crust:
Mix together butter, flour and nuts.
With wet hands, press into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch glass pan.
Bake at 350° until brown. Cool.

title: nanny bilyeu's banana pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook over medium heat until it starts to thicken.
Take off heat and add vanilla flavoring. Layer vanilla wafers in Pyrex dish.
Pour mixture over wafers, then slice bananas and do this until Pyrex is full.
Let set for awhile before serving.

title: pasta seafood salad
directions: Prepare shells as package directs.
Mix mustard, dill weed and salad dressing; set aside.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Partially thaw whipped topping.
In a medium bowl, mix all ingredients thoroughly and pour into cooled pie shells. Refrigerate to chill.
This pie freezes well for later use. Yields 2 pies.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Slice all of vegetables in rather large pieces.
Pour sauce made of last 5 ingredients over the vegetables and toss.
Either decorate with quartered tomatoes (unpeeled) or toss in just before serving.

title: mexican saladgroves, texas
directions: Mix all together first 5 ingredients.
Just before serving, add dressing and Fritos.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Remove seed from peppers.
Wash peppers.
Combine rice, salt, beef, egg, milk and onion.
Stuff into green peppers.
Combine water and soup.
Can be made in crock-pot on low temperature 7 hours or high, 3 to 4 hours.
Also can be baked in oven at 350° for 2 hours.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Grind first 4 ingredients together.
Drain and sprinkle with salt.
Let stand overnight; drain.
Combine the rest of ingredients and pour into vegetable mixture.
Heat to a full rolling boil for 5 to 10 minutes.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: lasagna
directions: Early in the day in hot skillet, saute onion in salad oil. Add chuck.
Cook until red color disappears.
Mash garlic with salt or use garlic salt.
Add to meat with pepper, oregano, parsley, tomatoes, tomato sauce, Parmesan cheese and simmer 30 minutes. Refrigerate (not necessary).
Meanwhile, boil lasagna noodles in water and butter or as label directs.
Drain and rinse in cool water.

title: venison stew
directions: Clean venison well.
Trim and discard all membrane.
Cube venison and salt and pepper well.
Quick fry in oil using 5-quart pot.
Add potatoes, carrots and onions.
Cover all with water. Simmer for 2 hours or until venison is fork-tender.
Enjoy!

title: chocolate nut bread
directions: Place flour, cocoa, dry buttermilk, sugar, cinnamon, baking soda and baking powder in bowl and mix at low speed to blend well. Mix water, oil, egg, sweetener and vanilla with a fork to blend. Add to flour mixture and mix at medium speed only until flour is moistened.
Add nuts to dough and spread evenly in a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan which has been greased with margarine.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean from the center and the bread pulls away from the sides of the pan.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Turn out on wire rack to cool to room temperature.

title: waldorf red cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Make a paste with the food coloring and cocoa.
Add to mixture.
Add salt and buttermilk with flour and vanilla.
Add vinegar and soda.
Do not beat hard, just blend in.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in two well greased and floured 9-inch pans.

title: hot water corn bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Pour boiling water into mixture and stir until all ingredients are wet and you have a heavy batter you can handle with your hands.

title: tea room cranberry salad
directions: Bring 3 cups water to a boil and add orange and raspberry gelatin.
Mix well, then add cranberry sauce and crushed pineapple.
Stir well until cranberry sauce has dissolved.
Add chopped pecans.
Pour into large glass casserole or mold and chill overnight or until firm.

title: peanut butter haystacks
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 1 minute.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper and leave to cool.

title: chocolate swirl cheesecake(light)
directions: Coat the bottom of a 10-inch spring-form pan with vegetable cooking spray; sprinkle with chocolate wafer cookie crumbs and set aside.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Add 2 bottles Zesty Italian dressing.

title: mixed tomato salad
directions: Halve the tomatoes.
In a large bowl, mix the tomato halves with the onion and garlic.
Stir in the basil, cilantro and cumin. Season the mixture with salt and pepper and let stand for at least 15 minutes to let the flavors meld.
Garnish with additional basil sprigs.
Add chunks of mozzarella just before serving for a different variation of the salad.

title: cherry pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add eggs one at a time. Add milk and flour alternately.
Add flavorings and cherries.
Bake at 275° 2 hours in a greased tube pan.

title: mexican dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Let set in refrigerator 24 hours, stirring once or twice.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Thaw and drain frozen vegetables.
Combine vegetable soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimientos and 1/2 can onions. Pour into casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 to 40- minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.

title: strawberry jello mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Cool.
Add thawed strawberries with their juice and sour cream.
Blend well.
Pour into mold and allow to set in refrigerator.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Blend together cream cheese, Cool Whip and lemon juice.
Pour into pie crust.
Pour strawberry pie filling on top.

title: cheese chicken
directions: Dip chicken into milk and egg mixture and then roll in crushed crackers.
Place on baking sheet and bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: hummus(chickpea dip)
directions: Blend in blender or food processor.
Cut pita bread into triangle sized pieces.
Serve warm.
Dip pita into Hummus. Excellent.

title: banana bread
directions: Beat sugar and Crisco.	Add eggs and bananas.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add optional items, if desired.

title: cheesy scalloped vegetables
directions: Mix 1 packet potato slices, water, margarine, nutmeg and carrots in 2 quart round microwave-proof casserole.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High for 12 minutes; stir in milk, 1 packet sauce mix and the broccoli.
Cover and microwave until potatoes are tender, 6 to 9 minutes.
Stir in cheese.
Let stand until cheese melts.

title: rosie's pizzelles
directions: Beat eggs, adding sugar gradually.
Beat until smooth.
Add cooled melted margarine and anise.
Add flour to egg mixture.
If desired, add several drops of food coloring (red and blue work best).

title: sausage egg bake
directions: Cook Sausage, Mix soup, Beaten eggs, pepper.
Add cheese on top and bake uncovered 40 minutes at 375 degrees.

title: shrimp cheese ball
directions: Mix all above ingredients.
Roll in chopped nuts if you wish.

title: quick and easy toppings for cakes
directions: Smash bananas and blend in well with Cool Whip.
Place on any flavor of cake.

title: pizza-easy as 1-2-3
directions: Toast a crispy English muffin.
Top with any thick pizza sauce. Add your favorite pizza extras.

title: spinach or broccoli with rice
directions: Let spinach or broccoli thaw completely.
Loosen with fork and drain.
Add to the other ingredients.
Place in a casserole and cook in moderate (350°) oven until mixture is hot and bubbly, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: crab salad
directions: Chop and mix together the crab meat, water chestnuts, onions and cucumber.
Stir together the mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Add this to the other ingredients.
Serve.
This makes a very large salad.

title: chocolate mint truffles
directions: Place chocolate morsels in double boiler; bring cool water in bottom pan to boil.
Reduce heat to low; cook until chocolate melts.
Remove from double boiler.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually stir in 1/4 chocolate to yolks; add to remaining mixture, stirring constantly.
Add butter, sugar and mint extract.
Beat at medium speed until butter melts and mixture is smooth.
Cover with paper towel and let stand in cool, dry place for 1 hour.
Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Chill until firm. Melt chocolate candy coating.
Dip each ball, shaking off extra. Place on waxed paper.
Chill until coating has hardened.
Melt vanilla coating.
Drizzle balls with vanilla coating.

title: spaghetti chicken casserole
directions: Saute onions and sliced mushrooms in butter. Add chicken, soup, and sour cream.
In a separate pot, cook spaghetti and rinse.
Mix spaghetti with chicken mixture and bake in a 13 x 9 inch baking dish at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle parmesan cheese over the top of the dish and serve.

title: grandma's potato dinner
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef.
Remove and set aside. Add oil to skillet and heat.
Add potatoes and cook until lightly browned.
Remove; add onion to skillet and cook over medium heat until tender.
Sprinkle with flour, stirring constantly, 2 or 3 minutes.
Add milk, salt, pepper, hamburger meat and potatoes.
Mix well.
Cover and cook over medium heat 40 minutes or until tender. Sprinkle with grated cheese until cheese melts.

title: lemonade pound cake
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Mix cake as directed, adding pudding.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Take cake from pan while still hot and punch holes in it. Thaw lemonade.
Mix 1/2 cup lemonade and 1/2 cup powdered sugar well. Spoon over cake while still hot.
When cake is cool, mix 1/2 cup powdered sugar and 1/4 cup lemonade to make glaze and pour over cake.

title: yeast waffles
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add salt and sugar; then yeast and oil.
Add milk alternately with flour.
Put batter in large covered container (they will rise some).
Make them up a day in advance. Will keep a week or more.
Store in refrigerator.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli or asparagus according to package.
Drain. Arrange in a greased baking dish with flowerets facing outward. Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayo and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken; sprinkle with cheese.
Melt oleo and mix thoroughly with stuffing mix.
Spread over soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until topping browns.

title: kay's perfect pot roast
directions: In large pan, melt fat until 3 tablespoons is obtained.
Add meat and brown on all sides.
Add onion soup mix, ketchup and water.
Cover pan.
On high heat, bring to boil, then turn to simmer and cook, 30 to 40 minutes per pound.

title: cookies 'n cream
directions: Put all ingredients together and blend in food processor (or blender) until light and creamy. Pour into bowl. Sprinkle with crushed Oreos.

title: sausage bread
directions: Fry sausage until done, (drain), roll out dough.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased tube pan.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple crumb cake
directions: Pour apple and pineapple in bottom of baking dish.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° until top is brown.

title: creamy peanut butter fudge
directions: Put sugar in saucepan.
Add vanilla, cocoa and milk.
Bring to boil until forms a ball when dropped in cold water.
Take off burner.
Add peanut butter and butter.
Stir well.
Pour into pan and cool.

title: jello cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix dry jello and Cool Whip.
Add cottage cheese and fruit cocktail.
Mix well and pour in bowl.
Chill.

title: stuffed squash
directions: Parboil squash in water until barely tender.
Cool and cut in half lengthwise. Scoop out inside of squash leaving 1/4 inch shell.
Mix scooped out portion with stuffing, onions, egg, salt and pepper.
Place back in cavities of squash.
Place in greased baking dish.
Top each half with 1/2 strip of bacon.
Bake at 400° until bacon is browned.

title: peach pizazz
directions: In blender, combine all but ice.
Blend 30 seconds.
Add ice, one at a time; blend low until slushy.
Pour into a large pitcher. Garnish with peach or lemon slices.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix the ingredients in large bowl with electric mixer.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown together pork and beef; put in kettle.
Add the celery, onion, 2 cups water and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 1/2 hour, then add the soy sauce and bead molasses.
Cook 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender.
Add bean sprouts and thicken.
Serve over rice and/or noodles.

title: jew cake
directions: Beat together margarine, shortening, vanilla, sugar and eggs. Mix with flour and cocoa.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes. Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: Mix all together and make into balls the size of a hickory nut.
Bake in slow oven.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Cook Karo and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour over Rice Krispies and form into balls. Place on wax paper until balls are cool.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; season with garlic salt and pepper.
Drain. Combine sour cream, cream cheese and taco seasoning.
Put beef in casserole.
Spread with sour cream mixture.
Top with diced pepper, onion and tomato.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cover with grated cheese for several minutes at the end of baking time to melt.
Serve with corn chips.

title: chili
directions: Cook hamburger meat in water.
Pour water off.
Add more water.
Do this several times.
Drain well.
Mix all ingredients together in a crock-pot.
Stir well until blended.
Add enough water to mix well.
Cook on low all day.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all together.
Put in about 1/3 to 1 cup hot water.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
It will look curdled.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: tropical punch
directions: Combine Punch, lemonade, orange juice, grape and water.
Pour over ice in large punch bowl.
Add ginger ale gradually.
Stir. Float small scoops of sherbet on top.
Makes 30 (5 ounce) servings.

title: savory apple stuffing(low-fat)
directions: Saute onion, apples and celery in melted margarine.
Stir in stuffing mix, parsley and salt.
Add apple cider just to moisten. Bake for 45 minutes for 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together well; put into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate in double boiler; pour over top of dry mix in pan.
Cut and put in refrigerator for 1 hour or longer.
Enjoy eating.

title: buttermilk fried chicken
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Pour buttermilk mixture over top of chicken.
Cover and refrigerate at least 30 minutes.
Remove chicken from liquid.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture.

title: barbecue hot dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in a deep dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: potato potluck casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together through the grated sharp cheese. Add potatoes and fold into first ingredients.
Put in a 3-quart greased casserole.
Mix oleo and corn flakes; put over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick donuts
directions: Combine flour, sugar and nutmeg.
Cut in butter.
In a measuring cup, beat egg; add milk to measure 2/3 cup.
Add to flour mixture and stir until blended.
Turn out on a floured board and knead just until smooth.
Roll and cut with a donut cutter. Fry in deep fat.
Drain and dust thickly with powdered sugar.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until done and set aside.
Boil potatoes about 15 minutes.
In a large bowl combine peas, soup, corn, butter, milk and potatoes.
Stir well.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces and add to mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: gingersnap strips(no rolling out or cutting)
directions: Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: graham cracker delight candy
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and roll into small balls.
In double boiler, melt household wax and chocolate chips.
Dip balls into mixture and put on wax paper.

title: ranch cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk and eggs.
Mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat a well-greased 9-inch cast-iron skillet in a 400° oven for 3 minutes.
Pour batter into hot skillet.
