Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until golden brown. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Tear tortillas into pieces.
Layer 1/2 of tortillas on bottom of baking dish.
Layer 1/2 of chicken on top of tortillas.
Mix soups, chilies and chicken broth.
Pour 1/2 mixture over chicken in pan.
Layer tortillas, chicken, cheese and soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: screamers
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and press in a 9 x 11-inch pan.

title: marble squares
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and sugar, mixing well until well blended.
Add 1 egg; mix well.
Combine margarine, water and squares of chocolate or cocoa in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat; stir in combined flour and sugar.
Add 2 eggs, sour cream, soda and salt; mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan on cookie sheet.
Spoon cream cheese mixture over chocolate batter.
Cut through batter with knife several times for marble effect.
Sprinkle with chocolate pieces.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until wooden pick is inserted in center and comes out clean.
Worth the trouble!!!

title: fried alligator
directions: Place alligator in deep dish.
Season to taste and pour in vinegar and lemon juice.
Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Mix cornmeal and flour; remove meat from marinade. Dip meat in cornmeal-flour mixture; then drop into skillet with about 1 inch of oil heated to 375°.
Fry until golden brown and serve hot.

title: sweet potato pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In mixing bowl, beat together margarine and sugar until well blended. Add egg and egg whites, one at a time beating well after each. Mix in sweet potatoes and vanilla.

title: bing cherries in wine salad
directions: Add enough water to cherry juice from drained cherries to make 1 cup.
Place juice in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Stir in gelatin.
Add wine and refrigerate.
When gelatin begins to set, stir in cherries and nuts.
Pour into oiled 2 cup mold or bowl and refrigerate until firm.

title: italian spaghetti pizza
directions: Cook spaghetti 10 minutes, drain and add beaten eggs and milk. Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Brown ground beef; put this on top of spaghetti mixture.
Pour jar of spaghetti sauce over this.
Place 2 cups of cheese on top of ground beef and then place pepperoni over all of this.
Bake for 30 minutes or until bubbly at 350°.

title: pepsi punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid
as
directed, except cut down a little on water. Add pineapple juice.
Just before serving, add Pepsi.

title: iced oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt, pudding and rolled oats; set aside.
In large bowl, cream together the butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla; beat until creamy. Add egg.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in golden raisins. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 9 to 11 minutes, or until light brown.

title: berries in the snow
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.	Add to prepared Dream Whip.
Mix	melted	oleo and graham crumbs.
Pat down on bottom of glass
Pyrex
pan,	11 x 9 x 1 3/4-inch.
Use 1/2 of Dream Whip mixture, then pie filling, then layer rest of Dream Whip and cream cheese.
Chill.
Store in refrigerator.
Serves about 15.

title: carrot cake
directions: Stir together all dry ingredients.
Then stir in the oil, vanilla and eggs at one time in the same bowl.
Then add pineapple, carrots and nuts.
Then use shortening (not oil) to grease two iron skillets and flour over the top of shortening, like you would to bake cakes.
Divide the cake into the skillets and bake at 325° to 350°, depending on oven, for 30 minutes.
Test for doneness.

title: beach chicken
directions: Thaw spinach; drain all liquid from spinach and mix with cheese, garlic and mayo. Lightly flour chicken breasts; salt and pepper. Cut slit in chicken and stuff with spinach mix. Lay bacon across top. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. Reduce to 350° for 20 minutes more.

title: helen's chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add chicken broth.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apricot salad
directions: Put jello, water and sugar in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and dissolve cream cheese in mixture.
Add baby food and crushed pineapple.
Set aside to cool.

title: veg-all chicken pot pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into pie crust, cover with top crust.
Seal edges and split top crust.
Brush with beaten egg. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Enjoy!!

title: chicken roll-ups
directions: Separate rolls.
Combine chicken and cheese.
Reserve 1/2 of mixture.
Place about 3 tablespoons of chicken/cheese mixture on each roll.
Roll up and place seam side down in greased baking dish.
Mix soup, milk and pimento together.
Add reserved chicken and cheese mixture.
Pour over roll ups and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Cook sugar, buttermilk, butter and soda to soft ball stage. Add vanilla and nuts; beat until creamy.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all together in
heavy
kettle and heat to boiling. May pour over shredded	beef, ribs, fried hamburger or on pork chops.

title: apple crunch squares
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix until crumbly.
Reserve one cup.
Press mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: surfin' tuna casserole
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl; stir in milk.
Add remaining ingredients except 1/2 cup of the cheese; mix well.
Pour mixture into 9-inch microwavable pie plate.
Cover loosely with waxed paper.
Microwave on High 5 minutes.
Stir mixture thoroughly to completely mix center and outside edges; smooth top.
Cover. Microwave 5 minutes or until center is no longer wet.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese; cover and let stand 5 minutes. Makes 6 servings.
Preparation Time:
15 minutes.
Cooking Time: 10 minutes.

title: country style green beans
directions: Boil pork ribs about 1/2 hour.
Add green beans, salt, pepper and bacon drippings.
Cook about another 1 1/2 hours until beans are just tender and meat falls apart easily.
Remove meat and tear into small pieces.
Return meat to pot.
Add potatoes and cook until potatoes are tender.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Cook noodles and mix chicken.
Saute onion and pepper in butter.
Add to noodles and chicken.
Stir in Ro-Tel, English peas and chopped up Velveeta cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts. Stir up and serve.

title: chocolate cream cheese cake
directions: Use all ingredients to make cake. Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: broiled potato skins
directions: Prick potatoes with fork to allow steam to escape.
Bake potatoes in 425° oven until tender, about 1 hour; cool slightly. Cut each potato lengthwise into halves; scoop insides, leaving a 3/8-inch shell.
Spread inside of shell with margarine.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cut each into 6 pieces.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon.
Set oven control to broil or 550°.
Broil potatoes with tops about 5 inches from heat, until cheese is melted, about 2 minutes.

title: sausage stuffed acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise.
Remove seeds.
Place cut side down on a rack in a skillet and add 2/3 cup water.
Cover and steam 10 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Place fruit in deep oven dish.
Sprinkle brown sugar over fruit.
Mix together flour, granulated sugar and baking powder. Mix lightly beaten egg into flour/sugar mixture until lumpy. Sprinkle this mixture over fruit.
Pour melted margarine or butter over flour/sugar mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until top is lightly golden and fruit tender.
Serve with milk, cream or ice cream.
Makes 6 servings. Try 1/2 teaspoon nutmeg with rhubarb.

title: old fashioned meat loaf
directions: In large bowl beat eggs lightly and mix in chuck, crumbs, onion and pepper.
Add salt, mustard, milk and catsup.
Combine lightly.
Top with more ketchup or barbecue sauce.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate until jelled.
Pour over cheese mixture.

title: coconut cake
directions: Follow directions on box.
Make 2 layers.

title: rich chocolate bread pudding(century-old recipe)
directions: Beat egg yolks, butter and sugar.
Add crumbs, salt and milk. Cook in double boiler until thick.
Add cocoa or melted chocolate. Beat about 1 minute.
Fold in vanilla and egg whites, beaten stiff.
Bake at 350° until firm or a knife comes out clean.
Serve with whipped cream or chocolate sauce.

title: best ever banana bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Beat bananas to a liquid and add eggs.
In a separate bowl, cream shortening.
Gradually add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add banana mixture.
Combine flour, baking soda, and salt; blend into batter.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into two well greased loaf pans and bake at 300° for 1 1/4 hours or until firm to the touch.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, put bread cubes first.
Melt butter and add all ingredients together.
Pour over bread cubes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Good served with ham.

title: good night christmas cookies
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until stiff.
Fold in sugar, nuts and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Put in a 450° oven (if using electric, turn off); leave in until oven is cool or overnight.
Or you can bake in a 250° oven (real slow) for 35 minutes.

title: seafoam icing
directions: Combine all ingredients, except for the vanilla in the top of a double boiler.
Cook over rapidly boiling water, using an electric beater, beat until the mixture stands in soft peaks.
Remove from heat.
Add the vanilla and continue beating until icing is thick enough to spread.
This makes enough for a large cake.

title: chicken breast stroganoff
directions: Brown chicken in butter.
Slice in 1-inch strips.
Remove from pan.
In frypan, add parsley, chives, dill weed, salt and pepper. When heated through, add mushrooms and liquid and chicken broth. Let this come to a boil.
In a small bowl, combine sour cream and flour.
Stir in chicken broth and cook until thickened.
Add chicken strips.
(Broccoli pieces can also be added.)
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve with cooked egg noodles or potatoes.
Yield: 2 servings.

title: banana muffins
directions: Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 24.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Rinse raisins in hot water; drain dry. Combine raisins, glazed fruit, nuts, juice and flavoring; let stand.
Cream the butter and sugar until smooth. Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix until smooth. Add dry ingredients. Blend in fruit mixture by hand.
Let stand 1 1/2 hours in refrigerator, better overnight.
Divide into small amounts and drop on cookie sheet. Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 12 to 15 minutes or until light brown.
You may divide cookie mixture into large balls, wrap in foil and store in the freezer for months, if you wish.
It keeps real well.

title: saturday night special
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add pork and beans, salt and tomatoes.
Let simmer.
Put half of hamburger mixture into a casserole dish and top with a layer of onions.
Add remaining hamburger mixture.
Top with bacon and brown sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease a 9-inch square baking pan. Beat egg in mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until blended.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: marshmallow balls
directions: Mix and heat caramels, milk and margarine until caramel is melted.
Dip marshmallows into melted caramel mix and then roll in Rice Krispies.
Work carefully so marshmallows retain shape.
Cool on waxed paper or aluminum foil.

title: cheesy chicken broccoli bake
directions: Separate chicken breasts and place in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place a slice of cheese on each breast. Spoon soup onto each piece straight from can.
You have to "paint" it on. Combine margarine with stuffing mix.
Sprinkle over each piece. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
tags: cream of chicken and broccoli soup

title: dip(for rye bread, chips, vegetables, etc.)
directions: Mix together and refrigerate until you are ready to use dip.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In 10-inch iron skillet, heat Crisco in oven until very hot.
While Crisco is heating, mix milk, eggs, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Add corn meal to the mixture and stir real well.
Pour into hot skillet and bake for 20 minutes, until golden brown.

title: grama moe's tomato salad
directions: Place in large bowl and toss.
Make ahead and let set at room temperature for at least 2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place into greased pan and place on cookie sheet in an oven at 350°.
Bake almost 1 hour until light brown.
Serve warm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: never fail chocolate candy
directions: Use a heavy pan.
Heat on low heat until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chopped nuts and vanilla flavor.
Put in slightly greased bowl.
Refrigerate until sets up, then cut.

title: wacky cake
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 35 to 40 minutes.

title: trout german style
directions: Place several trout on wire rack in electric skillet.
Pour water over them to partially cover.
Sprinkle with onion, salt and celery salt.
Cover and cook approximately 10 minutes.
Serve immediately with melted butter.

title: marinated carrot salad
directions: Cook sliced carrots until slightly tender (don't overcook). Slice onion and separate into rings. Slice green pepper. Combine vegetables. Stir together vinegar and sugar until dissolved. Add oil, soup, salt, pepper, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well. Add to vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve cold. Keeps well in refrigerator for 2 to 3 weeks.

title: mushroom-barley soup
directions: Saute onions, celery and garlic in butter until tender.
Add dry barley and saute 10 more minutes until barley gets thick. Add chicken stock and mushrooms. Boil and simmer until barley is tender, about 1/2 hour to 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: microwave cornbread(for summertime baking - cool)
directions: Beat together egg, milk and cooking oil.
Combine dry ingredients and beat next 3. Add and mix.
Grease loaf pan and microwave on Medium 9 to 11 minutes until toothpick comes out clean.
Serves 6.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream together sugar, butter, oil and egg yolks.
Mix flour, salt and baking soda.
Add slowly to creamed mixture.
Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Add coconut and pecans.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Pour into 2 - 9-inch pans - sided greased and bottoms lined with waxed paper.
Bake at 350 for 40 minutes.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese set at room temperature until soft.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly.
Form into a ball.
Can be rolled in chopped parsley or nuts.
Store in refrigerator.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, crab, Parmesan cheese, mayonnaise, garlic salt and lemon juice.
Put in small casserole dish and sprinkle with extra Parmesan cheese and paprika.

title: chicken 'n gravy
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces.
Salt and flour chicken and brown in skillet.
Put chicken in 2-quart baking dish.
Mix soup and water; pour over chicken.
Cover dish tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: weight watchers salmon casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in dish sprayed with Pam.
Makes 1 serving of 3 to 4 ounces protein.

title: 3 week cole slaw
directions: Bring celery seed, salt, vinegar and sugar to a boil.
Pour over slaw.
Cover tightly and refrigerate.
Turn over occasionally. Keeps 3 weeks.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Mix brown sugar, margarine, syrup and molasses.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Pour over popcorn.
Place in 250° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes.
Separate grains.

title: easy breakfast rolls
directions: Place biscuits in a greased 9-inch cake pan.
Make an indentation in the center of each biscuit with a spoon.
Fill with jam or jelly.
Mix egg, milk and sugar; pour over biscuits.
If desired, frost with powdered sugar icing.

title: crumb crust topping
directions: Stir together flour and salt; mix in rolled oats.
Crumb together with butter and cold water.
Top fruit pie with crumb crust instead of pastry shell and bake as directed.

title: octopus hot dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs in 1/2 only up to about 1/2-inch from end, leaving a whole piece at the top.
Turn hot dog and cut again to the same mark.
This will give you 4 small areas.
Now, boil hot dogs 4 to 5 minutes.
This will cause 4 areas to spread out and this enables the hot dog to sit like an octopus.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into graham cracker crusts.
Chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onion and celery in 1 cup water.
When soft, mash in cooking water.
Put chicken broth in double boiler and bring to a boil.
Add potato mixture.
Add grated Velveeta cheese and salt to taste.
(Chicken bouillon granules can be added if desired.)
Cook in double boiler until cheese melts.
Serve plain or with croutons.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: risotto
directions: Mix broth and water. Place in pan and simmer on a back burner. Heat oil in large saucepan; add onion and cook until soft.
Add rice, stirring, and cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Add 1/2 cup broth, cook and stir until rice absorbs water.
Continue to add broth 1/2 cup at a time as previous amount is absorbed, stirring constantly. The entire process takes 25 to 30 minutes.
Rice should be creamy on outside and slightly chewy inside.
Stir in cheese and butter before serving.

title: red cabbage
directions: Saute cabbage in margarine, salt and pepper, onion, apple, juice of lemon and lemon peeling (remove before serving).
Add 1 cup water and simmer 30 minutes.
Add vinegar, bay leaves and cloves.
Simmer 10 minutes (low flame).
You may add bouillon cube. Delicious with pork roast.

title: hungarian postum cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients 3 times.
Beat yolks until lemon colored; add 3/4 cup sugar and beat.
Add hot water and beat again.
Beat egg whites well, but not stiff.
Add 3/4 cup sugar slowly to whites and beat until peaks form.
Add 3 tablespoons egg white mixture to yolks.
Add dry ingredients to yolks; blend well.
Fold in egg whites to yolk mixture.
Bake 35 minutes in 2 (9-inch) greased and floured cake pans at 350°.

title: aunt mae's elegant potatoes au gratin
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
Cool, peel and shred in medium grater.
Shred cheese.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Halve the cabbage; cut out core and wash.
Cut in small pieces.
Heat butter and onions in skillet and place cabbage and water in skillet.
Saute until golden brown.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Boil noodles according to directions.
Mix cabbage mixture and noodles together and serve.

title: eggs in a basket
directions: Butter both sides of bread.
Cut hole in middle of bread.
Put bread in 10-inch skillet over medium heat.
Crack eggs.
Put egg into the holes in bread.
Add a little shortening in skillet.
Cook until both sides of bread are golden brown.
(Kids love these.)

title: bark candy
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler or in microwave oven. Quickly mix in candy chips or nuts.
Spread thinly on wax paper (need lots of wax paper)
and allow to cool until hard.
Break apart and store in airtight container in a cool place.

title: nut cookies
directions: Grease cookie sheet lightly.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Blend Equal with orange juice and vanilla.
Work shortening with spoon until creamy.
Add liquid ingredients and mix well.
Add dry ingredients and work until lightly creamed. Add nuts and orange rind.
Shape into a roll.
Wrap in wax paper, chill and slice.
Place 2 inches apart.
Bake 12 minutes in 400° oven.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onions and carrots in butter or margarine in a fry pan until tender. Add flour to make a roux. Add the roux to the water. Use a wire whisk stirring until smooth. Add the cheese whiz, half and half, liquid smoke and salt and pepper. Simmer on low, stirring often for about 20 minutes. Add broccoli tops and cook till broccoli is tender, another 25 minutes. Serves 8.

title: apricot bread pudding with orange sauce
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light and fluffy.
Combine next 4 ingredients and gradually stir into mixture.
Put bread cubes, apricots and pecans in buttered shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish and pour egg mixture over top.
Set in shallow pan of hot water and bake in preheated moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve with warm Orange Sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: homemade play dough
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate when not using.
This is not an edible recipe, although it won't hurt if eaten, but it can be a real mother's helper.

title: no-bake orange cookies
directions: Crush the vanilla wafers. Combine crumbs, coconut and 1/4 cup confectioners sugar. Add the orange juice concentrate and mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in additional confectioners sugar.
Makes about 36.

title: best microwave baked potato
directions: Prick baked potato with a fork; wrap potato in soaked paper towel. Wrap in Saran Wrap. Cook in microwave on High power for 10 minutes. Will not dry out the tater!

title: graham cracker treats
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cover cookie sheet with foil.
Break graham crackers into squares and place on foil with edges of crackers touching.

title: cherry-o-cream cheese pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until fluffy; gradually add Eagle Brand milk while continuing to beat until well blended.
Add lemon juice and vanilla; blend well.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill 2 to 3 hours before topping with pie filling.

title: chicken a la creole
directions: Boil chicken.
Skin, bone and reserve the stock (skim off fat).
Saute onion, garlic buds, bell pepper, parsley and green onion in oil.
Add other ingredients and chicken meat.
Simmer for thirty minutes or more.
Serve over rice.

title: spinach supreme
directions: Place frozen spinach in boiling water, add salt. Bring to boil and cover and reduce heat. Cook 4 to 6 minutes. Drain. Mix soup mix and sour cream. Add spinach. Cover and bake in casserole for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: rosemarie's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and onions. Add green peppers. Add whole tomatoes, cut into large pieces; add tomato sauce and paste. Add garlic, bay leaves and cloves. Simmer for 4 hours.

title: uncooked relish
directions: Place ground vegetables in a mixing bowl; cover with salt. Let stand for 2 hours; drain well.
Add vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and celery seed.
Heat just to boiling point.
Do not cook. Seal in sterilized jars.
Yield:
6 pints.

title: six in one casserole
directions: Put in casserole in layers starting with the potatoes. Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: peachy pork picante
directions: With a little oil in skillet, brown cubed pork. Add salsa and peach preserves. Stir and mix well. Cover and lower heat. Simmer for 15 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: peanut butter play dough
directions: Mix together.
Make something beautiful and fun and then eat it.

title: stained glass cookies
directions: Melt the margarine and chocolate chips in double boiler.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Mix well.

title: kuchta's sweet potato pudding(yield: 6-8 servings)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 400°.

title: sugar cookie fruit pizza
directions: Cut dough 1/8-inch thick and lay in circles to cover 12-inch pizza pan from center out in spiral, overlapping.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Mix the cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and lemon juice; spread on cookie, exposing crust at edge like a pizza.
Put on cut up fruit in a spiral (kiwi, strawberries, blueberries, raspberries, peaches and nectarines).
Brush with apricot preserves, thinned with hot water.
Keep refrigerated until served.

title: june frosting
directions: Place sugar, water, salt and cream of tartar in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Cook 1 minute.
Pour, while beating constantly, over unbeaten egg white.
Beat until frosting holds up in a peak. Add vanilla anytime during beating.
This frosting remains soft.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Prepare rice and keep warm.
Meanwhile, cook green peppers and onions in heated oil in covered pan over low heat until tender, but not browned.
Blend cornstarch with small amount of chicken stock and add remaining stock with soy sauce.
Gently stir chicken into vegetables; cook and stir until sauce is clear and thickened.
Add tomatoes.
Serve over rice.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Press 1 can of rolls in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together and spread over dough. Top with pineapple. Spread can of rolls on top for top crust. Brush on egg white to help brown. Bake 30 minutes in preheated oven at 350°.

title: swedish kringle
directions: Mix flour, butter and 1 tablespoon water together as for pie crust.
Pat real thin in cookie sheet or brownie pan.
Bring 1 cup water and butter to a boil.
Add almond extract and 1 cup flour. Mix well.

Take off heat and add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add vanilla. Spread this mixture on crust and bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes. Spread with butter frosting to which 2 teaspoons almond extract has been added. Top with sliced almonds.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Blend the cream cheese and jello together to form a smooth paste. Add the boiling water, stirring well. Add the pineapple, including the juice and nuts. Pour into mold and congeal.

title: crab casserole
directions: Dice half the bread in a large buttered casserole. Combine crab, mayonnaise, celery, green pepper, onion and salt.
Spread over the diced bread.
Spread remaining diced bread over crab mixture. Combine eggs and milk and pour over bread. Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread undiluted mushroom soup over top. Sprinkle with shredded cheese. Return to oven and bake 1 hour longer.
Yields 10 servings.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine ingredients and mix with poppy seed dressing.

title: mexican bean soup
directions: Cook beef in a skillet until well done.
Drain off fat.
Add onion and Season All.
Add pinto beans, all of the can of hominy and stewed tomatoes.
Add 1 can of tomato juice.
Use 1 can for extra juice to dilute the soup when it gets too thick or use it for next day as a warm over.
Good with corn bread or corn tortillas.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Put one pie crust in bottom of pie pan.
Mix first 6 ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Top with remaining pie shell and seal edges.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients (not the candy kisses) well.
Then shape into balls.
Roll in granulated sugar.
Cook on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
While hot, put a candy kiss in middle of cookie.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: vegetable pot pie
directions: Heat 1/4 c. olive oil in skillet and saute first six ingredients over medium high heat till onions are translucent. Add tofu and herbs and cook for 2 minutes more.
Add salt, pepper and parmesan cheese.
Place vegetable mixture in deep dish pie plate and add gravy till it reaches top of veggie mixture.
Cover with the rolled pie dough and prick crust with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 35-45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: grandma t's date and nut cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, and mix well. Mix together the flour, soda and salt; add all at once and blend well.
Mix in vanilla, then add dates and nuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for approximately 12 minutes, just until lightly browned.
Cookies should be soft. Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: pineapple and cheese salad
directions: Cook juice, flour, 6 large marshmallows and 2 eggs.
When mixture is thick; cool and add remaining ingredients.

title: scotch crunchies(microwave)
directions: In large glass bowl, place butterscotch and chocolate pieces. Micro-cook, uncovered, until melted, about 2 1/2 minutes; stir after each minute.
Stir in noodles and marshmallows or raisins.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add onion and taco seasoning; mix well.
Combine chili and refried beans and heat thoroughly (done easily in the microwave).

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All and water chestnuts.
Mix all ingredients; cook at 300° for 45 minutes.
Crush 20 Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle on top. Melt stick of butter.
Pour over casserole for 15 minutes longer.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add oil, nutmeg and apple pie spice. Blend in well.
Sift together and add flour, salt and soda.
Stir in nuts and apples.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be frosted when cooled with a cream cheese frosting.
Makes 12 servings.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Combine Eagle brand and water.
Add pudding mix, beat until well blended.
Chill for 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In large bowl layer pudding, top with 1/3 wafers and then add bananas.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Mix
all ingredients and let it stand in the refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake at 400° for 10	minutes
and
then 30 minutes at 375°.	Cool and serve.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until almost done.
Boil eggs.
Strain macaroni in colander with cold water.
Cool eggs, also.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Keep covered in the refrigerator until ready to serve.
Very good!

title: finger jello
directions: Mix unflavored gelatine and flavored jello in a large bowl. Mix well. Add 6 cups boiling water.
Stir well until all jello is dissolved.
If you do not stir long enough, you may get a rubbery bottom.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Chill. After it hardens, cut into blocks or can cut with cookie cutters.

title: squash relish
directions: Mix shredded vegetables.
Add 5 tablespoons salt.
Store in refrigerator overnight.
Then drain thoroughly.
Rinse with cold water.
Drain thoroughly.
Then add boiled vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and turmeric.
Bring to boil.
Pour over squash mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Pack in jars; put in hot water bath for 10 minutes.

title: green pea salad
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix gently and serve.
(Good served with seafood.)

title: sausage quiche
directions: Punch holes in pie shell and bake before pouring mixture. Preheat oven to 375°.
Fully cook sausage, cheese, onion and flour; mix well.
Spread in pie shell.
Beat eggs, milk and parsley flakes.
Slowly pour over sausage mixture.
Bake on baking sheet for 35 to 40 minutes or until filling is set.

title: orange caramel fudge
directions: In skillet, heat 1 cup sugar, stirring until it melts.
Stir constantly until golden.
Carefully stir in warm milk, 2 cups sugar and the butter.
Cook to soft ball stage, 234°.
Remove from heat. Stir in the orange peel and nuts.
Pour into large Pyrex greased pan and spread evenly.
Cool completely before cutting into pieces. WATCH and add those last 2 cups of sugar while the first mixture is very light in color as it burns easily.
My favorite.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in the 1/4 cup warm water.
Cream sugar and shortening together; add eggs, yeast, salt and water.
Mix well, then add flour, cup by cup.
Let dough rise until double in size, then knead down.
Shape into rolls or loaves.
Let rise again until double in size.
Bake until done.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread crushed pineapple in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread pie filling over pineapple.
Next, sprinkle coconut and chopped nuts.
Pour on dry cake mix and over all the mixture.
Pour melted butter over the cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin with Eagle Brand milk.
Then mix the eggs and the remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°, then 35 minutes at 350°.

title: soft honey sugar cookie
directions: In large bowl with electric mixer at medium speed, beat margarine, sugar, honey, egg and vanilla extract until thoroughly blended.
Blend in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Cover; chill dough at least 2 hours.
On a lightly floured surface, roll dough out to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut dough with cookie cutter into desired shapes.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes or until golden brown.

title: goulash
directions: Sprinkle ground chuck liberally with seasoned meat tenderizer.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt to taste.
Add chopped onions to ground chuck.
Cook until browned.
Drain well. Cook macaroni until tender (not as long as you usually cook macaroni).
Add chopped tomatoes to drained macaroni and let simmer a few minutes.
Add chuck mixture.
Mix well and simmer about 15 to 20 minutes.
Additional seasonings may be added to achieve desired taste.

title: fat-free banana nut bread
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, soda and 3/4 teaspoon salt; set aside.

title: steak and gravy
directions: Pour water into crock-pot.
Turn on so it can begin to heat. Cut round steak into serving-sized pieces.
Salt and pepper steak and brown in canola oil.
(Works best to brown in iron skillet.) As pieces brown, remove from grease and put in crock-pot.

title: purple cow
directions: Blend and pour into glasses.

title: blueberry dump cake
directions: In a medium size Pyrex dish, layer blueberries on bottom, then pineapple, nuts, sugar and lemon juice.
Top with dry cake mix. Dot with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° until blueberries bubble and cake mix makes crust, approximately 30 minutes.

title: easy chicken and rice
directions: Sprinkle rice into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour onion soup over rice.
Add 1 cup water or milk.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper; place chicken in baking dish and spread cream of celery or chicken soup over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add water as necessary to keep moist.
Curry powder may be added if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dry barbecue rub
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let set at least 6 hours before using.
Rub on meat and bake in oven.

title: baked chicken with pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple; set aside.
Combine pineapple juice with garlic, cornstarch, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and rosemary. Place chicken in pan, skin side up; broil until brown.
Add pineapple slices to chicken, then stir sauce and pour over.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: "saudi" champagne
directions: Place a few each of orange, lemon and apple slices into pitcher.
Pour equal amounts of chilled apple juice and chilled Perrier over the fruit.
Stir, add ice and serve.

title: coleslaw
directions: Mix together in gallon jar:
cabbage, green peppers and sliced onions.
Next, mix together in saucepan:
vinegar, salt, sugar, mustard seed, celery seed and turmeric.
Bring to boil, then pour over cabbage mixture.
Keep refrigerated.
Will last for weeks.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Melt shortening in large heavy skillet over medium heat.
Stir in next 6 ingredients.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Stir in broth, tomatoes, parsley, salt, pepper, thyme, red pepper and bay leaf. Cover and boil.
Add rice, gradually stirring with a fork.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Mix in shrimp and remaining 1/4 cup green pepper.
Simmer until shrimp is done.
Remove bay leaf and serve.

title: pollo a la acapulco(chicken acapulco)
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces. Brown chicken in a saute pan and salt and pepper to taste. Stir in 1/2 of the sour cream and 1 can of soup. Add spices and mix well. Let simmer while you mix the rest. Mix remaining sour cream, cheese and soup. Take a tortilla and put a healthy spoonful of the simmering mix in it and roll (like a burrito). Place them seam side down in an 11 x 14-inch pan (glass works best). Once you have placed them in the dish, cover them with the remaining mixture. Cover and bake at 325° until heated through.

title: pink vegetable salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Add tomato sauce.
Heat over low fire, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Beat cream cheese with mayonnaise.
Add chopped vegetables and olives.
Combine with tomato mixture.
Turn into 1 1/2 quart mold or individual molds. Chill.

title: pelayo's dessert flan
directions: You will
need	2
loaf pans and 2 (13 x 9-inch) baking dishes.

title: oriental pepper steak
directions: In small skillet, heat oil and brown beef; drain.
Stir in soup mix and garlic powder, blended with 3/4 cup water.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add green pepper and tomato; simmer, covered, 15 minutes or until beef is tender.
Stir in cornstarch, blended with remaining water.
Bring to a boil, then simmer, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened, about 5 minutes.
Serve, if desired, over hot cooked rice.

title: sesame chicken
directions: In a deep bowl, combine first six ingredients.
Set aside. In another bowl, roll chicken in evaporated milk, then in Bisquick mixture, then in sesame seed.
Place chicken into an oblong 9 x 11-inch glass baking dish.
Place melted butter over each piece of chicken.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Turn pieces and cook another 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mash salmon well with fork.
Add egg, onion, lemon juice, salt, dash of pepper, chopped parsley, bread crumbs and flour.
Mix well and then pack lightly in a small 7 x 3 x 1/2-inch greased loaf pan. Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: low-fat beef stroganoff
directions: Melt the margarine in large nonstick skillet over medium heat. Cook the beef in the margarine until browned about 8-10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Reserve 1/3 cup beef broth; add remaining beef broth, ketchup, salt and garlic to meat and heat to boiling. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes. Add the onions and mushrooms to beef mixture and cook 5 minutes or until onion is tender. Shake 1/3 cup beef broth and flour in a tightly covered container. Gradually stir broth-flour mixture into beef mixture and heat to boiling, stirring constantly until thickened. Reduce heat, stir in sour cream and cook until hot, but do not boil. Serve over noodles. Makes 6 Servings.

title: mullagin (venison)
directions: Layer in large covered casserole ingredients as they are listed above.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: shrimp puff
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread cubes.
Add bread cubes and put in souffle dish or 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch dish.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour or until center is set.

title: banana split delight(this is great for picnics and summer entertaining!)
directions: Cover the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with crumbs.
Slice bananas and layer over crumbs.
Slice ice cream into 1/2-inch slices and layer evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Freeze until firm!
Melt chocolate chips and butter.
Add powdered sugar and evaporated milk.
Cook until thick and smooth.
Cool.
Pour over ice cream and nuts.
Freeze until firm!
Cover with whipped cream and top with the crumbs.
Remove from the freezer 1/2 hour before serving. This can be stored several weeks in the freezer.
Enjoy!

title: green onion teasers
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well. Serve on triangles of toasted bread or Ritz crackers.

title: enchilada casserole(con espinaceas)
directions: Place meat in heavy skillet; cook over medium heat until it loses all its color.
Drain.
Stir in onion, tomatoes, spinach, salt and pepper.

title: reunion punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill and add 1 dozen ice cubes before serving.

title: fruit cake dessert
directions: Slice cake horizontally into 3 to 4 layers.
Mix cooked pudding and drained fruit cup.
Place one cake layer on plate.
Cover with portion of pudding/fruit mixture.
Repeat, ending on top with a cake layer.
Frost with whipped cream.
Refrigerate overnight so cake will absorb other ingredients.
Slice and serve.

title: never fail pie crusts(may prepare ahead.  freezes well.  makes 2 pie crusts.)
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Mix egg, water and vinegar.
Pour liquid into flour mixture and stir until well blended.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thickness and line pie pans.

title: christmas pickles
directions: To jar of pickles add salt, pickling spice, alum and vinegar; fill with cold water and put lid on (do not need to refrigerate). Shake occasionally for a few days.
This can be done whenever pickles are ripe.
Before Thanksgiving or Christmas, drain water and rinse out spices.
Cut pickles in 1/2-inch rings.
Add 6 cups sugar and 8 tablespoons water.
Refrigerate.
Shake occasionally. Will keep in the refrigerator a long time.

title: french onion soup
directions: In large saucepan, mix onions, butter and garlic.
Cover and cook over low heat, until onions are tender.
Stir in beef broth, Worcestershire sauce and pepper, bring to a boil; reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes; ladle soup into 4 ovenproof soup bowls.
Top each serving with toasted bread, shredded Swiss and Parmesan cheese.
Broil 3 inches from heat until cheese melts, 45 to 60 seconds.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix and spread in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: crunchy cole slaw
directions: Toss together the prepared dressing and all ingredients right before serving.

title: ongoing pickles
directions: Use wide mouthed gallon or 1/2 gallon jar.
Bring all ingredients except cucumbers and onions to a boil.
Cool and pour into jar.
Add cucumbers and onions and store in refrigerator. Keep adding cucumbers as necessary.

title: apple-cinnamon cookies
directions: Cream the butter, powdered sugar and salt.
Add applesauce, cinnamon and vanilla.
Gradually add 2 1/2 cups of flour.
Shape by hand into small balls.
Roll cookies in a mixture of 1/2 cup of sugar and 2 teaspoons of cinnamon.
Place on cookie sheet and press with fingertips.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar with 2 tablespoons flour or cornstarch and 1 cup boiling water in a saucepan.
Put on stove and thicken.
Add 2 tablespoons strawberry gelatin.
Place strawberries in pie shell.
Pour syrup over pie and chill.

title: one cup apple pie
directions: Melt margarine, pour into baking dish.
Combine sugar and flour in mixing bowl.
Add milk, then pour into margarine.
Add apple pie filling.
Bake 35 minutes at 325°.

title: patriotic cake(1776 recipe)
directions: To the risen bread dough, add all the other ingredients, dissolving the soda in the water.
Wash and drain thoroughly the currants and raisins.
Pour the mixture into a greased pan and set it in a warm place to rise for 20 minutes.
Bake in a moderate oven and when cool, ice and ornament with candied cherries.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix in oblong baking dish.
Make biscuits out of the Bisquick mix and drop on top of the chicken mixture.
Bake at 325°
until biscuits are brown.

title: monster cookies
directions: Beat eggs, then add sugars, vanilla, corn syrup, baking soda, butter, peanut butter, oatmeal and chocolate chips in order given. Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon and flatten with fork dipped in flour. Bake in preheated 350° oven 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Cut tortillas in narrow strips and fry in oil until crisp. Pour up oil, except for 1 tablespoon.
Puree garlic, tomato and onion in blender.
Saute in oil (3 minutes).
Add broth, chopped egg, cumin and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Place tortilla strips and cheese in bowls.
Ladle soup over.
Serves 4.

title: cherry drop cookies
directions: Cream butter, stir in sugar gradually, mixing well after each addition.
Add egg and beat with a spoon until fluffy.
In a second bowl, mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to first mixture, alternately with the cream.
Add vanilla, dip cherries into the batter, one at a time and remove with a spoon.
Place on a well-buttered sheet.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 50 small cookies. Pitted dates may also be added.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion, bell peppers and celery and add to other ingredients.
Top with grated cheese and heat until cheese melts at 425°.

title: apricot nectar salad
directions: Combine pineapple and apricot nectar in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add gelatin, stirring until gelatin dissolves.
Add cream cheese; stir until melted.
Chill until the consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Fold in carrots, pecans and whipped topping. Pour into an oiled 5 cup mold or 9-inch square dish.
Chill until firm. Yield:
9 to 12 servings.

title: easy deviled eggs with olive caviar
directions: Boil eggs.
Mix the mayonnaise, mustard, lemon juice, salt and red pepper.
Put into egg halves.
Sprinkle with chopped olives.

title: hot ham sandwiches
directions: Melt margarine and blend in mustard, poppy seed, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Slice rolls in half.
Spread margarine mixture on both sides of rolls with a rubber spatula.
Layer ham evenly over bottom half of rolls.
Top each with 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Place top layer of rolls over cheese.
Put rolls back into pans and cut.
Heat rolls for 20 minutes at 400° covered with foil.

title: egg bread
directions: Use a wooden spoon.
In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in water. Stir in honey.
Add margarine, salt and only 2 cups of the flour. Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Beat on low speed with mixer until blended.
Increase speed to high; beat one minute.
Stir in additional cup of flour.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk, about 45 minutes.

title: barbecued chicken wings
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except chicken.
Mix to blend well.
Add the chicken wings and toss to coat.
Marinate at room temperature for 1 hour or overnight in the refrigerator.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine soup, milk and seasonings.
Stir in vegetables and meat.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Cut biscuits into quarters. Remove dish from oven and place biscuit pieces on mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until biscuits are brown.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Combine macaroni, cheese, tuna, pickles and onions in large bowl.
Stir together mayonnaise, salt, pepper and garlic.
Pour over mixture and toss. Cover and chill at least three hours.
Good served on lettuce either in leaves or shredded.

title: italian chicken pasta
directions: Simply cut 1 pound boneless, skinless chicken into cubes. Shake with salt, pepper and flour.
Brown in skillet with 2 tablespoons oil.
Stir in 1 can Hunt's ready sauce (chunky Italian).
Heat through and serve over favorite pasta.

title: tea syrup for big family
directions: Bring water and tea bags to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Let stand overnight.
Remove tea bags.
Add sugar.
Stir until clear. Makes 10 to 12 gallons of tea.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Trim any fat from chicken;
slice in thin strips.
In a large nonstick skillet, heat oil.
Add garlic and onion; saute until softened.
Add
chicken
slices;
cook
until they turn white,
5 to	8
minutes.
Add
vegetables;
stir-fry
for
2 minutes.
Add salsa;
heat through.
Meanwhile, bring a large kettle of water to a boil and cook spaghetti until al dente, 8 to
10 minutes.
Drain in a colander, turn into a bowl and top with sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Thaw hash browns. Add onions, soup, sour cream, cheese and butter; mix.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven. Top with cornflake crumbs. Bake for 15 minutes.

title: hot pepper relish
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, catsup, Wesson oil, garlic and salt and boil 5 minutes.
Pack banana peppers in hot, sterilized jars tightly.
Pour hot liquid over peppers and seal.

title: quick baked beans
directions: Pour all ingredients in baking dish.
Bake at 350° until beans are cooked down.

title: fettucine
directions: Cook noodles.
While they are cooking, melt butter in frying pan on medium heat.
Saute onion and garlic for 2 minutes.
Add cream and boil rapidly until slightly thickened and large shiny bubbles form (about 2 minutes).
Add noodles to pan and gently toss.
Add 1/2 cup cheese and toss.
Add another 1/2 cup cheese, salt and pepper to noodles and toss again.
Sprinkle nutmeg and remaining cheese over top.
Put top of pan on and let set to make sure cheese melts and doesn't get clumpy.
Do the cheese little bits at a time as instructed or it isn't smooth and creamy.
Serves lots.
Cooking time is 15 to 20 minutes.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Place all ingredients raw in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix juice, tapioca, sugar and salt.
Pour over raw veggies.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 300° for 5 to 6 hours.
Serves 4.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Brown pork in oil.
Cover. Simmer 20 minutes.
Remove.
Saute vegetables.
Remove.
Blend jam, reserved pineapple syrup, vinegar and soy sauce.
Stir a little sauce into cornstarch and ginger.
Add to skillet; cook until mixture thickens.
Stir in pork, vegetables and pineapple. Serves 4.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix water with buttermilk. Cook in deep fryer.
Have oil hot. Drop with a teaspoon in hot oil.
Cook until brown.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Layer beans and onions in ungreased 2-quart baking dish.
Mix ketchup, brown sugar, mustard, chopped bacon, salt and pepper; pour over beans.
Add enough reserved bean liquid to cover.
Put the fried bacon strips across the top of the dish.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: squash cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, eggs and oil together in a large mixing bowl.
Add the vanilla, baking powder, salt, baking soda, squash and cinnamon into the large mixing bowl with the cream mixture. When batter is mixed thoroughly, add the chocolate chips.
Pour the batter into a greased and floured Bundt pan and cook for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cake can be frosted or just sprinkled with powdered sugar.

title: surprise salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Soften the cream cheese; mix together with the pineapple juice.
Cream thoroughly.
When jello is cool, add cream cheese mixture, nuts, pineapple, celery and whipped cream; mix all together.
Let stand in icebox.

title: salal-apple jelly
directions: Cook berries and apple peels in water to cover for 15 minutes. Cool and strain through two layers of cheesecloth or one of clean flannel, set in a strainer.
Measure 8 1/2 cups juice.
Prepare jelly according to directions for apple jelly that come with pectin.
Use any proportion of apple to salal berries.
More berries give darker color and tarter flavor.

title: easy vegetable pizza
directions: For crust, unroll crescent rolls and pat into a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake according to directions.
Cool.

title: martha's tater tot casserole
directions: Crumble meat finely and add onion. Cook until pink in meat is gone.
Put into casserole.
Mix soup and milk. Add to casserole. Add beans, if desired. Top with Tater Tots.
Can also use onion rings.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.

title: mayonnaise biscuits or muffins
directions: Sift flour in a bowl and add the mayonnaise and the milk, stirring well.
Grease a muffin tin and fill about 1/2 to 3/4 full of the dough in each cup.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° to 375° (according to your oven) until brown (about 20 minutes).
Makes about 1 dozen.

title: chicken ruben
directions: Lightly grease a casserole dish with cooking spray and arrange chicken in dish.
Salt and pepper the chicken.
Place sauerkraut over the chicken breasts, enough to cover evenly. Place swiss cheese over top in an even layer.
Pour thousand island dressing over top of the cheese and spread out with a spoon.
Sprinkle with the parsley.
Cover with foil and place into a 325 degree oven and bake for 1- 1 1/2 hours.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Melt Velveeta in microwave.
Mix ground beef, cream of mushroom soup, picante sauce and Velveeta. Heat in microwave.
Serve warm with chips.

title: crock-pot lasagna
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat and drain off excess grease. Stir in Italian seasoning. Spray the inside of the crock-pot with nonstick spray.

title: italian beef pie
directions: Brown meat and mushrooms and then mix well all the ingredients, except cheese.
Place in a 2-quart casserole and cover with cheese.
Heat oven to 300°.
Cover casserole and bake for 35 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 10 minutes more.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Measure all ingredients into mixing bowl.
Beat at low speed or mix by hand until well blended.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove immediately from baking sheet and cool.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: chocolate tidbit candy
directions: Melt chips over low heat.
Remove from stove; add noodles and peanuts.
Drop on waxed paper.
Cool.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix box cake mix using milk instead of water plus 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Add 1/2 package coconut and bake according to directions in 9 x 13-inch pan.
When done, punch holes in cake with fork. Mix 1/2 cup evaporated milk with 1/2 cup water, 1/2 cup powdered sugar and 1 teaspoon sugar and pour over cake while hot.
Top with Cool Whip and coconut (1/2 package).

title: cranberry or whiskey sours
directions: Mix all in blender.
Add ice cubes.
Pour into glasses.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and peanuts together in a glass bowl.
Cook on High for 4 minutes.
Take out and stir.
Cook 4 more minutes on High.
Take out; add vanilla and butter and stir.
Cook 1 more minute.
Take out and add baking soda.
Stir well and pour into a greased pan before it starts to harden.
After cool, break into pieces.

title: microwave pecan brittle
directions: Combine pecans, sugar, syrup and salt in a 2-quart glass platter or bowl.
Microwave on High for 7 to 8 minutes, stirring once midway through cooking.
Add butter and vanilla.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Add baking soda; stir until foamy and spread quickly on greased cookie sheet.

title: fancy eggs
directions: Toast halves of English muffins or hamburger buns and butter them.
Top with hot scrambled eggs (you can add your favorite fresh herb to the egg mixture before scrambling if desired). Sprinkle top with shredded Cheddar cheese (and more fresh herbs, if desired).

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together with hand mixer until creamy. Good with strawberries and apples.

title: cheese muffins
directions: Stir cheese into dry ingredients until well coated.
Beat egg with milk and stir into flour mixture until well blended, then add butter.
Do not overmix.
Bake in greased muffin tin at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 24 servings.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Melt shortening in skillet over low heat.
Shake steaks one at a time until coated.
Save what is left in bag.
Place steaks in skillet.
Increase to medium heat and fry steaks for five minutes on each side until done.
Remove steaks to platter.
Put the coating mixture leftover in bag into skillet.
Add water and stir well to mix meat scrapings and coating mix.
Heat to boiling; stir and pour over steak.

title: baked leg of lamb
directions: Cut slits in lamb with tip of sharp knife; insert garlic slivers in slits.
Sprinkle pepper and salt over lamb.
Spread with mustard.
Sprinkle with flour.
Place lamb in shallow roasting pan.
Drizzle on Worcestershire.
Roast, uncovered, in a 325° oven until done, about 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from pan to a heated platter and make gravy by adding a little flour and water to the drippings in the pan.
Season with additional salt and pepper.
Overnight refrigeration with seasoning before roasting will enhance the taste of this meat.

title: easy red beans 'n rice
directions: Combine all ingredients, except rice.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat to low and simmer 1 hour.
Serve over hot rice.

title: hot ice cream crepes
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Divide ice cream among crepes and roll up.
Place in ovenproof dish.
Bake 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve with cold chocolate sauce.

title: old-fashioned no fail icing
directions: *Use only to dust away doubts, fears and confusion.

title: crabmeat ball
directions: Mix 1/2 cup of crabmeat in deep bowl with cream cheese, onions, parsley and garlic; form into ball.
Roll ball in Parmesan cheese.
Put in serving dish.
Mix remaining crabmeat, chili sauce and horseradish.
Pour over ball when ready to serve.
Serve with crackers.

title: never fail fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine sugar and milk.
Put over medium heat; bring to a boil.
Boil 11 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; add chocolate chips, margarine and vanilla. Beat with electric mixer for 20 minutes on high.
Add 1 cup nuts. Pour into buttered pans and cool.
Cut in pieces.
Makes 4 pounds.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Heat the pork in a skillet until its crumbly and drain well.
Melt the margarine with the flour and blend.
Add milk and stir; then the cheese and stir until melted; then salt and pepper.
Stir in noodles, pork, chicken, celery and pimentos.
Grease a casserole and pour in hash.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: garlic butter
directions: Combine cream cheese and margarine.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until well blended.
Chill.
Good to spread on any kind of bread.
Serve with any Italian dishes.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar, mustard seed, salt, alum and turmeric in a large kettle.
Bring to a good rolling boil and add cucumbers and boil until they turn white.
Add dill to the jar bottoms, fill and seal while hot.
Onion rings are delicious with them also.

title: sesame pearl cookies
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and vanilla. Stir in flour and salt. Mix well. Shape into balls. Roll in sesame seeds. Place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Makes 3 dozen.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine sugar, salt, celery seed, mustard, pepper and vinegar in a one-quart saucepan; bring to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in corn, green pepper, pimientos and onion. Cool.
Pour into a jar, cover tightly and refrigerate several days before serving.

title: blazing saddles campfire beans
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain off fat.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir and simmer for 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: mexican goulash
directions: Brown hamburger with chopped onion.
Drain grease and sprinkle on taco seasoning.
Add can of Ro-Tel.
Next, cut up corn tortillas and add to hamburger mixture.
Mix in cream of mushroom soup.
After mixture is thoroughly mixed, cover with Velveeta. Put lid on until cheese melts, then serve.

title: strawberry chiffon cake
directions: Measure the first 4 ingredients level, then sift into bowl. Add the next 5 ingredients, in order, to dry ingredients.
Whip the egg whites and cream of tartar to very stiff peaks.
Pour yolk mixture into egg whites; fold carefully.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes, plus 10 minutes at 350°.
Turn pan upside down until cold.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Make cornbread using first three ingredients.
Cool and crumble.
Combine tomatoes, peppers, onion, pickles and bacon.

title: tuna tater pie
directions: Mix 3/4 cup mayo with next 5 ingredients.
Stir in next 3 ingredients.
Turn into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Remove; stir together potatoes and 1/4 cup mayo.
Spoon around edge of pie.
Broil 4 inches from heat until lightly brown.

title: mezetti
directions: Heat shortening, add ground beef and onions, cook until beef is brown. Add chili powder and salt, mix. Sprinkle noodles over top. Mix soup and water and pour over meat mixture. Cover, bring to steaming then lower heat and cook for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese, cook another 5 minutes. Serves 8.

title: steak and rice casserole
directions: Cut steak into cubes.
Brown cubed steak and put in bottom of casserole.
Add rice and soup mixture.
Cover and bake at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: easy hamburger and potato dinner
directions: You will also need aluminum foil.

title: prosciutto sauce with fusilli pasta
directions: Cover bottom of frying pan with olive oil.
Heat oil until hot.
Brown onion lightly.
Add can of crushed tomatoes and sugar. Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add basil and Prosciutto and cook for 20 minutes.
Serve over fusilli pasta.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Fry hamburger and sausage, stirring to break apart.
Add onion, sweet pepper and spices.
Cook until well done; drain all grease away.
Combine meat mixture with spaghetti and stir together. Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top, then sprinkle Mozzarella cheese over top.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted and serve.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese.
Mix all ingredients except nuts.
Form into a ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Half of this recipe makes a large cheese ball.
Refrigerate.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix thoroughly together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes in slow oven (350°).

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix jello according to directions.
Add strawberries, pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Pour half the mixture in jello mold and, when it is firm, spread sour cream on top and then add rest of jello mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: hawaiian fruit pizza
directions: Spread cookie dough on pizza pan to form crust and bake as directed on package.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar for sauce and spread on crust.
Add fruit in circular motion and continue until all crust is covered.
The bananas make a good first layer.

title: divinity(candy)
directions: Beat egg whites until it forms fluffy peaks.
Set aside. Bring sugar, Karo and water to a boil.
Heat until it reaches hard ball stage.
(When drops solidify when added to cold water.) Slowly add hot mixture to egg white while beating at high speed. Continue mixing until mixture is more solidified and gets a dull appearance.
Add vanilla.
Scoop onto wax paper in golf ball size pieces.
Allow to cool.
Maraschino cherries and juice can be added when mixing if desired.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Mix mayo and sour cream together; set aside.
Put together the day before.
Layer in this order (do not mix).
Cover with Saran Wrap and press down together to mellow flavor.

title: company beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in shortening in large skillet.
Add onion, tomatoes, ketchup, steak sauce, green pepper and parsley.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook macaroni and drain.

title: frozen punch
directions: Mix all ingredients well and freeze.
Take out of freezer to thaw and allow to get slushy.

title: breakfast apple fritters
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine egg and milk with a fork and stir into dry ingredients.
Fold in chopped apples.
Drop by cooking spoon size mounds into hot vegetable oil and fry until well browned on both sides.
Drain on paper towel.
Keep warm while all are being fried.
Serve sprinkled with powdered sugar or with syrup on the side or both.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all the ingredients.
Place into casserole.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pineapple paradise salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple and juice. When semi-set, stir in sour cream and nuts.
Serves 12.

title: spice cake
directions: Beat all together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour.

title: cream cheese and fruit salad
directions: In a small saucepan, bring pineapple and sugar to boil and then turn off.
Mix gelatine in water until dissolved.
In large bowl, cream the softened cream cheese.
Gradually stir in the hot pineapple, then add gelatine and mix well.
Add the mandarin oranges, cherries, 2 tablespoons of cherry juice, marshmallows and coconut.
Stir well.
Cool and refrigerate until mixture is set. Keep refrigerated to maintain firmness.

title: princess bars
directions: Filling:
Cook dates with 1 Tbsp. butter and 1/4 c. water on medium heat for about 20 minutes, stir often.
Set aside to cool.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix with milk until smooth and thickened.
Stir in Eagle Brand milk and whipped topping.
Add lemon juice.
Layer bananas with vanilla wafers in large bowl.
Pour pudding mixture over all.
Chill before serving.

title: oven chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash chicken.
Dip in Ranch dressing. Roll in mixture of seasoned salt and Italian bread crumbs.
Bake for 45 minutes or until done.

title: dip
directions: Layer first four ingredients and heat in microwave until warm. Dip with tortilla chips.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix ingredients together and use enough buttermilk to make stiff batter.
Heat deep fryer.
Dip small spoons of batter and drop in grease.
Brown and drain.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix in a saucepan.
Simmer half an hour.
For meats.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Mix all by hand.
Cream butter.
Beat in sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, without previous beating.
Beat well after each egg.
Sift all dry ingredients together in separate bowl.
In another bowl, mix together the honey, brandy and vanilla.
Add a little honey mixture to butter, alternating with flour mixture.
Add fruits and nuts.
Grease cookie sheet lightly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls, 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 11 minutes.

title: garlic roasted chicken and potatoes
directions: In a large roasting pan in a 400° oven, melt butter.
Remove pan from oven.
Cut potatoes in bite size chunks.
Place chicken, potatoes and garlic in pan.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt.
Turn ingredients to coat with butter; arrange chicken skin side up. Bake 40 minutes, basting occasionally with drippings.
Mix syrup and 1/2 teaspoon salt in a cup.
Brush chicken with syrup mixture and spoon drippings in pan over potatoes and chicken.
Bake 20 minutes longer, until chicken and potatoes are fork-tender.

title: pasta fazool
directions: Brown pork; add onion.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add all ingredients. Bring to boil; lower heat and cook 10 to 12 minutes.

title: zucchini parmesan
directions: Peel and slice the zucchini.

Put in microwave bowl with lid. Sprinkle the butter on. After that, sprinkle the black pepper and Parmesan cheese on. Cover bowl with lid and put in microwave for 5 minutes, then 2 to 3 minutes on High.

title: oven omelet
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in buttered or sprayed 3-quart casserole at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Grease or spray baking dish with Pam.
Add diced potatoes. Mix sugar, flour, spices and salt together; sprinkle over potatoes.
Add lemon juice to water and pour over potato mixture. Slice oleo over the potatoes.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients (flour, cocoa, salt, sugar and soda) into 9 x 13-inch square pan.
Add liquid ingredients.
Blend with fork; don't mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
If mixed in bowl, recipe will make 2 (9-inch) cakes, 3 (8-inch) cakes or 2 1/2 dozen cupcakes.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: For dressing, place vinegar, basil, salt, pepper and sugar in food processor or blender. With motor running, add oil in slow, steady stream until oil is thoroughly blended.

title: christmas rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes or until rice is tender. Stir while cooking.

title: lemon cheese bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix, 1 egg and oil until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup; pat in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°. Beat cheese, sugar, lemon juice and 1 egg until light and smooth. Spread over baked layer.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs.
Bake 15 minutes.
Cool, then cut.

title: no cook fondant
directions: Mix with spoon, then knead by hand.
Makes 1 1/3 pounds. Store in cool place.
Shape as desired.

title: banana pudding
directions: Make pudding as directed.
Layer as follows in a 9 x 13-inch pan:
wafers, pudding, bananas, Cool Whip and nuts.

title: hash brown quiche
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press hash brown potatoes in pan and brush with melted butter.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes. Remove from oven and cover with ham, cheese and onions.
Beat milk and eggs and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion. Add green chilies and sour cream. Mix well. Spoon a little of mixture into each tortilla. Add shredded cheese on top. Roll up and place, seam side down, in Pam-sprayed Pyrex.
Mix together soup, green sauce and milk. Pour over enchiladas. Cover with shredded cheese.
Cover with foil and bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spice cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together in a large bowl on low speed for 30 seconds, then on high speed for 3 minutes.
Bake at 350° in long pan for 45 minutes, in round 9-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes or in an 8-inch pan for 40 to 45 minutes.
Top with caramel icing.

title: panetone cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix dry ingredients. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add the vanilla, rum and lemon.
Grease tube pan and sprinkle with flour. Bake in a 400° oven until cake rises, about 45 minutes. Lower oven to 350° and continue baking for another 15 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, rice, milk and vanilla well.
Then mix raisins in next.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Boil the potatoes in water until done.
Peel and dice. Combine with the Velveeta cheese, bacon and mayonnaise.
Mix together.
Bake in casserole dish at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: creole lemonade
directions: Place sugar, water, lemon
juice and pineapple juice in a large punch bowl.
Mix well.

title: pork with sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Cut pork into pieces suitable for serving and place in skillet with oil; brown, then remove.
Add onion; brown slightly.
Return pork to skillet, sprinkle with salt and pepper and cover with boiling water.
Add the apples and sweet potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° until potatoes and apples are tender.
(Serve with sliced tomato salad, milk, bread and butter.)

title: fat-free pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Stir in ingredients in order given. Pour into quiche dish (ungreased, no crust).
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Then bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.

title: garden fresh potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water, covered, until tender; peel and slice.
Add oil, onion, lemon juice, salt and pepper; mix well.
Let stand 1 to 2 hours.
Add celery, green pepper, ham, eggs and mayonnaise; mix lightly.
Spoon into a salad bowl lined with lettuce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: best ever brownies
directions: Melt cocoa with butter in small pan.
Beat eggs well; gradually add sugar.
Stir in vanilla and cocoa mixture, then salt, flour and nuts.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven in a buttered 8 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: stuffed grapevine leaves
directions: Steam onions over very low heat with 1 teaspoon of salt, stirring occasionally, for 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add rice and 1/2 cup of the olive oil and mix.
Add herbs and vegetables and mix.
Add salt and pepper and half the lemon juice. Wash grapevine leaves thoroughly to remove all brine.
Separate leaves carefully.
Remove thick stem portions.
Cut large leaves in half.
Place 1 tablespoonful filling on underside of leaf. Starting at base, fold over and fold in sides, rolling tightly toward point.

title: baked corn
directions: Combine melted butter, egg and sour cream.
Add and stir in whole and creamed corn.
Stir in corn bread mix, salt and pepper. Bake in casserole dish 1 hour at 375°.
Make sure it does not get too dry.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix well with hands.
Form small balls.
If mixture will not stick together, add a few drops of water.
Bake at 325° for twenty minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Yields approximately 36 to 40.

title: blueberry cream cheese pie
directions: Mix Dream Whip per directions.
Add cream cheese.
Whip; pour into pie shell.
Top with pie filling.

title: olive bites
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine flour, salt and mustard in a bowl; stir in cheese.
Combine melted Crisco, milk and Tabasco; add to bowl and stir until dry ingredients are moistened and dough is formed.

title: tossed spicy vegetables
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower in a large saucepan of boiling water until just tender, about 3 minutes.
Drain.
Heat olive oil in heavy medium skillet over medium heat.
Add sliced onion and minced garlic and saute until soft, about 8 minutes.
Add chopped parsley, capers, white wine, vinegar, lemon peel, dried oregano and crushed red pepper and stir 2 minutes.
Add vegetables and toss until coated and heated through.
Season vegetables to taste with salt and pepper.
Mix in grated Parmesan cheese and serve immediately.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: spicy potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until fork-tender.
Do not peel potatoes. Allow to cool and cut into bite-size pieces.
Combine mayonnaise, salsa and mustard and toss with potatoes.
Add scallions, pepper and carrots.
Chill salad until ready to serve.

title: golden carrot slices
directions: Cook carrots until tender in salted water (about 10 minutes). Drain and cool carrots.
Place carrots, onions and peppers in layers in a 1 1/2-quart size container.
Mix soup, sugar, vinegar, oil and mustard together and pour over carrots.
Cover and leave in the refrigerator several hours before serving.
Will keep at least a week in refrigerator.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients and make a loaf. Bake in moderate oven at 350° about 1 1/2 hours. Serves 8.

title: greek vegetarian sandwich
directions: Lightly brown pita bread in frypan; no oil needed (the natural oils come out).
Layer pita with veggies.
Top with cheese and dressing.
Fold in half and eat.
Makes 1 sandwich.

title: broiled tuna and tomato
directions: Combine tuna, mayo, green pepper, mustard, onion and horseradish.
Spread mixture on bread slices.
Top each with a tomato slice.
Arrange cheese on top of tomato.
Place on cookie sheet and broil about 4 inches from heat until cheese melts. Serve immediately.
Can microwave 30 to 60 seconds.

title: hearty chicken pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small saucepan cover butternut squash with water and cook 8 minutes; drain, reserving 3/4 cup liquid.
In a large bowl, combine squash, zucchini, onion and chicken.
In a small saucepan combine evaporated milk and cornstarch.
Add poultry seasoning and flavor enhancer.
Stirring constantly over low heat, add reserved liquid and cook until slightly thickened.
Pour sauce over chicken mixture; fold in sunflower kernels.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and top with second shell, punching edges together.
Sprinkle top with toasted butternut squash seeds, if desired.
Bake 45 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: texas pecan candy cake
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Grease and flour tube pan with removable bottom.
Combine cherries, pineapple and dates in large bowl.
Sprinkle with flour; toss to coat well.
Add pecans and coconut.
Toss to mix.
Add condensed milk; stir to mix well. Spoon evenly into tube pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 250°.
Cool in pan.
Remove from pan and wrap tightly in foil.
Refrigerate at least 2 weeks.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix and refrigerate for several hours.
Drop in hot oil.
Cook until golden brown.

title: whole salmon baked in foil
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place cleaned salmon on long, double-length piece of heavy-duty aluminum foil on top of large baking pan.
Place other ingredients on top.
Bring up edge of foil and seal.
Bake for 50 minutes to 1 hour.
At end of 50 minutes, loosen foil and test for doneness.
Fish is cooked when back center fin can be easily removed when pulled with fingers. Remove from oven.
Skin when cold.
(Save the liquid for court bouillon.)
Decorate with thinly sliced cucumber, dill sprigs, lemon and lime slices, cherry tomatoes, etc.
Serve with Cucumber Sauce.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Stir while cooking over medium heat, especially at end.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sour cream, dry pudding mix, milk and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Layer vanilla wafers, bananas and pudding mix.
Repeat, ending with pudding mix.
Cover with remaining half of Cool Whip.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: Chop
beef and onion fine.
Mix with softened cheese and seasonings.
Shape	into
ball,
roll in chipped beef, covering the outside with the beef.	Serve with Wheat Thins crackers.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Pop corn and set aside.
Combine sugar, water, syrup and salt and cook to hard ball stage.
Add butter and vanilla.
Slowly pour over popcorn.
Mix well and press into balls.
Use shortening or water on hands to form balls.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Pop popcorn.
Pour a large amount into a large bowl.
Have children help add the other ingredients.
Shape into balls.
They are a little sticky until they harden (about 1 hour).
Enjoy!

title: okra pickles(they are hot!)
directions: Put first five ingredients in jar.
Heat to boiling last three.
Pour over okra and seal.

title: topsy turvey apple pie
directions: Spread butter on bottom and sides of pie pan.
Press nuts around side and bottom.
Pat brown sugar over nuts.
Roll pastry and place over nuts
(to keep mix of sugar and butter from caramel state).
Drizzle Karo or honey before the crust goes on.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Turn into pie plate.
Roll out top pastry; adjust over apples.
Seal; prick top of pie with fork. Bake for 20 minutes at 400°, then 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Cool 5 minutes.
Place serving plate; invert (and hope) that pie comes out of pie pan.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook slowly for 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in 1 teaspoon soda.
Spread in greased pan.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
In separate bowl, mix eggs and pineapple.
Mix all with big spoon.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
After cooled, ice with cream cheese icing.

title: banana cream pie(quick and easy -- low calories, 150 calories per piece)
directions: Mix pudding and skim milk; add Cool Whip. Layer sliced banana on bottom of pie crust. Put pudding mixture on top of bananas and then top pie with more sliced bananas. Refrigerate for 3 or more hours or overnight.

title: crispy treats
directions: Mix cereals, peanuts, and marshmallows. Melt bark in oven at 150 degrees. Chocolate can be melted in microwave. Pour over mixture and drop on wax paper to cool or into a 9 x 13 buttered baking dish and cut into small squares when candy begins to set. It will be easier to separate when it is completely cool. If you do not like the marshmallows, replace with extra cereal.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill in freezer until slushy, stirring frequently.
