For parties or showers, match your Kool-Aid with your color scheme.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add chocolate and well beaten eggs. Alternate the mixture with milk and dry ingredients. Drop from spoon on greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes. When cool, ice with favorite butter icing.

title: fancy eggnog
directions: Beat egg yolks and sugar.
Add whiskey slowly, stirring constantly.
Continue stirring and add cream, then stiffly beaten egg whites.
Chill and top each serving with nutmeg.
Yield: 20 to 25 servings.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Blend grated cheese and butter.
Add other ingredients in order.
Drop from spoon bite-sized pieces of dough, which is stiff.
Bake 18 minutes at 325°.
These are easy to keep, may be made well ahead of time and frozen.
Thaw at room temperature and serve.

title: white frosting
directions: Cook milk and flour until thick; cool in refrigerator.
Beat Crisco and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add cold milk-flour mixture and vanilla.
Beat again until fluffy and spread on cake.

title: pita sandwiches
directions: Can use anything you like.

title: orange juice punch
directions: Combine orange juice and lemonade and add 1 cup water (keep refrigerated).
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Stir together.

title: simple punch
directions: Exactly divide in half all ingredients except sherbet or strawberries and mix together.
Add sherbet or strawberries to top of punch with ice.
Sherbet is great for kid's party, while adults love the strawberries.
Makes 2 bowls.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls in pizza pan.
Spread cooked sausage on crust.
Spread hash browns on crust.
Pour eggs-milk over crust. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover full pizza with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese on top after baking.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: *Can substitute fat-free Italian dressing.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix the margarine, flour, brown sugar and nuts together. Pack in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Remove and let it cool completely. Mix the Cool Whip, powdered sugar, cream cheese and vanilla together. Spread over cool crust. Top with cherry pie filling. Refrigerate at least 1 hour to set. Serve.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain all beans, running water over kidney beans to remove thickened juice.
Combine all ingredients and let stand 12 to 24 hours before serving.

title: boiled custard
directions: Beat egg yolks well and strain. Pour eggs over sugar, then add milk.
Cook until it coats a spoon. Add vanilla and set aside to cool.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add salt and pepper.
Drain.
Add all canned ingredients and stir until it comes to a slow boil.
In a 9 x 11-inch casserole, layer:

title: meatball soup
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Shape into small balls.
Brown in oil and drain.
In large pan, combine next 5 ingredients.
Add vegetables and meat balls.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, 15 minutes.

title: italian chicken linguini
directions: In greased casserole dish, bake chicken breasts 45 minutes, covered, at 400°.
Remove from pan; cut in bite size pieces.
Put tomatoes, oregano and cornstarch in saucepan and heat until slightly thickened.
Prepare linguini according to directions on package no more than 2 minutes.
Drain.
Layer linguini, chicken pieces, tomato mixture and cheese.
Bake at 375° for approximately 35 to 40 minutes until cheese melts.

title: pistachio surprise
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and press into 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Open can of pineapple; drain.
Cream together the cottage cheese and package of Jell-O.
Add pineapple, then mix in walnuts and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Let set about 2 hours.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: mountain dew salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water and Mountain Dew.
Chill until almost set.
Add chopped bananas and pineapple. Chill until firm.
Mix pudding and milk.
Let it set and then fold in Cool Whip and frost jello with it.

title: spinach dip
directions: Drain spinach; cook until boiling, then add egg.
Cook until egg is done, then add cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted, then put in bowl.
Add sour cream and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salt and water until tender.
Slice 6 or 7 pieces of the Mexican cheese very thin to place on top of casserole.
Melt the rest of the Mexican cheese and the cream cheese together.
Drain broccoli and add the melted cheese.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Place sliced Mexican cheese on top. Crumble Ritz crackers over cheese.
Broil in oven until brown.

title: baked cod - norwegian style
directions: Lay cod fillets lengthwise in shallow baking pan.
Season with salt and pepper to taste and sprinkle with paprika.
Saute coarsely chopped onion in butter or margarine until golden and tender.
Cook bacon separately until crisp and crumble into onion and butter mixture.
Mix and ladle onto fillets evenly; bake at 325°, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, garlic and drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, ketchup, oregano and sugar.
Remove from heat; add cream cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: orange delight
directions: Whip up in blender.

title: cantaloupe slush
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric blender. Cover and process until smooth. Serve immediately.
Makes 4 cups.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In skillet, brown bacon; add beef and brown.
Add onions and cook, but do not brown.
Drain fat.
Add seasonings, stir in soup. Cook slowly, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Stir in sour cream and heat; do not boil.
Serve over hot buttered noodles.
Serves 6.

title: mustard dip
directions: Combine mustard, vinegar and water in saucepan.
Add sugar and egg yolk.
Stir with wire whisk over medium heat.
Beat until thickens.
Cool.
Whip the cream cheese with electric mixer.
Beat in mustard mixture until smooth.
Store in refrigerator.

title: dilled cheese and salami salad
directions: Cut cheese and salami into matchsticks; place in bowl.
Thinly slice cucumber; add to the bowl.

title: meal-in-one
directions: Using a large casserole, put any type of canned vegetables that you like in the bottom.
Put cut-up potatoes on top.
Salt and pepper.
Place pork chops on top of potatoes.
Slice onion, bell pepper and margarine on top of pork chops.
Cover; cook for one hour on medium.

title: jello pound cake
directions: Mix jello and cake mix; add water and beat 2 minutes.
Add oil and beat 2 minutes.
Beat entire mixture 3 minutes more.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Can be iced or frosted with icing sugar.
Fill center with ice cream or fruit cake; makes a nice birthday cake for a man.

title: brazil nut and date cake
directions: Put nuts, dates and cherries into a large bowl.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt over nut mixture.
Mix with hands until mixture is coated.
Beat eggs until foamy. Add vanilla. Stir into fruit and nuts until well mixed.
Pour into greased and waxed paper pan.
Spread evenly. Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes in a 300° oven.

title: coconut bananas
directions: Cut bananas into fourths.
Place lemon juice, sour cream and coconut in separate bowls.
Dip bananas into lemon juice, roll in sour cream and then in coconut.
Be sure to cover thoroughly.
Put in covered bowl and refrigerate for several hours or overnight. Yield: 16 banana pieces.
Nice for a brunch fruit.

title: no name cake
directions: Mix 1 cup pecans, butter and flour.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: for the crowd casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion; cook until tender but not brown.
Add next 8 ingredients; mix well.
Stir in noodles.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) 30 minutes or until hot.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: quick and easy divinity
directions: In small glass mixing bowl, combine frosting mix, corn syrup, vanilla and boiling water.
Beat with an electric mixer on low speed just until blended.
Beat on high speed for about 5 minutes or until stiff peaks form.
Transfer to larger bowl.
Gradually beat in sugar on low speed.
tags: Betty Crocker fluffy white frosting mix

title: layered salad
directions: In a large bowl, put items in by the order given.
Chill overnight, covered, before serving.

title: hilda's white cookies
directions: Cream sugars and lard.
Add remaining ingredients with flour (enough to stiffen) and roll out.
Place on greased sheet. Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: decorating frosting
directions: Beat egg whites until they hold a soft peak.
Add sugar gradually and beat until sugar is dissolved and frosting stands in peaks.
Add syrup and beat one minute.
Use food coloring to get desired color.
Add a few drops of water, if a thinner frosting is desired.
Keep well covered when not in use.

title: swedish heirloom cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Shape into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet 15 to 18 minutes at 325°.
Do not brown. Roll warm cookies in additional confectioners sugar.

title: mashed potato meat casserole
directions: Fry meat and put in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour in corn and top with mashed potatoes.
Smooth top.
Pour a little milk on top and shake on a little pepper.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat. Sift dry ingredients together and stir into creamed mixture. Add nuts. Form dough into rolls 1 1/2-inches in diameter and wrap in waxed paper.
Chill in refrigerator.
Cut dough into slices and arrange on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: monkey bread
directions: Coat biscuits with sugar and cinnamon.
Place in Bundt pan. Melt butter and 3/4 cup sugar.
Add nuts and pour over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
No need to grease pan.
Dump on plate immediately.
Break into pieces and enjoy.
Makes a good breakfast bread.

title: nut puffs
directions: Mix in order given.
Roll in balls.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar when cool.

title: company casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Saute meat in butter or oleo.
Stir in tomato sauce.
Remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, onions and green pepper.
In 2-quart casserole, spread half of noodles.
Cover with cheese mixture, then cover with rest of noodles.
Pour melted butter over noodles. Pour tomato meat sauce over all.
Chill overnight, if desired. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 8 servings.

title: streusel pie crust
directions: Mix Crisco and 3 cups flour.
Then add egg, salt, vinegar, and water.
Mix well.
Roll out dough.
Set aside.
To make streusel topping, mix 3/4 c. flour, cinnamon, brown sugar, and oleo.
Crumble all together with a pastry cutter.
Sprinkle on top of pie dough.
Bake 15 minutes at 450 degrees, then 35 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter; add flour and blend.
Add milk; cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add cheeses, onion and steak sauce.
Cook until cheese melts, stirring constantly.
Cook macaroni; add to cheese mixture.
Put into 2-quart casserole; bake 20 minutes in moderate oven.

title: easy broccoli quiche
directions: Cook broccoli, covered, in a small amount of boiling water for 10 minutes; drain.
Place broccoli in a lightly greased 9-inch pie plate; sprinkle with green pepper, onion and cheese.
Set aside.

title: six layer dinner
directions: Place in well-greased casserole in the order given above. Season layers to taste.
Bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours in moderate oven with cover on.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Boil roast in water and wine for 3 hours.
Shred beef.
Remove half the water and wine; reserve.
Combine with the wine and water all the ingredients including the roast.
Season and simmer, adding reserve liquid as necessary.
Cook until desired doneness.

title: chinese meatballs
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Dredge in 1/3 cup cornstarch.
Pour oil into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine sugar and 3 tablespoons cornstarch in large saucepan; mix well.
Add pineapple juice, chicken broth, 2 tablespoons soy sauce and vinegar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Add meatballs, pineapple and pepper.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve over rice.

title: miracle meat rolls
directions: Mix ingredients into a meat mixture.

title: cracker salad
directions: Crumble the crackers; add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine
first 6 ingredients in a large mixing bowl and blend well.
Combine
buttermilk,
eggs and oil and stir into dry ingredients.
Cover
mixture
and
refrigerate overnight. Preheat oven
to
Fill cupcake papers 3/4 full and bake 20 minutes or until done.

title: applesauce spice cake(low-fat diabetic recipe)
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine the first 6 ingredients.
In mixer bowl, beat the margarine with mixer for 30 seconds.
Add sugar; beat until well combined.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients and applesauce alternately to beaten mixture.
Stir in raisins.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 15.

title: banana sundae dessert
directions: Cover
9 x 13-inch glass pan with cracker crumbs.
Slice bananas on top,
then
slices of ice cream on top of bananas. Sprinkle walnuts on top and freeze until firm.
Melt chocolate chips and 1/2 cup butter. Add
powdered
sugar and evaporated milk.
Cook until thick and smooth; add vanilla.
Cool.
Pour over
ice
cream and return to freezer.
Top with whipped cream and a cup of cracker crumbs.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Trim fat from steak; cut in bite size pieces.
Cook in hot oil in large skillet over medium heat until browned, stirring often. Add onion and green pepper; cook 5 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in tomatoes and next 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil; cover. Reduce heat and cook 45 minutes or until tender, adding additional water if necessary.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4; contains 341 calories.

title: easy stew
directions: Cut up all ingredients and place in baking dish. Add gravy, tomato sauce, flour, wine and seasonings.
Mix well.
Add water so liquid almost covers ingredients.
Cover dish tightly with aluminum foil so steam can't escape.
Place in oven at 325°.
No need to preheat oven.
Bake 3 to 4 hours.
After 3 hours, add 1 can drained peas, if desired.

title: brownies
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate together.
Add eggs, sugar, vanilla, flour, baking powder and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350` for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: hot chocolate sauce for ice cream
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a saucepan and gradually add water and cook about 3 minutes.
Add the vanilla.
Serve hot or cold over ice cream.

title: microwave baked apples
directions: Cut a thin slice off bottom of each apple to form a flat surface.
Place apples in a microwave casserole.
Mix syrup, butter and cinnamon in a small bowl.
Spoon into center of apples. Cover loosely with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes or until apples are tender, rotating dish halfway through cooking time.

title: stir-fried pork and vegetables
directions: In large skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add pork and stir-fry approximately 10 minutes or until meat is no longer pink. Add vegetables and 1/2 cup water; mix gently.
Bring to boil, cover and simmer for 6 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are hot.
Garnish with sprouts.
Contains 8 g. fat and 65 mg. cholesterol.
Serves 4.

title: crispy-crinkly spice snaps
directions: Mix together, shortening, sugar, egg and molasses.
Sift together and stir in flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves and ginger.
Mix all together and form into walnut-sized balls. Put them two inches apart on a greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until crispy and crinkly!

title: fruit cake
directions: Cut
up
fruit and nuts; mix with 1/4 cup flour and set aside. beat butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour
and
flavorings.
Stir
in	fruit
and
nut mixture.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: light fettucine alfredo
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan over medium heat.
Add garlic, saute 1 minute.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add milk, stir until blended.
Cook 8 minutes or until thick.
Stir in cream cheese. Add 1 cup Parmesan cheese, stir until melted.
Pour over hot fettucine.
Sprinkle remaining Parmesan over mixture.

title: rocky road bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Heat 1/2 cup chocolate chips and margarine over low heat until melted.
Mix Bisquick, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Stir in chocolate mixture. Spread in pan; bake for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows, nuts and remaining chocolate chips.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes, or until marshmallows are lightly browned.
Cool completely.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: eggplant anina
directions: Slice eggplants in circles; leave skin on.
Slice potatoes; leave skin on.
In one frying pan, fry eggplants with a reasonable amount of salt to get water out of eggplant.
Drain well on paper towels.
In another frying pan, fry potatoes.
Drain well on paper towels.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Mix pudding as directed on box. Slice cake and line bowl with cake.
Put layer of strawberries and layer of pudding, then another layer of cake. Top it off with Cool Whip.

title: noodle broccoli cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray casserole dish with cooking spray.

title: upside-down peach cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 9-inch cake pan.
Set aside. Place butter, sugar, egg and vanilla in large bowl.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Mix half of flour into egg mixture.
Pour in cream and mix well.
Add remaining flour and mix well.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Set batter aside.

title: tuna spread
directions: Mix above ingredients.
Butter bread (optional if not freezing) and lightly spread mixture on bread.
Can be frozen up to 2 months. Makes 48 (1-inch) squares.

title: boiled cookies
directions: In a saucepan, mix first four ingredients.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 1/2 minutes, then remove from heat.
Stir in oatmeal, peanut butter, nuts and vanilla.
When well mixed, drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sour cream. Sift flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Pour half of batter into lightly greased baking pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 of topping over batter.
Pour remaining batter over mixture, then sprinkle on remaining topping.
Take spoon and press topping lightly into batter.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: countryside chicken bake
directions: Place rice in cake pan sprayed with cooking spray.
Combine soup and all other ingredients, mixing until well blended.
Pour half the mixture over rice; top with chicken and remaining soup mixture.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour
until chicken is tender and rice is cooked.
You may sprinkle with paprika before baking for a more colorful look.

title: baked corn
directions: Dump in bowl.
Mix and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: porky pig casserole
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water. Mix soup and water, green pepper, pimento, onion and mayonnaise. Drain almost all water off macaroni. Stir cheese in macaroni and let melt.
Mix everything together and put in casserole dish. Top with tidbits. Put pats of butter all over the top. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes or until tidbits brown.

title: cornucopia stuffing
directions: Saute carrot, celery and onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Stir in sage, salt, cinnamon and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
In a large bowl, combine bread cubes, chopped apple, walnuts and wheat germ.
Add cooked vegetable mixture.
Drizzle with enough broth to moisten.
Stuff turkey as usual.

title: oatmeal macaroons
directions: Mix oleo, sugars, vanilla and eggs.
Beat very well.
Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon to oleo mix.
Mix well.
Fold in oats, raisins and walnuts.
Drop on greased sheets.
Cook at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese and soften cream cheese.
Mix with all other ingredients, except parsley and nuts.
Cool thoroughly in fridge, then shape into balls (size you desire).
Then roll each ball into parsley and ground nut mixture.
Wrap in Saran Wrap. Keep refrigerated.

title: broccoli-cheddar rolls
directions: Roll dough into a 12-inch square on a lightly floured surface. Combine broccoli and next 4 ingredients; stir well.
Spread mixture evenly over dough, leaving a 1/2-inch border.
Starting on one side, roll dough tightly jelly roll fashion.
Moisten seam edge of dough with water.
Press securely to seal, turning seam side down.
Cut roll into 8 slices.
Cut each slice almost in half again, cutting to within 1/2 inch of bottom.
Gently open out halves, invert and place on a lightly greased baking sheet. Brush with melted butter.
Cover and let rise in a warm place free from drafts for 45 minutes or until doubled in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes until golden brown.
Yields 8 servings.

title: sweet potato denise
directions: Cook potatoes in skins.
Peel and slice.
Combine cranberry sauce, apple juice or cider, water, brown sugar and nutmeg in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook over low heat for 5 minutes. Stir until margarine is melted.
Arrange sweet potatoes, nuts and raisins in a casserole.
Pour sauce over and bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: liver in creole sauce
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a skillet and cook over medium heat until vegetables are tender (2 to 3 minutes).
Add tomatoes and next 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until liver is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix ingredients (except soup); shape into balls.
Place in skillet and cover with tomato soup.
Bake slowly at 325° for 1 1/4 hours; remove cover last 15 minutes to allow rice to pop out of balls for porcupine appearance.

title: pineapple mustard chicken
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Brown in hot oil.
Add garlic and thyme.
Turn chicken over; brown other side.
Combine 2 tablespoons reserved juice with cornstarch; set aside.
Combine honey and mustard; add to chicken in skillet with remaining pineapple juice.
Cover; simmer for 25 minutes.
Stir cornstarch mixture into pan juices. Add pineapple; stir until sauce boils and thickens.

title: italian chicken
directions: You will need 1 Reynolds bag (cooking).

title: perfection salad
directions: This recipe was given to Robin by her Aunt Jane Capewell Ward and was tested for Knox gelatine by her mother, Peg Sutliff Capewell and her grandma Clara (Kit) Bronwell Tracy Loucks from Gloversville, North Carolina.

title: yummies
directions: Mix the first five ingredients and add powdered sugar.
Mix and chill.
Melt chocolate chips with paraffin.
Form chilled candy into logs or balls and dip on toothpick into paraffin mixture.
Place on waxed paper to dry.
Makes 4 dozen. Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar; cream until light and fluffy. Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients with milk; alternate.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter in cake pan.
Sprinkle with 3 tablespoons brown sugar.
Arrange pineapple and nuts.
Pour butter over fruit and bake 45 minutes in moderate oven.

title: championship chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese evenly in 8 inch microwave dish or pie plate.
Spread chili evenly over cream cheese.
Sprinkle cheddar cheese over top. Microwave on high 1 minute.
Rotate 1/2 turn and continue to microwave on high for 1 additional minute or until cheese is melted.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: patti's dip
directions: Mix ingredients and form into 3 small balls or 1 large.

title: fruited tea cooler
directions: Steep tea bags in 1 quart boiling water for 5 minutes. Combine with remaining ingredients and 2 1/2 quarts water in larger container.
Serve over ice cubes and garnish with mint leaves.
Yields 8 servings.

title: squash patties
directions: Mash squash; add other ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls into deep fat.
Brown on one side; turn and brown on other side. Remove from fat; drain on paper towels.

title: fruit julius
directions: Combine all ingredients together in a blender.
Serves 2.

title: linguine with shrimp
directions: In small saucepan, cook briefly on mid-heat first 8 ingredients.
Pour over cooked linguine.
Garnish with fresh shredded parsley and fresh grated Parmesan cheese.

title: grilled herbed corn
directions: In a small bowl, mix first six ingredients.
Spread 1 tablespoon of mixture over each ear of corn.
Wrap corn in heavy-duty foil.
Grill, covered, for 10 to 15 minutes, turning often.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and egg.
Beat well and add vanilla.
Sift flour and other dry ingredients.
Add these and milk.
Chill dough.
Roll and cut with floured cutter.
Bake at 325°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Put toast, meat and cheese in large glass baking pan (9 x 13-inch).
Beat the eggs, milk, salt and mustard together.
Pour over other ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours or more. Bake 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: cranberry wassail
directions: Tie cloves and cinnamon in a cheesecloth bag; set aside. Combine cranberry juice cocktail, next 6 ingredients and spice bag in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Uncover and simmer an additional 20 minutes.
Discard spice bag.
Add ginger ale and cook until hot.
Garnish with apple wedges, if desired.
Yield: 17 cups.

title: mrs. cleaver's cookies(beaver's favorite)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Blend dry ingredients.
Stir in.
Mix in chips.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Add beef consomme, beef broth and onion soup mix.
Stir well. Add rice. Stir.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mama's egg pie
directions: Beat eggs, add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, mix chips, nuts and eggs.
Add sugars, butter and flour.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into pie shell, place on baking sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes (or until pastry is lightly brown).
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: microwave texas-style hot chili
directions: Place bacon on microwave roasting rack in 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cook on High for 4 1/2 to 5 minutes.
Crumble bacon and set aside.
Slice sausage.
Cook in 3-quart casserole on High for 5 minutes, stirring 3 times.
Drain off fat.
Add beef, onion, green pepper, garlic, chili pepper, jalapeno pepper, chili powder, salt, oregano, water and tomato paste.
Cook, covered, on High for 45 minutes.
Drain beans and add to chili.
Cook, covered, on High for 30 to 35 minutes.
Can be served with shredded American cheese.
Makes 8 servings.

title: shrimp nixon
directions: Combine shrimp, eggs, Bleu cheese, Cheddar cheese, mayonnaise, honey and salt.
Mix gently. Butter a 2-quart casserole.
Fill with shrimp mixture and top with potato chips.
Bake in a preheated 250° oven for 1 hour.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Combine and simmer for 20 minutes.
Do not boil.
After 20 minutes, remove the cinnamon stick and lemon peel.
Serve with orange slices studded with cloves.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread in casserole dish. Top with crushed corn flakes and/or slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese and broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add onion and garlic and saute over medium to low heat until onion is tender.
Sprinkle flour over and cook, stirring constantly 3 minutes.

title: fudge cookies
directions: In a sauce pan, put milk, chips, and butter.
Cook over low heat until melted.
Stir in flour, vanilla and pecans.
Drop cookie mix by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.

title: toll house pan cookies
directions: In large bowl, combine margarine, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla until creamy. Beat in the eggs. Add flour, baking soda and salt. Mix well. Stir in chocolate chips. Pour into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool, cut and enjoy.

title: crock-pot round steak
directions: Cover steak with flour and brown with shortening in skillet. Place mixes in crock-pot and add 2 1/2 cups water.
Stir until well mixed.
Add steak.
Cook on high for 5 to 6 hours.

title: four star asparagus soup
directions: Bring broth, asparagus, 1/2 teaspoon thyme, garlic and bay leaf to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes.
Remove bay leaf. Process in blender until smooth.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Mix well the cream cheese, sugars and extract.
Dip apples in mixture.
Roll in nuts, if desired.

title: tangy cube steaks
directions: Bring large pan of hot tap water to boil for noodles. Meanwhile, heat oil in large, heavy skillet and cook steaks, following recipe below.
Cook noodles after steaks are browned. Drain.
Toss with butter.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix all and spread in 13 x 9 x 2 greased pan.
(Pampered Chef Bar Pan works well.)
Bake 25 minutes or until brown.

title: conventional crepes(the official breakfast of the davis family)
directions: Mix all ingredients with a wire whisk.
Take out the white things (from the eggs).
Melt butter in a skillet or spray it with nonstick spray and pour some mix onto it, spreading it thin by tilting the pan.
Flip.
Cover with sugar or fruit and roll. Cover the top of the rolled crepe with sugar, whipped cream, etc. Makes 12.
Double to make 24.

title: black-eyed pea salad (alabama)(heritage of america cookbook)
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together black-eyed peas, tomatoes, corn, green onion and jalapeno peppers.
Cover and chill for several hours.

title: gumbo stew
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add onion and garlic; cook until onion is soft.
Add tomatoes, okra and seasonings; simmer for 20 minutes. Add spinach (you can also use other dark greens) and simmer five minutes longer.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: bluefish recipe
directions: You will need a brown bag large enough to hold fish.

title: strawberry or raspberry pie
directions: Boil water, sugar, cornstarch and jello together; cool.
Stand berries up in shell and pour cooled mixture over.
Chill before serving.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: chili popcorn
directions: Combine margarine, chili powder, salt, garlic powder and paprika; drizzle over warm popcorn.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil; boil for about 15 minutes.
Makes about 1/2 gallon.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large mixer bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 10 minutes.
Pour into paper-lined 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: onion soup
directions: Cook onions slowly in butter and Crisco oil in covered pot for 15 minutes.
Uncover and raise heat to moderate.
Add salt, pepper and sugar.
Stir frequently until deep golden brown.
Sprinkle flour in and stir for 3 minutes.
Remove and add boiling stocks. Return to heat and simmer for 4 to 5 minutes.
Serve with French bread covered with cheeses and browned under the broiler.
Serves 6.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes until crumbly.
Mix with salt and pepper to taste.
Mix with other ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 60 minutes.

title: cherry winks
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat margarine and sugar until light.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Add flour mixture. Mix well.
Stir in nuts, dates and chopped cherries.
Shape tablespoon of dough into balls.
Roll in cereal.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Top each with cherry quarter.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 14 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: pea and peanut salad
directions: Put peas in boiling water for 1 minute.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Drain well.
Mix all together.

title: cheese cake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together flour and brown sugar; cut in butter until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Set aside 1 cup of crumb mixture for topping.
Press remaining mixture into bottom of an ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
In mixer bowl, beat cream cheese on medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add egg, milk, lemon juice and vanilla.
Beat well.
Spread over baked layer.
Combine nuts and reserved cup of crumb mixture.
Sprinkle over cream cheese mixture.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into bags.
Yields 24 bars.

title: gooey bars
directions: In bowl, mix cake mix, margarine and 1 egg with a fork.
Press in a greased 11 x 13-inch pan.
In another bowl, mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs; beat 5 minutes.
Pour over pan contents.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: swiss steak(crock-pot)
directions: Cut steak into serving-size pieces.
Season with salt and pepper; place in crock-pot.
Add onions, pepper and celery.
Pour soup over all.
Cover and cook on low 8 hours.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix all together and chill overnight.
Serve with cut up Lenders onion bagels.

title: chicken tacos
directions: Saute onion in bacon drippings until tender.
To this, add both cans of soup and milk and stir until thoroughly mixed.
To this add chopped peppers, including juice.
Drain chicken pieces and add to mixture.
Stir once more until thoroughly mixed.
Boil rapidly for 10 minutes, stirring to keep from scorching.
Let cool.

title: ugly cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, eggs, 1 stick oleo and water.
Pour in a 13 1/2 x 9-inch pan; do not cook!

title: greatest ever cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg, mixing well, then oil again mixing well.
Add oats, corn flakes, coconut and nuts.
Stir well. Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix well.
Form into balls the size of walnuts.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with a fork dipped in water.
Bake until golden brown.
Allow to cool on cookie sheets a few minutes before removing.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt.
Combine Crisco, margarine and sugars.
Beat until creamy.
Add vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Chill dough overnight.

title: spaghetti
directions: Cook garlic, green pepper, onion, salt, red pepper and paprika in cooking oil for 10 minutes.
Add ground beef and cook for 10 minutes longer or until brown.
Add spaghetti and cook 10 minutes. Add tomatoes and corn; simmer for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream and blend the Cheddar cheese with the Blue cheese.
Add Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Put in small bowl.
Cover and let it age for 6 hours. Shape in ball. Roll in pecans and parsley. Wrap in wax paper and chill before serving.

title: fudge peppermint dream
directions: Mix and pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze for 15 minutes.

title: country corn bread(makes two 8 x 8 x 2-inch breads)
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in large bowl.
Add eggs and milk.
Stir to make a smooth batter; stir in bacon drippings.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pans.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 25 minutes or until crusty and golden brown.
Cool slightly and serve warm.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and salt; set aside.
In a saucepan bring to a full boil oleo, water and cocoa; then set aside.
Mix soda and buttermilk; beat in eggs.
Add cocoa sauce to dry ingredients; then add buttermilk mixture and vanilla.
Mix together well.
Batter will be thin.
Grease and flour a large 9 x 15-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: no bake pineapple whipped cream cake
directions: Separate ladyfingers into single layers.
Line the sides and bottom of a 9 or 10-inch spring-form pan with some of the ladyfingers, rounded side of ladyfingers facing outside of pan. Set aside.
Whip the cream stiff.
Beat together the sugar and cream cheese.
(For best results, have cream cheese at room temperature for 1 hour prior to recipe use.)
Fold the whipped cream into the cream cheese and sugar mixture and beat slightly. Spread 1/3 of the whipped cream mixture over the ladyfingers. Then spread 1/4 of the pineapple pie filling.

title: everything cookies
directions: Mix oil or applesauce, margarine and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla, then add flour, salt, baking soda and cream of tartar. Finally add oatmeal, rice cereal, chocolate chips, nuts and coconut.
Bake on cookie sheets at 350° for 10 to 18 minutes.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins until tender.
Add salt, sugar, corn syrup, vinegar and beaten eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into uncooked pie crust.
Cover with a thin layer of pie crust to make a lattice design.
Bake in moderate oven until golden brown.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Cover bottom of pizza pan with cookie dough.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Mix together Cool Whip, cream cheese and xxxx sugar.
Spread over cooled crust.
Layer sliced fruit over Cool Whip mixture.
Mix both juices, sugar and cornstarch together.
Boil glaze until thick.
Drizzle over fruit.
Chill and serve.

title: cream cheese and olive sandwiches
directions: Combine cheese, olives, nuts and mayonnaise. Spread on bread and cut off crusts.
Make into bite sized sandwiches.
Use pick to put an olive or pickle on top.

title: new england corn chowder
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan.
Add onion and cook a few minutes until tender.
Add potatoes and enough water to cover them in the pan.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Turn heat back to maintain boil, for about 10 minutes.

title: barbecue ribs(crock-pot)
directions: Sprinkle ribs with salt and pepper and broil 30 minutes to brown and remove excess fat.
Put the sliced onion in the Crock-Pot.
Slice the ribs into serving pieces and put in on top of the onion.
Pour in the barbecue sauce.
Cover and cook on Low 8-10 hours (High: 4-5 hours).

title: egg casserole
directions: Trim crust from bread.
Tear bread into pieces.
Mix with shredded cheese.
Spread in a 7 1/2 X 12 inch greased baking dish alternating with strips of bacon.
Beat eggs with milk.
Stir in salt, pepper, mustard and cream of tartar.
Pour over bread and cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Refrigerate overnight.
Back uncovered for 50 to 60 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: fuzzy navel cake
directions: Mix together ingredients with a spoon. Grease and flour 9 x 13 cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean. Cool cake.

title: curry beef
directions: Wash and trim beef; set aside.
Cut onion and garlic; put oil in pressure cooker; add garlic and let fry until brown.
Add onion and fry one minute. Add beef and a little salt, fry until light brown.
Add water.
Cover cooker and let it pressure for 10 minutes.
Put cooker under cold tap water.
When the steam is gone, open cooker.
Put it back on the stove.
Add curry, potatoes, pepper, coconut milk and salt to taste.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Serve on rice.

title: pumpkin bread or cupcakes
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, oil, pumpkin and water.
Mix all dry ingredients together and add to first mixture.
Makes 2 loaves of bread or 24 muffins.
Bake at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in covered casserole dish at 400° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat and bake at 350° until done.

title: corn salad
directions: Chop
all vegetables.
Mix
all
ingredients
well
and bring mixture to a full boil.
Cook 30 minutes after it starts boiling. Place in jars while hot and seal.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together cream cheese and pineapple. Add green pepper, onion and seasoned salt. Mix well and shape into a ball. Roll ball in chopped pecans until outside is coated. Chill before serving. Serve with crackers.

title: kevin's fizz
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in container of an electric blender; blend until smooth.
Stir in club soda.
Serve right away.
Makes 7 cups.

title: refreshing summer delight
directions: Mix all together in a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients as you would for pie crust.
Add buttermilk and mix well.
Add raisins and knead a little.
Shape into 2 large or 3 small loaves.
Bake in 8-inch pie tins.
Just before you put loaves into oven, cut a cross on top of each.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Check with a cake tester.
Keep in plastic bags to mellow.
It is best after sitting a day.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes in a saucepan.

Add water to cover and bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until very tender. Drain. Combine potatoes, cream cheese, yogurt, garlic and salt in a bowl. Beat until smooth. Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish coated with Pam spray.
Drizzle margarine over mixture. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: boeuf bourguignonne
directions: Brown bacon and beef; season with 1 1/2 tsp. salt and pepper; stir in flour.
Cook in crock-pot for 8 to 10 hours.
Cream 1/4 c. flour and water for thickening.
Serve over pasta.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Melt butter.
Roll Rice Krispies very fine.
Dip chicken pieces in butter and roll in Rice Krispies.
Sprinkle on garlic salt, paprika and pepper.
Bake in oven 1 hour or more.

title: lemony apple dumplings
directions: Combine flour and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cut in shortening until crumbly.
Stir in milk until pastry forms a ball; set aside.
Stir brown sugar, butter, cinnamon and remaining salt to form a paste. Divide and press into center of each apple; pat any extra filling on outside of apples.
On a floured surface, roll pastry into a 14-inch square.
Cut into four 7-inch squares.
Place 1 apple in center of each square.
Brush edges of pastry with egg white. Fold up corners to center; pinch to seal.
Place in a greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: "no calorie" cake
directions: Bake cake mix as directed.
Remove from oven and poke holes all over top of cake with a wooden spoon handle.
Pour over the top, sweet milk and butterscotch or caramel topping while cake is warm.
Just before serving, frost with Cool Whip and crushed Heath bar.
There won't be leftovers!

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan; bring to a boil and simmer 20 minutes.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to boil; let cool.
Mix together the yeast, warm water and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Mix in the flour. Batter will be sticky.
Let raise once, then form into balls, 3 to a muffin cup.
Let raise again.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. (Dough can be used for cinnamon rolls.)
This will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: parmesan dip
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.
Serve with baked potato spears or on baked potatoes.

title: cheese garlic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix Bisquick with milk and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat for 30 seconds.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix margarine and garlic powder.
Brush over warm biscuits before removing from cookie sheet.
Serve warm.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk; then pour over mixture of cracker crumbs, raisins, nuts and cherries.
Stir until well mixed and place in greased mold or bowl until cold.
Turn out and keep refrigerated.
It will stay fresh for several weeks.

title: maple walnut bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a bowl.
Add walnuts, stirring to cook evenly with flour mixture. Combine milk, eggs, oil, syrup and vanilla.
Add all at once to flour mixture and stir only to dampen dry ingredients.
Turn batter into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Cool in pan on rack for 10 minutes, then turn onto rack to cool completely.
Wrap cooled bread in foil and store overnight for easier slicing.
Serve with butter or cream cheese.

title: luscious lemon cake
directions: Bake cake by box directions to make 2 layers.
Mix other ingredients together and frost and stack cakes.

title: pear-pineapple salad
directions: Beat egg, sugar and flour.
Mix.
Then add juice.
Cook until thick and add vinegar.
Let cool.
Add to fruit in a large bowl. Top with grated cheese, whipped cream and nuts.
This will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Cream
butter and margarine.
Add sugar and cream again. Add flour
gradually.
Add
vanilla
and nuts.
Shape in small rolls and freeze.
Cut slices to your desired thickness.
Bake until brown around edges at 350°.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cut chicken into thin strips and cook.
Mix 1/2 of picante sauce, cream cheese and chicken in saucepan over low heat until smooth.
Spoon 2 tablespoons chicken mixture onto each tortilla; roll up.
Place seam side down, in lightly greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese over tortillas; cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Pour remaining picante sauce over tortillas.
If desired, top with sour cream and olives.

title: yellow squash souffle
directions: Slice squash and cook until partly done.
Drain.
Place squash in a deep casserole.
Beat eggs, add sugar, flour, onion flakes and Milnot.
Put margarine on hot squash in casserole.
Pour liquid mixture over squash and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate chip coconut pecan bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pat into 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Mix together remaining ingredient and pour over cake mixture.
Pour 1 can Eagle Brand milk over all and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover for 1 day.
Stir and pour into quart jar with holes in lid so it can breath.
Refrigerate for 2-3 days before using. To feed starter pour into bowl and add the same amounts of sugar, potato flakes and warm water.
Let set 8-12 hours.
Take out one cup and put the rest back in a jar in the refrigerator.
May feed every 3-7 days.

title: barbecue franks
directions: Combine onion, catsup, water, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Add franks to sauce. Simmer another 5 to 7 minutes.
Serve in warm roll.
Add sauce to flavor.

title: little smokies crescent wraps
directions: Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Cut each lengthwise into 3 triangles.
Place one little smokie in dough.
Place on ungreased baking sheet, dough point down.
Bake according to dough package directions.
Serve hot or warm.
Makes 48.

title: broccoli-spinach bake
directions: Defrost and drain vegetables.
Mix with stuffing and egg. Put half into baking dish (about 8 x 8-inch or 2-quart round), sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Spread on 1/2 can soup and 1/2 of onions.
Add remaining vegetables, soup and onions.
Bake, covered, 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: chocolate filled snowballs
directions: Beat butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add sifted flour and nuts.
Blend well; chill dough.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Brown hamburger.
Put spaghetti on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add 1 package Cheddar and Mozzarella cheese.
Add mushrooms.
Spread sauce and hamburger over mushrooms.
Add remaining package Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake 40 minutes at 400°.

title: stuffed pepper with salmon
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cut 2 peppers in half, seeds removed.
Parboil 15 minutes and drain.
Stuff with salad mixture. Pour tomato juice around pepper.
Bake 350-375° for 20 minutes. If dry add more juice.
Serving 2.

title: zesty french dressing
directions: In a blender or food processor, process all ingredients until smooth and thickened.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour. Shake well before serving. Yield: about 1 1/2 cups.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Put into bottom of quart jar.
Fill with sliced pickles, peeled or unpeeled (don't slice too thin).
Then add more dill and onion on top.
Fill can with following Hot Vinegar Mixture.

title: pickle relish
directions: Chop fine the cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Salt to taste. Cover with water; let stand overnight.
Next morning, drain and add remaining ingredients.
Cook for about 1 hour on medium heat. Place in jars and seal.

title: quick and easy 15 minute soup
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Then add sauteed hamburger.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Do not add any other seasonings.

title: easy cream cheese fruit squares
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

title: sutton's chicken
directions: Dust chicken with flour, dip into an egg wash made by beating eggs with milk, then dip in cornmeal.
Heat oil in large skillet. Fry chicken until golden brown, 5 to 7 minutes on each side.
Put a ham slice on top of each chicken breast, then turn carefully so that ham is underneath.
Lower heat and cook 5 minutes more. Remove chicken from pan and keep warm.
Add chicken stock and coffee to the same pan and reduce by half.
Stir in butter and cream, lower heat and cook until thickened.
Stir in scallions, season to taste.
Place chicken, ham side up, on plates and top with ham gravy.
Serve with grits and okra.

title: texas beef skillet
directions: Combine garlic with salt.
Saute onion in oil for 5 minutes. Add garlic, salt and ground beef.
Cook 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer over low heat, stirring occasionally, 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: coffee-cola cooler
directions: *May substitute 1 tablespoon brown sugar.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Mix well and place in 3 (9-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cushaw (squash) pie
directions: Combine cushaw, sugar and salt.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 15 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Do not overbake.
Makes 2 (9-inch) deep dish pies.

title: egg gravy
directions: In skillet add drippings.
Heat the drippings.
Stir in the flour.
Cook and stir until brown.
Add the water, beaten egg, salt and pepper.
Stir to right thickness.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: In a saucepan, boil the water with 1 tsp. baking soda.
Pour mixture over nuts and dates; set aside.
Cream together mayonnaise and sugar, then add cocoa.
Add to nuts and dates.
Gradually add flour, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and stir well.
Bake at 350° for 40-45 minutes.

title: sally lun bread
directions: Proof yeast with water; set aside 5 minutes.
Scald milk with sugar and butter mixture.
Cool to lukewarm.
Place milk mixture in large mixing bowl, cool lukewarm.
Add 3 cups flour, salt and yeast mixture.
Blend until smooth paste.
Add eggs to make batter.
Add rest of flour to form dough.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes until smooth; sit in warm place, covered, at 80° to 90° until double in size.
Divide dough in 4 to make large loaves.
Shape, place in greased loaf pan; allow to rise.
Bake at 350° for 20 or 30 minutes.
While hot, brush with milk and melted butter mixture.

title: mac and ham casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed on package.
Add peas, ham and milk.
Mix well.

title: ester's zucchini bread loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugars with oil; blend well.
Add eggs and mix.
Add zucchini and mix well.
Add vanilla and sifted dry ingredients; blend well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour batter into 2 loaf pans (7 3/8 x 3 5/8 x 2 1/4-inches) greased.
Bake 45 minutes; test with toothpick.
Let set 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: sweet and sour sausage delight
directions: Wash sausage, cut up into small pieces and brown in frying pan.
Set aside.
In large dish, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Add sausage.
Bake in oven at 350° for 2 hours longer for thicker sauce (stir occasionally).
Delicious!!!!

title: mushroom rice
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole bowl.
Cut margarine in pats.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: crawfish pie
directions: Saute all vegetables in margarine until tender, about 10 minutes.
Add whipping cream, evaporated milk, cornstarch, garlic powder, Tony's, and crawfish tails.
Cook until thickened.
Place in uncooked pie shell.
Cover with second pie shell and bake at 350° until golden brown, about 40 minutes.

title: blueberry sour cream streusel pie
directions: Combine sugar, brown sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Cut in cold butter.
Top with walnuts. Sprinkle over pie.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: brunswick-style stew
directions: Put turkey legs in roasting pan and cook in 350° oven until golden brown.
Remove from oven; set aside to cool.
Cook and stir sausage in 4-quart Dutch oven until brown.
Remove from pan with slotted spoon onto plate and blot with paper towels.
Pour off all fat.
Trim meat from turkey bones and cut into bite size pieces. Return sausage, turkey pieces to Dutch oven and add water, onion, celery, basil, Tabasco and bay leaf.
Cover and simmer until turkey is tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Now add tomatoes, corn and carrots. Break tomatoes up by hand.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat; cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 20 to 25 minutes; remove bay leaf.
Can serve as is, or if thickening is desired, use cornstarch and water.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Serve immediately or add chips later.

title: four layer delight
directions: Beat until smooth.
Spread over cream cheese layer.
Spread with remainder of large carton Cool Whip.
If desired, top with chopped nuts or grated chocolate.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Brown the onion with the ground chuck.
Mix all ingredients and place in large pot.
Cook at low heat overnight or 4 hours at high heat.
Serves 8.

title: casserole barbecued chicken
directions: Dip chicken into flour mixed with salt.
Fry in hot fat until brown.
Remove chicken to 3-quart casserole.
Add onion to fat; saute until golden and tender.
Add celery and next 6 ingredients; pour over chicken.
Chill.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into balls about the size of marbles.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until brown.
Keep warm. Makes about 190 balls.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix butter, the sugars, vanilla and pudding.
Mix.
Beat in eggs. Gradually add flour and baking soda.
After mixed, add chips.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In saucepan, mix first 4 ingredients. Gradually add hot water, stirring constantly. Cook and stir over high heat until mixture comes to a boil. Reduce heat; cook and stir 2 minutes. Stir small amounts of hot mixture into egg yolks, then return to hot mixture. Bring to boil and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Add butter and lemon peel. Slowly add lemon juice, mixing well. Pour into pastry shell. Spread Meringue over filling. Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Cool before serving.

title: ro-tel beef dip
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Melt cheese in crock-pot or boiler. Mix all ingredients.
Heat thoroughly.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: water-crisped tortilla chips
directions: May use other seasoning of choice.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Cube bread; put in bottom of casserole.
Put meat on next, then potatoes.
Put cheese and margarine on top.
Mix eggs, milk and seasonings; pour over this.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef in butter.
Add soup, 1 3/4 cups water and mushrooms.
Simmer 40 minutes
or until beef is tender.
Stir in flour, blended with sour cream and remaining water.
Bring to boiling, then simmer, stirring constantly until sauce is thickened.
Cook noodles and mix with stroganoff.

title: skillet potatoes
directions: Melt butter or oleo in large skillet.
Saute onion and bell pepper until onion is translucent.
Add sliced potatoes; cook until soft, but not mushy.

title: shrimp patties
directions: Grind shrimp up coarsely in grinder or processor; add onion and remaining dry ingredients.
Add olive oil to shrimp, combine mixture and form patties.
May be baked, fried or frozen for later use.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix well.
Pour in a greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until it's done.

title: easy "top raman" salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Let stand overnight before serving.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Prepare separately yellow cake mix, adding flavoring, and the vanilla pie filling mix.
Bake cake per the directions on the box. When cake is cool, spread mix between the layers.
Frost, if you like, with fluffy white frosting and top with additional crushed pineapple.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: brownie mix(for a quick after school treat, keep this handy)
directions: In a large bowl, sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add sugar and cocoa.
Blend well.
With a pastry blender, cut in shortening until evenly distributed. Put in a large, airtight container. Label.
Store in a cool, dry place.
Use within 10 to 12 weeks.
Makes about 17 cups of Brownie Mix.

title: hoe cakes
directions: Heat 1/4 cup Crisco shortening or oil to 365° in electric skillet or on medium-high heat in heavy skillet.
Combine cornmeal and baking soda in medium bowl.
Add buttermilk, egg and 1 tablespoon melted shortening.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour 1/4 cup batter into skillet for each hoe cake. Fry 1 or 2 minutes or until golden brown on each side.
Add additional shortening, if necessary.
Drain on paper towels. Serve immediately.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Combine vanilla pudding mix and milk in bowl.
Beat well. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in frozen strawberries until separated and partially thawed.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Dilute cheese soup with 1/4 cup bean liquid and pour over beans. Stir in 1/2 can onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle the rest of the onions on top.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer.

title: pumpkin praline cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a Bundt pan well.
Combine cake mix, pumpkin, oil, light brown sugar, water and spices in electric mixer bowl and beat at medium speed 1 minute.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat after each egg another full minute.
Pour half of batter into prepared Bundt pan.
Top with praline mixture made by combining chopped nuts, dark brown sugar and butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May be frozen.
Thaw at least 1 hour before serving.

title: praline pecans(great holiday gift in festive canister)
directions: Mix all ingredients except nuts, vanilla and cream of tartar in deep Corningware casserole over moderate heat to "boil" while stirring for one minute.
Remove from heat; add and blend vanilla and cream of tartar.
Quickly add nuts, turning over with spatula to coat.
Pour out onto wax paper-covered surface and separate. Allow to "dry" and store in an airtight container.

title: oven pancakes
directions: Combine eggs, flour and milk; beat lightly with egg beater. Should be lumpy.
Heat butter in 11 or 12-inch cast-iron skillet until foamy.
Remove from heat, quickly add batter.
Cut apple into 1/4-inch slices, toss in juice and sugar, arrange in pinwheel in pancake before or during baking.
Bake 25 minutes or until brown at 425°.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar or jam.

title: homemade tomato juice
directions: Wash and scald.
Cut away hard stem or bruised places and quarter tomatoes.
Simmer until soft.
Stir occasionally.
Put through sieve fine enough to remove seeds.
Bring juice to boiling and pour immediately into sterilized Kerr jars filling to within 1/4-inch of top.
Add 1 teaspoon salt to each quart of juice.
Put on heated caps and bands firmly tight.
Process 15 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: apricot lemon cake
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add oil and cake mix.
Add jello (dry).
Add apricot nectar and lemon extract. Bake in a 10-inch tube pan at 300° for 1 hour.
While hot and still in pan, glaze with 1 cup powdered sugar, 1 teaspoon nectar and juice of 1 lemon, mixed.

title: rice dressing
directions: Mix all
ingredients together, diluting soup with 1 can water for each soup.
Pour
in casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: golden chicken nuggets
directions: Bone and halve chicken breasts; remove skin.
Cut each breast half into 6 to 8 pieces, about 1 1/2 inches square.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese, thyme, basil and salt on wax paper.
Dip chicken nuggets in melted butter, then in crumb mixture.
Place in single layer on foil-lined cookie sheets.
Bake in a hot (400°) oven for 10 minutes.

title: cinnamon toast
directions: First, put 2 pieces of bread in toaster.
Next, spread butter on them.
Then mix about 2 teaspoons sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cinnamon.
With a spoon, spread it on the bread.
Last, put the bread in the microwave for 20 seconds on High.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Set aside. In a cup, put shortening, orange juice and rind (chopped) and fill with boiling water to make 3/4 cup. Stir into dry ingredients. Bake in an ungreased loaf pan at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. May add orange juice to make a thinner batter.

title: berry pie
directions: Mix berries, sugar and flour.
Fill pie shell.
Sprinkle with peel and juice.
Dot with oleo.
Put top crust on; rub milk on top. Make slits.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: picadillo-fideo
directions: Brown beef and onions with spices.
Brown nest of vermicelli on each side of heavy large skillet or electric skillet.
Add tomatoes and enough water to cover vermicelli and meat.
Cook until water is absorbed and vermicelli is tender, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Shake well; serve over salad.

title: cranbrosia
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar.
Mix well to dissolve sugar. Drain well and reserve liquid from oranges and pineapple. Add oranges, pineapple, coconut and banana to cranberries.
Sprinkle gelatin over 3/4 cup of combined juices to soften.
Place over medium heat, stirring to dissolve.
Add fruit. Fold whipped cream into fruit.
Put in dish and chill until firm.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Wash raisins in hot water and drain.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and milk.
Combine with oatmeal and raisins.
Mix well.
Add flour, soda, salt and spices.
Beat thoroughly.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: oven-fried chicken
directions: Melt margarine in rectangular
pan in oven.
Mix baking mix, paprika, salt and
pepper; coat chicken.
Place skin side down
in pan.
Bake 35 minutes in 425° oven.
Turn; bake about 15 minutes or until done.

title: company casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook noodles as label directs; drain. In skillet, in 1 tablespoon butter, saute beef until browned. Stir in tomato sauce.
Remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese and next 4 ingredients.

title: shrimp-apple salad
directions: Combine shrimp, eggs, apple and green pepper with lemon juice and mayonnaise and mix well.
Serve on crisp lettuce.
Garnish with paprika.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Drain juice from pears.
Heat 1 cup of juice (if not one cup, add water to make 1 cup) to boiling point.
Pour over jello and stir.
Cool, but do not let set.
Mix cheese and 1 tablespoon cream; add jello and beat with electric mixer until blended. Chill until partly thickened.
Fold in mashed pears and Dream Whip or whipped cream.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour, salt and sugar. Add milk gradually. Stirring, cook over medium heat until thickened. When it boils, it is thickened. Stir in corn and eggs. Pour into a greased casserole. Set in shallow pan of hot water. Bake 15 minutes at 375°, then 30 minutes at 350°. Check; if knife placed into the center comes out clean and middle is firm, it is done. It usually takes at least 1 hour.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring the butter and water to a boil.
Add the flour; stir until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Add the eggs; beat in one at a time.
Beat until smooth.
Drop onto cookie sheet, using about 1/4 cup for each puff.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients; add water (a little at a time, until mixture is soft).
Form meatballs and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Then turn over and bake another 20 minutes.

title: roquefort cheese biscuits
directions: Mash cheese in bowl with mixing fork.
Beat in butter, cream and add egg yolk.
Knead in flour.
Form into ball.
Wrap in wax paper and chill until firm. Roll out to 1/4 inch.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch rounds.
Brush with egg and bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.
These can be baked, frozen and reheated for 5 minutes.

title: cherry slices
directions: Cream butter thoroughly.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add sifted dry ingredients gradually, beating well.
Spread in a large 11 x 17-inch greased pan, saving a little more than a cup of batter.
Spread cherry pie filling to within half-inch from edges of pan.
Place remaining dough by spoonfuls over the cherry filling.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
When cooked, sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes about 30 slices.

title: low-fat, low calorie egg nog
directions: Blend with mixer on medium speed until foamy.
Chill 24 hours. Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Mix meat and barbecue sauce.
Press biscuits into muffin pan, making cups.
Spoon meat mixture into each cup and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 350° until biscuits brown.

title: scotch shortbread
directions: Mix butter and sugar, stir in flour.
Mix thoroughly with hands.
Chill dough.
Roll out 1/3 to 1/2 inch thick.
Cut into fancy shapes.
Flute edges by pinching between fingers.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 300° about 20 minutes.
Do not let brown.
Yields about 2 dozen cookies.

title: pinwheels
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Spread cream cheese on tortillas. Sprinkle chopped olives over cheese.
Roll tortillas.
Slice tortillas.
Serve with picante sauce.

title: 5 layer blueberry cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Put equal amounts of batter in two 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes or until springs back.
Cool in pans.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Sift dry ingredients together to remove lumps.
Pour cold water into mixture.
Cook in microwave until boiling, 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour in cold milk.
Can add butter, if desired.
Spoon over toast or biscuits.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Soak eggplant in salt water 1 hour.
Rinse.
Beat egg and milk together and pour over eggplant and let stand a few minutes. Drain.
Coat with flour and fry until brown in hot oil.
Drain.

title: golden carrots
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter, peel, onion and dill.
Add oranges. Heat.
Cook carrots until tender.
Combine with sauce. Sprinkle with cashews.
Serves 6.

title: corn chowder
directions: Wash and cut wings into 1 to 1 1/2-inch pieces crosswise.
Stir bacon in Dutch oven over high heat.
When fat from bacon starts to melt, add onion.
Cook until glossy, stirring.
Add turkey, salt and pepper.
Stir 2 minutes over high heat.
Add carrots, celery and water.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 2 hours.
Add undrained corn; cook 30 minutes.
Mix half and half with flour in a small bowl.
Add 1/2 cup hot chowder; mix well. Continue adding chowder in small amounts and mixing until flour completely dissolves with no lumps.
Stir into chowder.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes.
Serve garnished with parsley.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Add Italian seasoning and salt to each layer.
Cook zucchini until half done.
Brown the hamburger and drain.
Layer zucchini in a buttered casserole dish.
Next, layer mushrooms, cheese and hamburger; repeat.
Cover with tomato sauce.
Bake in 350° oven until it bubbles.

title: 1-2-3 peanut butter cookie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and then add Bisquick.
Drop by small teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind together the cranberries and oranges.
Add sugar and nuts.
In a separate dish, dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Combine cranberry mixture and Jell-O.
Chill.

title: baked chicken breasts supreme
directions: Cover each chicken breast half with 1 slice of ham and 1 slice of cheese.
Put about 1 tablespoon of stuffing in the center of each.
Roll up and secure with a toothpick.
Place rolled up chicken breasts in a greased casserole.
Combine soup and sour cream, mixing well, and pour over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours, basting occasionally.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine everything except pecans.
Stir until well blended. Stir in pecans.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: quick key lime pie
directions: Mix together the limeade and sweetened condensed milk.
After mixed well, fold Cool Whip.
Place in graham cracker crust and chill in refrigerator.
Great after a heavy meal, light and refreshing.

title: good dip
directions: Mix picante sauce, peach preserves and mustard.
Pour over cream cheese.
Serve with different kinds of crackers.

title: sugar coated peanuts
directions: Dissolve sugar in water in saucepan over medium heat.
Add peanuts and continue to cook over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Cook until peanuts are completely sugar coated and no wet syrup.
Pour and spread over ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, stirring at 5 minute intervals.
Then bake 2 hours at 200°, stirring, or until done.

title: sweet and sour cabbage soup
directions: Brown meat in heavy pot.
Add salt and pepper to taste, tomatoes, water, onion soup, sugars, cabbage and lemon juice. Cover and simmer 2 hours.
If desired, more lemon juice or sugar may be added.
Cabbage will not be mushy due to lemon juice and tomato.
This is very good with corn bread.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together well and enjoy.

title: french apple cobbler
directions: Combine apples, 1 cup of sugar, 4 tablespoons of flour, cinnamon, 1/2 teaspoon salt and water.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch pan and dot with butter.
Beat together 1 cup of flour, 1 cup of sugar, baking powder, 1/2 teaspoon salt, butter and eggs.
Drop by spoonfuls on apple mixture.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin nut tea bread
directions: Add sugar and oil; mix well.
Add pumpkin and eggs.
In a separate bowl, mix all the dry ingredients.
Combine the 2 mixtures.
Add nuts.
Pour into 2 ungreased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Eat one; freeze one.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and milk.
Boil, then remove from heat.
Add beaten egg yolks, stirring fast.
Mix all together and bake.

title: cranberry sauce
directions: Boil apple juice; add sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cranberries and apples.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add oranges and peel. Stir.
Chill.
Can be made ahead and refrigerated.

title: norwegian health bread(grovbrod)
directions: My mother did not have time to make thin lefse, living on a large farm.
She made thick lefse called potato cakes and we loved them.
So here goes!
I'll try to remember.

title: chocolate pies
directions: Cook ingredients until thick.
Pour mixture into pie shells. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: coconut yellow layer cake
directions: Cream butter until very light in color.
Gradually add sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, until well mixed.
Sift flour, baking powder and soda together.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk to butter mixture.
Add vanilla.
Fold in with a large spoon. Pour into 3 (9-inch) greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.
Let layers cool completely before frosting. Use the recipe for Lemon Frosting to frost this cake.
When cool and icing is made, spread on layers and sprinkle on coconut.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix marshmallows, pecans and pineapple; stir in sauce.
Mix cream cheese that has been whipped with juice of pineapple.
Let stand overnight.
Fold in cream that has been whipped.
Put in paper cupcake cups.
Garnish with cherry, half pecan or something of your choice.
Place in freezer and serve as needed.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix milk, cream, sugar, salt, and vanilla.
Heat to lukewarm and add junkets.
Mix well.
Pour in freezer and allow to stand for five minutes before freezing.
Add any fruit desired prior to pouring into freezer.

title: scalloped potatoes with ham
directions: Peel potatoes and slice medium thin.
Melt butter on high heat.
Stir in flour and seasoning.
Add cold milk, then cook on medium until sauce begins to thicken.
Turn to low and stir occasionally until sauce is thick.
Then stir in cheese.
In 3-quart casserole, alternate layers of potatoes and ham.
Pour sauce over this and bake, uncovered, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 375°.

title: roast beef spirals
directions: Whip cream cheese, garlic and ginger.
Spread generously and evenly on roast beef slice and roll up lengthwise.
Wrap rolls in foil and freeze for at least 30 minutes.
Remove from freezer and immediately cut into 1-inch wide slices.
Garnish with green olive or cut pickle chunk.
Attach with cellophane tipped toothpick. Makes 36 spirals.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut steak into small cubes.
Flour and brown in large boiler in about 1/4 cup oil.
Add a small amount of flour to absorb the remaining oil; brown.
Then add enough water to fill boiler half full; add potatoes, chopped onion and sliced carrots.
Cook slow for 2 hours or until meat and potatoes are tender.
Add water whenever needed.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: In a heavy pot mix sugar and flour, gradually add in eggs and milk.
Add water and vanilla and heat just until hot (do not boil). Pour into freezer can and finish filling with milk.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: baked cheese grits
directions: Cook the grits in water, milk and salt.
When thick, remove from the heat.
Add the cheese, butter and Tabasco.
Beat the eggs and gradually add the hot grits.
Pour in a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until top is brown (can be fixed 24 hours ahead and brought to room temperature before baking).

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, sour cream, and eggs.
Set aside.
Mix together brown sugar and cinnamon.
Put half the cake mixture in a pan, sprinkle brown sugar mixture over top.
Then put the rest of the cake mixture on top. Swirl the mix in the pan with a knife. Bake at 350 for 20 to 30 minutes or until done.
Mix last three ingredients and pour over hot cake.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: In a blender, blend chocolate chips and coffee until chocolate is melted.
Add eggs and rum and blend until smooth.
In a chilled bowl, whip 1 cup heavy cream until it holds stiff peaks; fold into chocolate mixture.
Transfer to dessert glasses and chill for 30 minutes.
Garnish with extra whipped cream and chocolate shavings. Serves 4.
(Recipe can not be doubled.)

title: myra's cheese ball(from kitchen fixins-humc 1978, myra kilgore)
directions: Combine cheese, fruit and nuts and form into a bowl.
Roll in additional chopped pecans.
Makes a ball the size of a grapefruit.

title: microwave hot roquefort canapes
directions: Place cream cheese in small microwave bowl; heat, uncovered, on defrost 30 seconds or until cheese is soft.
Add Roquefort cheese chopped walnuts, mustard and Worcestershire sauce to blend. Spread cheese mixture on crackers.
Arrange a maximum of 10 canapes on large paper plate or microwave serving platter lined with a paper or cloth napkin.
Heat, uncovered, on roast for 1 minute or until cheese begins to melt.
Top with a piece of walnut; serve hot.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients well; place in baking dish.

title: mama's buttermilk fried chicken
directions: Place flour, salt and pepper in paper bag.
Add 2 or 3 pieces of chicken and shake until well coated.
Dip in buttermilk and place in flour again; coat.
Drop chicken in hot oil and fry until done.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix well.
Makes enough for a 2 1/2 pound fryer or 6 pork chops.
Put in iron skillet; cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Stir flour and baking powder together.
Melt butter and brown sugar over low heat.
Stir in slightly beaten egg; blend in dry ingredients, mixing well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in
a greased and floured 8-inch square pan in a slow oven (300°) for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cut while warm.

title: strawberry walnut loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Beat together the sugar, butter and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
In medium bowl, combine flour, oats, baking powder and salt.
In small bowl, combine preserves and sour cream.
Add dry ingredients alternately with preserves to batter mixture, mixing well until well blended. Stir in nuts.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake about 45 minutes; tent bread with foil and continue baking until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean or 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: peanut butter crumb cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt; cut in butter and peanut butter until mixture resembles corn meal.
Reserve 2/3 cup.
To the remaining mixture, add milk, eggs and soda, dissolved in water and flavoring.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry mousse(light and refreshing!)
directions: You will also need foil muffin cups.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Place hamburger rolls on cookie sheet (1/2 roll at a time). Spread with pizza sauce and top with Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni, if desired.
Bake in oven at 425° until cheese is melted.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and rub each with oil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Allow to cool to touch.
Cut each potato in half and scoop out pulp, leaving shells intact.
Mash pulp and add remaining ingredients and 1/2 of cheese.
Mix well.
Stuff shells and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: lo-cal pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and yogurt.
Spread in pie shaped container.
Put strawberries on top.
Serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in a little bit of salted water until tender and drain well.
In saucepan, cook onion, carrots and 4 tablespoons margarine until tender.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups stuffing, soup and sour cream.
Stir in squash gently.
Pour mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Melt remaining margarine and toss remaining stuffing in it. Use as topping prior to baking.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
