tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Combine Ro-Tel and cheese in a microwave-safe bowl and microwave until cheese is melted, stirring often.
Add both cans of soup; mix well.
Combine chicken, onion and 1/2 package of crushed chips in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour soup and cheese mixture over chicken mixture and stir.
Cover with remaining crushed chips.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: quick sugar-free oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, oats and sweetener together. Set aside.

title: potato candy
directions: Boil the potato until well done.
Remove from water and mash with butter.
Slowly add sugar.
Roll onto waxed paper 1/8-inch thick.
Spread peanut butter over; don't go to the edges.
Roll up.
Slice into pinwheels.
Refrigerate.

title: cottage salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together with a large spoon thoroughly. Chill 1/2 hour before serving.

title: pie filling jam
directions: Boil or simmer together for 10 minutes.
Take from heat and stir in Jell-O, using a flavor that goes with the pie filling. Stir until dissolved.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: sparkling fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit; reserve juices.
Add water to juice to make 1/2 cup.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in cranberry sauce, pecans, oranges and pineapple.
Pour into lightly oiled 4 cup mold.
Chill.

title: simple stuffed flounder
directions: Mix crabmeat, buttered crumbs, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Lay fish flat.
Spread mixture on top and then roll fillets like a jelly roll.
Place rolls in a shallow baking dish lined with butter.
Then pour white sauce over fish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk.
Bring to a rolling boil. Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add chocolate chips, marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Stir until well blended. Pour into pan and cool.

title: strawberry delight cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add sugar and salt.
Stir until dissolved.
Add frozen berries to hot mix.
Set aside, stirring frequently until berries thaw. Place in refrigerator to thicken, but not jell.

title: stephanie's southern pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, and butter; add eggs and pecans and pour into a 9 inch crust.
Bake in preheated 375 degree oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all together.
Use 3 heaping teaspoonfuls to a cup of boiling water.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut the elephant into bite size pieces.
(Preparation time: approximately 2 months.)
Add the gravy to elephant pieces and cook over kerosene fire about 4 weeks at 465°.
Serves 3,800.
If additional guests drop in, 2 rabbits may be added, but do this only if necessary, as most people do not like to find hare in their stew!

title: chocolate bit graham bars
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Pour into an 8-inch buttered pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cut in small pieces while warm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli; spread drained broccoli in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Cook one stick butter, flour, bouillon cubes and milk until thick.
Use double boiler if you wish.
Top broccoli with cream sauce.
Mix water, 6 tablespoons butter and croutons. Spread this over the broccoli and sauce.
Bake at 350°.

title: shiloh spiced tea
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Store in a covered container. When serving, add 2 to 3 teaspoons of mixture to hot water.

title: beef stew
directions: Use a crock-pot or an oven dish.
Add enough water to cover. Add more later, if needed.

title: drop cookies
directions: Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: peppermint patties
directions: Heat milk, extract, food coloring and 6 cups sugar until smooth.
Turn onto surface sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Knead lightly to form smooth balls.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on wax paper-lined baking sheets, flatten each ball into a 1 1/2-inch patty.
Dry at least 1 hour on each side with fork.
Dip into warm coating, using pan rim to scrape off excess. Invert onto wax paper-lined baking sheets.
Let stand until firm. Store at room temperature or in refrigerator.

title: burnt sugar cake
directions: Burn 1/2 c. sugar until liquidized.
Add 1/4 c. water, stirring well.
Set aside.
Cream 1 1/2 c. white sugar, cold water, butter, egg yolks, and half of the flour.
Beat batter for 5 minutes.
Add egg whites, well beaten to other half of flour with baking powder.
Combine with batter and flavor with vanilla. Add burnt sugar.
Cook in a moderate oven.

title: yoga sicles
directions: Put all the ingredients in a big bowl.
Stir them together until its all mixed up. It should all be light purple.
Pour mixture into cups overnight and put it in the freezer.
Also place a popscicle stick in the glass, so you can get them out after its frozen.

title: cocktail meat balls or frankfurters
directions: Mix
beef,
bread
crumbs, egg and salt;
shape into 50 small meat balls (1/2 inch).
Place in shallow baking pan (13 x
9 x 2 inches).
Broil until browned;
turn once.
Spoon off fat. Meanwhile,
in
saucepan, cook onion and green pepper in butter until
tender.
Stir
in
remaining ingredients.
Pour over
meat balls.
Cover;
bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Makes 50 meat balls for appetizers.

title: instant cookies
directions: Combine biscuit mix and pudding mix in bowl.
Stir in oil and egg.
Mix thoroughly and shape into small balls (about a teaspoon each).
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with finger or spoon.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Add all ingredients at once.
Fold gently; can't whip. Refrigerate.

title: egg and cheese casserole
directions: Precook meat.
Cut into pieces.
Tear up bread.
Slice or cube cheese. Place alternate layers of bread and cheese in casserole. Beat eggs with milk, salt, mustard and Worcestershire.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Pour melted butter over top.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 300°, covered, for 1/2 hour and uncovered for 1/2 hour.
Add meat on top.

title: jean's hamburg casserole
directions: Make stuffing mix according to directions.
Put half of hamburg in casserole, crumbled up, then half of stuffing, then other half of hamburg and other half of stuffing.
Top with can of cream of mushroom soup.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: bacon and tomato dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender or food processor.
Blend until smooth.
Put in container and cover.
Chill at least 1 hour. Serve with assorted crackers.
If desired, hollow out a round loaf of bread and place dip inside.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.
Very good.

title: leftover meat and rice casserole(ham, chicken, turkey, beef)
directions: While rice is cooking per instructions, saute onion and celery in 1 to 2 tablespoons butter.
Add soup, milk and cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Stir together with rice and meat.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
If casserole seems a little dry, add more milk.
Top with shredded cheese, if desired.

title: corn chowder
directions: Chop bacon and place in
pan
to
brown.
Add celery, pepper and onion.
Fry together until bacon is brown.
Add corn and saute together for 3 minutes.
Add the
chopped vegetables and 2 cups of water.
Cover and cook slowly for 30 to
minutes.
Then
add rich
milk; heat to boiling again.
Add chopped parsley.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add ice cream and stir until melted.
When mixture thickens, fold in strawberries.
Fill pie shell (browned) or for a lovely "dressier" dessert, fill parfait glasses with mixture.
Garnish with a dollop of Cool Whip and a fresh whole strawberry.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Line and butter a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers. Make pudding using 3 cups milk. Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour half over layer of crackers, then second layer of crackers.
Pour remaining pudding layer, followed by third layer of crackers.
Pour icing on top.

title: gourmet ham casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package direction.
Drain and rinse. Place noodles in well-buttered 13 1/3 x 8 3/4 x 3/4-inch baking dish.
Place ham cubes on noodles and sprinkle with cheese. Pour half and half over top.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: southwestern pasta accents
directions: Prepare Pasta Accents according to package instructions.
Add lime juice, cilantro, cayenne pepper and black pepper; mix thoroughly.
Garnish with fresh chopped tomato.
Serves two as a main vegetarian meal.

title: potato onion supreme
directions: Cook potatoes, peel and slice 1/4-inch thick.
Set aside. Place onions, water and bouillon in a saucepan; bring to a boil, then simmer 5 to 7 minutes or until onions are tender.
Drain and set aside.

title: lemon cake top pudding
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Stir in beaten egg yolks of 3 eggs. Mix in milk; fold in stiffly beaten whites.
Pour into custard cups or single dish.
Set in pan of water.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Fry hamburger and drain.
In saucepan, add hamburger, potatoes (diced), onions (diced), carrots (sliced crosswise), green pepper (diced) and peas, including liquid.
Cook until veggies are tender.
Add the rice and let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on box.
Add pineapple to pudding and mix together.
Let set overnight.
Next day, add marshmallows, chopped nuts and whipped topping to the pudding.
Mix all together. You can chill or serve right away.

title: confetti salad
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients together, cool.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate.
This will keep in the refrigerator several days.
Food processor may be used to chop vegetables. Serves 8-10.

title: picante sauce
directions: Put all of the ingredients in large pot and bring to a boil. Simmer for 20 minutes.

title: shrimp diavolo
directions: Brown onion in olive oil.
Add seasonings and marinara sauce. Simmer for 10 minutes; add shrimp.
Simmer for additional 10 minutes.
Serve over linguini.

title: three-bean salad
directions: Mix beans, onions and parsley.
Mix Italian dressing, sugar and garlic; pour over salad and toss.
Cover and refrigerate, stirring occasionally, at least 3 hours.
Just before serving, remove salad to lettuce-lined salad bowl with slotted spoon. Serves 6.

title: lemon blueberry bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter together until fluffy; add eggs and beat well.	Stir in milk, set aside.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together, add 1/2 tsp. of lemon rind.
Stir by hand dry ingredients into cream mixture until flour is just moistened. Gently fold in blueberries.
Pour batter into greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
For glaze mix powdered sugar, lemon juice and remaining lemon rind; pour over hot bread before removing from pan.	Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes whole.
Boil eggs.
Let cool.
Cut eggs and potatoes up together in small pieces.

title: mexican cheese bites
directions: Mix the baking mix, sour cream, egg and chilies.
Stir in cheese.
Cover and refrigerate up to 4 hours.

title: end of season relish
directions: Chop vegetables, place in pan in layers, sprinkling each layer with salt.
Let stand overnight, drain and press out all liquid. Add sugar, vinegar, mustard and paprika to vegetables.
Cook 1 1/2 hours, stirring often.
Pour into clean jars and seal.

title: english custard squares
directions: Melt 2 squares chocolate and 1 stick butter in small saucepan. Add beaten egg, graham cracker crumbs, vanilla, coconut and nuts. Mix and press into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Put in refrigerator until firm.
Mix 1/2 cup melted butter, confectioners sugar, instant pudding and milk.
Put on top of crust.
Return to refrigerator until firm.
Melt 4 squares chocolate and 1 1/2 tablespoons butter.
Pour over other layers. Refrigerate until firm.
Keep in refrigerator because of egg.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve with crackers. If you'd like, you can form the mixture into a ball and roll in nuts.

title: mustard pickles
directions: Make a bring of 4 quarts water and 1 pint salt and pour over vegetables (cucumbers, tomatoes, onions and cauliflower).
Let set 24 hours.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients with mixer or blender.
Then put in ice cubes and blend.

title: eggplant oyster bake
directions: Scoop out eggplant pulp and chop.
Saute pulp in butter with onion, celery, garlic, parsley and thyme until lightly browned. Add bread crumbs.
Stuff eggplant shells with mixture or bake in baking dish.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs; add milk, salt and dry mustard. Layer sausage, cheese and bread.
Pour liquid over.
Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Rotate pan every 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat egg yolks well.
Beat in whiskey a little at a time. Beat egg whites, adding sugar.
Fold whites into yolk mixture, then fold in cream.

title: penne with broccoli
directions: Rinse broccoli.
Cook in boiling water for about 5 minutes. Heat butter in a large skillet.
Saute onion and mushrooms with basil, oregano and salt until soft.
Add broccoli.
Sprinkle with flour.
Stir to combine.
Add milk.
Heat to a boil, stirring. Lower heat.
Cook for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add Cheddar cheese and 1/2 of the Parmesan cheese.
Meanwhile, cook the pasta according to package directions.
Drain well.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together and drop in greased muffin tins.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 rolls.

title: ham loaf
directions: Grind together ham and pork.
Add eggs, cracker crumbs and milk.
Make into a loaf.
Mix together vinegar, brown sugar, water, dry mustard and pineapple juice.
Bring to boil and pour over loaf.
Bake for 2 hours at 350°.
Baste often.
Watch closely at end as syrup burns easily.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Have two 11 x 7-inch baking dishes ready. In large saucepan, cook onion in oil 5 minutes or until translucent.
Stir in chili powder, garlic powder and cumin.
Add cream cheese and cook over low heat, breaking cheese into chunks with a wooden spoon until melted.
Add chicken and salsa. Stir over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes until hot.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 1/4 cups of the Cheddar cheese and the olives.

title: golden apple bundles
directions: In a bowl, combine apples, nuts, brown sugar, raisins, flour, lemon peel and cinnamon; set aside.
Roll pastry to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut into 5-inch circles.
Spoon about 1/4 cup apple mixture into center of each circle.
Moisten edges of pastry with water.
Fold over and seal edges with a fork.
Place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Check and bake 10 minutes longer.
Brush each with milk and sprinkle with sugar. Return to oven for 5 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef with 1 large onion or use chopped up, stewed chicken plus onion.
Add beans, corn, taco seasoning mix, Ranch style dressing mix, stewed tomatoes, Ro-Tel tomatoes and green chilies.
Add water or chicken broth if chicken meat is used. Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: cool cake(no fat)
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
Substitute unsweetened applesauce instead of oil.
Use egg whites (no yolks).
Bake about 25 minutes.
Let cool.
Punch holes in cake.
Mix one box of sugar-free strawberry jello with 3/4 cup hot water and pour over cake.
Frost with lite Cool Whip and decorate with fresh strawberries.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Drain fruit; save juices.
Add water to juices to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Bring to a boil.
Add both packages jello.
Stir well.
Add sherbet.
Dissolve. Chill until slightly thickened. Fold in fruit.
Spoon into a 6-cup jello mold.
Chill until set. Unmold onto platter.
Garnish with lettuce leaves, orange slices and sour cream.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan combine 1 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually stir in water until smooth.
Stir in slightly beaten egg yolks.
Stirring constantly, bring mixture to a boil over medium heat, and boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon peel, lemon juice and butter.
Spoon hot filling into pie shell.
In small bowl with mixer at high speed, beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually beat in remaining 1/3 cup sugar.
Continue beating until stiff peaks form.
Spread meringue evenly over hot filling, sealing to crust.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Refrigerate.

title: mama's copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in salted water and drain.
Add onion.

title: cupcakes
directions: Put them in the oven.
Cool off.
Then eat them.

title: diabetic cheesecake
directions: Dissolve gelatine in water; set aside.
Beat cottage cheese to just reduce curds.
Beat cream cheese; then gelatine.
Mix well. Add vanilla, lemon juice, maple syrup, fructose and Sweet 'n Low. Mix well.
Pour into shell and chill for 2-3 hours.

title: potato soup
directions: Beat flour, milk and eggs to make paste.
Add to cooked tender potatoes and their water.
Add milk to the desired consistency. Add parsley and onion if desired.

title: sugar-free, fat-free lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix all of this together with the help of a mixer, then fold in 1/2 tub of lite Cool Whip.
Mix good and put into graham cracker pie crust.
Chill.

title: microwaved snackin' nuts(microwave oven)
directions: In a 1-quart glass measuring cup, melt (High) butter 30 seconds; add nuts.
Microwave (High) 4 to 5 minutes, stirring every minute.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and brown sugar; add to nuts, coating evenly.
Cool, spreading evenly on bread board.
Serve warm or cold.
Store in freezer for later use if desired.
Makes 2 cups.

title: fried tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into 3/4-inch slices.
Dip into egg and then into crumbs.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add tomato slices and cook until golden brown on each side.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients and place in 1 1/2 to 2-quart baking dish. Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milks and boil for 3 minutes.
After it reaches a rolling boil, add the marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Cool and cut.
(It doesn't get real hard.)

title: 24-hour slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Slice very thin the onion and bell pepper. Put in large bowl that has a tight lid.
Mix sugar, salad oil, vinegar, celery seed, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Let come to a boil.
Make sure sugar is dissolved.
Let cool a few minutes. Pour over cabbage but do not stir.
Place lid on and refrigerate overnight.
Stir next morning.
This will stay good in refrigerator for a week.

title: quick clams and pasta
directions: Put oil, garlic, oregano, parsley, clams with juice and seasonings in a saute pan.
Heat through and then add mushrooms. Set aside until spaghetti is cooked al dente.
Add it to the pan and toss to distribute clam mixture.
Toss in Parmesan.
Top with Mozzarella; cover and heat over low heat until cheese melts. Serves 4.

title: garlic cheese biscuits(red lobster)
directions: Heat
oven
Mix biscuit mix and milk until a soft dough
forms.
(May need a bit more milk to mix easily.) Stir
in grated cheese and drop by spoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until golden.

title: frozen lemon pies
directions: Beat egg yolks with condensed milk and lemonade concentrate. Chill.
Fold whipped cream into lemonade mixture; fold in egg whites.
Spoon into pie shells, cover and freeze for 6 hours. Serve with additional whipped cream.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Stir all together and pour in dish.

title: no cook divinity
directions: Combine dry frosting mix, corn syrup, vanilla and boiling water in small mixer bowl.
Beat on highest speed until stiff peaks form, about 5 minutes.
Transfer to large mixer bowl.
On low speed or by hand, gradually blend in sugar.
Stir in nuts. Drop mixture by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
When outside of candy feels firm, turn over and allow to dry at least 12 hours. Store candy in airtight container.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.
Divinity can be frozen in airtight containers up to 2 months.
tags: Betty Crocker fluffy white frosting mix

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add other ingredients and congeal.

title: communion bread
directions: Cut shortening into flour.
Add enough water to make a dough. Roll dough thin.
Cut with top of lipstick tube.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for about 20 minutes.
(Do not brown.)
Makes 350.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix and bake in a greased 2-quart casserole dish at 350° for 40 minutes.
This may be mixed the night before and baked next morning.

title: dump cake
directions: Put pineapple, then pie filling in a large loaf pan.
Cover with the cake mix and then pour the melted butter over the mix. Cover with coconut.
Nuts or chocolate chips may be added if desired.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Cover with aluminum foil when coconut turns brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender; drain.
Mix cornbread as directed on package.
Add sage and soup.
Add cornbread mixture to squash.
Cover with Velveeta cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: skillet salisbury steak
directions: Combine soup, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and horseradish; set aside.
Form patties with milk, egg, crumbs and onion.
Brown patties in skillet.
Pour off excess fat.
Cover with soup mixture.
Cook on low 30 minutes, adding water as needed to form gravy.
Makes 6 servings.
Only 1 pan!!

title: date loaf cake
directions: Pour hot water over dates; add butter and sugar, mixing well. Stir in egg, salt, soda and flour until well blended.
Stir in pecans and cherries.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan; bake at 250° until toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: japanese pokkar sweet and pungent spareribs
directions: Parboil spareribs.
Marinate in vinegar, sugar, maple syrup and soy sauce for several hours.
Remove ribs; brown in large skillet.
Just before ready to serve, add onions, celery, pineapple, carrots and green pepper.
Mix cornstarch with marinade.
Add to skillet.
Cook until thickened and vegetables are cooked slightly; they should be
crisp.

title: tuna zucchini cakes
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter.
Cook onion until tender, but not brown.
Remove from the heat.
Add tuna, zucchini, eggs, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 of the bread crumbs.
Stir until well combined.
Shape into six patties; coat with bread crumbs and fry in hot cooking oil, about 3 minutes on each side, until golden brown.

title: casey's chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
When done, cut in small pieces.
Mix soups and tomatoes together; add chicken pieces.

title: chicken in italian dressing
directions: Prepare chicken in pan with Italian dressing, enough to cover chicken.
Sprinkle with thyme.
Fry until done.
If needed, add more Italian dressing.

title: red salmon loaf
directions: Flake salmon into bowl.
Add cracker crumbs, egg white, onion, green pepper and milk; mix well.
Pack into 5 x 9-inch loaf pan. Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix cheese, onion, soup, eggs and mayonnaise together.
Add cooked and drained broccoli.
Pour into casserole.
Mix enough Ritz crackers with melted margarine until crumbly and use as topping for casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: grandma white's easy dessert
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to package directions.
Mix in applesauce.
Chill until set.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: hamburger skillet supper
directions: Brown beef; drain off fat.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Stir in onion, beans and sauce.
Beat until stiff and sticky the biscuit mix and milk.
Wrap a little dough around a cube of cheese and seal.
Drop into simmering mixture.
Cover; simmer for about 5 minutes.
Serve with a green salad.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Dice apples.
Cook flour, sugar, vinegar, pineapple juice and egg until thick.
Cool.
In large bowl, mix marshmallows, pineapple, apples, peanuts and cooled sauce, then add Cool Whip.
Chill 2 hours.

title: spiced chicken
directions: On wax paper, mix spices and flour; coat chicken. In a large nonstick skillet, heat oil. Add chicken; cook 5 minutes per side or until cooked through.

title: dog biscuits(for real - feed these to your dog)
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube in water.
Mix with rest of the ingredients.
Shape as desired and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: citrus glazed leg of lamb
directions: For glaze:
Combine cornstarch, cinnamon and nutmeg in saucepan.
Stir in honey and water.
Add orange and lemon slices. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove and discard orange and lemon slices.
Add walnuts and raisins.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Chop bacon and fry; drain grease.
Add chopped onion and brown.
Mix in crock-pot the beans, bacon, onion, vinegar, sugar and catsup.
Cook on low 3 to 4 hours.

title: sour cream dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Serve on salad greens, vegetable salads, cole slaw, baked potatoes, etc.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and dry green tomatoes.
Slice tomatoes medium-thin. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Remove chicken from bone; set aside.
Mix until mealy the flour, salt, Crisco and water, or until like biscuit dough. Knead well.
Roll out real thin.
Bring to boil broth chicken was cooked in.
Drop dough into broth; drop enough to make thick but still soupy.
Add chicken and black pepper to taste.

title: 6 minute fudge
directions: In a large saucepan, bring to a boil the sugar, cream of tartar and evaporated milk.
When it comes to a boil, cook for 6 minutes by the clock, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon.
Remove from heat.
Pour over bits of margarine.
Stir until completely dissolved.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir.
Pour into a greased pan (I use margarine).
Allow to stand at room temperature for approximately 1 hour.
Cut in squares or refrigerate overnight and cut the following day.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour over chicken or baste chicken.

title: irish tea bread(cut and come again cake)
directions: Place raisins, tea (or beer) and brown sugar in a large ceramic or glass bowl.
Mix; cover with cloth and let sit overnight at room temperature.

title: raspberry chicken salad
directions: Stem, gently rinse berries, pat dry and set aside.
Toss diced chicken with celery and almonds, then raspberries.
In a separate small bowl, blend mayo or yogurt with grated lime rind, juice and salt.
Pour over chicken; gently toss to coat.
Serve on crisp lettuce leaves.
Serves 4.

title: crab spread
directions: Lightly butter a dinner plate, then ice it with the cream cheese.
Drain and wash crabmeat; spread on top of the cheese. Spread chili sauce on top of the meat.
Serve with crackers.

title: pineapple pecan bread
directions: Cream shortening, gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add egg, beating well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; add to cream mixture, alternating with juice and beating well after each addition.
Stir in pineapple and pecans.
Pour batter into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes then remove to rack.
Cool completely.

title: hawaiian lime pie
directions: Combine pie filling, 1/3 cup sugar, salt and water in saucepan.
Mix in egg yolks, 1 cup water and pineapple juice. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil. Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar, beating until soft peaks form; fold into hot pudding.
Pour into pie shell.
Garnish with Dream Whip or whipped cream and pineapple chunks.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Combine hominy, mushrooms and pimientos in 2-quart casserole dish; set aside.
Saute onion and green pepper in margarine until tender.
Add Cheez Whiz to onion mixture.
Pour over hominy and mix well.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Microwave 5 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: chunky cheese spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken in oil in large skillet until no longer pink (5 minutes).
Remove chicken from pan and drain all but 1 tablespoon oil.
Add zucchini, bell pepper, mushrooms, onion and garlic to skillet.
Cook and stir over medium heat until crisp-tender.
Add chicken and spaghetti sauce.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Add 1 cup cheese; cook and stir just until cheese melts.

title: fudge cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and cocoa in 2-quart saucepan. Gradually stir in milk and cook over medium heat until thick. Remove from heat.
Stir a small amount of hot mixture into beaten egg yolks.
Return to saucepan mixture and cook 5 minutes more. Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Cool 5 minutes and pour into baked pie shell.
Spread meringue to edges, covering pie, and bake about 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: grandmother's coffee cake
directions: Cut butter into flour and sugar mixture.
Reserve a scant cup. Combine dry and liquid ingredients. Bake in greased square pan. Sprinkle reserved dry mixture over top of batter before baking. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Arrange caps in buttered dish.
Chop stems into tiny pieces.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Mix well together; the Spam will give the spread a good flavor if it is baked before mixing with the other ingredients.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Saute meat and onion.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add chili to meat mixture and heat.
Arrange a layer of corn chips, a layer of meat and chili mixture and a layer of cheese in a baking dish. Repeat layers and top with corn chips.
Heat in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: central park hot dogs
directions: Brown onion and garlic in oil lightly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Serve on plates with mustard or you can fill pastry triangles with a hot dog and some of the sauce, roll up and bake, then serve with mustard.

title: warriors casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add cheese but reserve some to garnish. Combine meat, soup, cheese, milk, green peppers and garlic salt. In a 2-quart casserole dish, layer 1 cup of meat mixture and 4 tortillas.
Repeat layer 2 more times.
Top with remaining mixture.
Cover and bake for 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Just be served top with lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.
Delicious with pinto beans.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Beat mashed sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and margarine until smooth.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix brown sugar, flour, margarine and pecans together.
Sprinkle mixture over sweet potato mixture in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cook bacon until crisp and crumble.
Chop onions and beef. Mix all ingredients together and form into ball.

title: clam chowder
directions: Drain juice from clams and add to vegetables.
Add enough water to barely cover vegetables.
Simmer, covered, over medium heat until tender.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine Master Cake Mix and the spices in a bowl.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix well.
Add bananas and then buttermilk with soda; beat.
Add vanilla and nut meats.
Bake in 9 x 7 x 5-inch loaf pans at 325° for about 1 hour.
When done, remove from pans and cool.
Cover with icing.

title: chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: Cut sausage into small slices and microwave for 3 minutes. Put oil in a Dutch oven.
Add pepper and onion; cook until tender. Add broth and rice.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes.
Add cut up chicken and sausage and all other spices.
Stir.
Add more broth to keep from sticking.
Taste.
Add more spices, if needed.
Cover and cook until rice is done.

title: green tomato jelly(you would think it is raspberry by taste and appearance.)
directions: Boil the chopped tomatoes and sugar for 30 minutes until mush. Add the jello; mix well.
Pour into jars.

title: witches brew
directions: Combine apple juice, water and lime juice in a large bowl. Cover mixture and chill.
